title: bark covered pretzels
directions: Melt bark.
Dip pretzels into it, then lay out on wax paper until they harden.
Using a 2-tined fork to spear the pretzels works well and can be done at one time.

title: cottage cheese salad
directions: Combine ingredients.
Fold in whipping cream and chill for several hours before serving.

title: chili
directions: Mix all ingredients together, except meat.
Fry hamburger meat, drain and add to all other ingredients.
Cook until done.

title: puppy chow party mix
directions: Pour cereal in large Tupperware bowl.
In small saucepan, melt chocolate chips, peanut butter and margarine. Pour over cereal and shake until all is coated. Open bowl and dump powdered sugar and shake again.
Good for parties and family gatherings.

title: finger lickin toffee
directions: Melt butter.
Add sugar and stir until dissolved.
When boiling, add Karo and water.
Set candy thermometer in pan.
Cook to hard crack stage (300°), 20 to 30 minutes.
Remove and spread on sheets of aluminum foil greased with oleo.
Spread chocolate wafers immediately.
Then sprinkle 1/2 of the chopped nuts.
Turn foil over and do other side with chocolate and nuts.
Work fast!

title: surprise pie
directions: Beat egg whites until frothy.
Add cream of tartar and sugar and beat until stiff.
Fold in cracker crumbs, nuts and vanilla. Pour into greased 9-inch pie pan.
Bake at 325° for 40 minutes. Cool.
Whip the cream and spread over pie.
You may want to put strawberry topping on pie before whipped topping.
Other toppings may be used.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Boil the whole chicken; put 3 bay leaves in the water as it cooks.
Remove bay leaves when done.
Cook until tender enough to pull off bone.
Remove all the skin and break chicken into small strips.
Put the rice on the bottom of a buttered pan.
Add 1/2 of chicken; pour the cream soups over it, except for onion soup.
Add rest of chicken.
Add 1/2 cup broth that chicken was cooked in. Stir ingredients of pan until barely moist.
Add margarine and milk.
Pour onion soup over top.
Let bake until good and bubbly, about 30 minutes at 350°.

title: pumpkin seeds
directions: Wash all seeds and pat dry with children.
Place on a cookie sheet.
Cover thickly with salt.
Bake or broil until golden brown.
Yum!

title: cream cheese hors d'oeuvre
directions: Mound cream cheese in center of a serving tray.
Mix shrimp and sauce together and pour over top of cheese.
Garnish with parsley. Surround with crackers.

title: hearts of palm salad
directions: Sprinkle avocado with lemon juice, tossing to coat.
Combine with the next 4 ingredients; toss gently.
Refrigerate.
Combine remaining ingredients and shake vigorously.
Chill.
Toss salad with dressing before serving.
Serves 8.

title: swiss and tuna buns
directions: Spoon mayonnaise into a bowl and blend in tuna, cheese, onions, salt and lemon pepper.

Spoon mixture onto bottom half of bun. Cover with top half and wrap each sandwich separately in foil. Place on baking sheet and bake at 350° for 20 minutes. Remove from oven and carefully unwrap before serving. Serve immediately.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook fresh squash; drain and mash. Add the rest of the ingredients, reserving half of the dressing mix. Combine well. Line a casserole dish with reserved dressing which has been mixed with 1/4 pounds margarine, saving some to sprinkle on top of finished dish. Fill with squash mixture and cover with remaining dressing mix. Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: pralines and cream
directions: Combine above ingredients and bake at 350° for 20 minutes, stirring every 5 minutes.
Cool.
Mix will be crumbly.
Pack half of the mixture in a 9 x 15-inch pan.
Pour 1 (12 ounce) jar Kraft caramel topping over this.
Soften 1/2 gallon vanilla ice cream and pour over mix.
Pour another jar of caramel topping over mix and top with rest of crunchy mixture.
Freeze.
Serves 20.

title: holiday cheese ball
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Mix well with hands.
Shape into ball.
Garnish with chopped parsley, sliced olives and chopped pecans.

title: hungarian goulash
directions: Saute onions in butter or margarine about 5 minutes.
Add beef and rest of ingredients.
Simmer, covered, for 2 hours, stirring occasionally.

title: green pepper steaks
directions: Cut beef into thin strips 1/8-inch thick.
Combine soy sauce, garlic, ginger and beef.
Toss and set aside.

title: pork chop casserole
directions: Combine rice, seasoned package rice mix and hot water.
Place in greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Set aside.
Sprinkle pork chops with pepper.
Place over rice mix.
Cover and bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Uncover casserole.
Combine celery soup and milk.
Pour over casserole.
Bake another 15 minutes uncovered.

title: pineapple lime salad
directions: Heat juice to dissolve gelatin, then mix all ingredients together in mold or container of choice.
You can add some chopped pecans if you like it nutty.

title: vegetable soup
directions: In a large pot, put shredded cabbage, soup meat, bones, onions and celery.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Cover with water and let simmer for 3 or 4 hours.
Then add potatoes, mixed vegetables, stewed tomatoes and beef consomme.
Salt and pepper to taste. Simmer until vegetables are cooked.

title: poppy seed cake
directions: Sugar
and
cinnamon mixed together the amount desired. Spray Bundt
pan
and
cover with sugar and cinnamon mixture. Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: cottage potatoes
directions: Combine all ingredients except potatoes.
Pour over potatoes and mix lightly.
Put in greased 3-quart casserole dish.
Top with 2 cups crushed potato chips and 1/4 cup melted oleo.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: vodka sauce for pasta
directions: Heat the oil in a medium saucepan.
Brown onion and garlic in hot oil; add vodka and boil for about 5 minutes.
Add tomatoes and spices to taste and simmer for about 30 minutes.
Add cream immediately prior to serving.
Heat through but do not bring to boil.
Serve with tube shaped pasta such as ziti or rigatoni.

title: strawberry cake
directions: Thaw strawberries. Mix evenly. Measure five ounces of berries for cake and five ounces for frosting. Use one tablespoon juice from berries for cake; add water to make 1/2 cup liquid. Put cake mix and flour into large mixing bowl.

title: stuffed eggs supreme
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a small skillet, cook mushrooms with tarragon in 2 tablespoons oleo until all liquid evaporates.
Melt 4 tablespoons of oleo in another saucepan.
Blend in flour, salt and pepper and cook, stirring, for 1 minute.
Add cream; cook, stirring, until mixture boils and thickens slightly.
Remove from heat.
Add Swiss cheese and 2 tablespoons Parmesan; stir until cheese melts.

title: cinnamon rolls
directions: Mix cake mix, yeast, flour and warm water.
Let rise until double in size.
Cut dough in half.
Roll into rectangle on a floured surface; spread with butter or oleo.
Sprinkle with white powdered sugar and cinnamon.
Roll in jelly roll fashion; cut into 2-inch rolls.
Repeat with second half of dough.
Place in two greased 9 x 13-inch pans.
Let rise.
Bake at 375° for 25 minutes.

title: peach pie
directions: Line pie plate with bottom crust.
Melt butter; add sugar, flour, lemon juice, salt, and cinnamon and mix well.
Place peaches in crust-lined pie plate and cover with butter and brown sugar mixture.
Add top crust, cut slits for venting, and sprinkle lightly with sugar.
Bake at 425° for 35 minutes, or until peaches are tender and filling is bubbly in center.

title: mrs. beam's bourbon pecan cake
directions: Soak raisins in bourbon overnight.
Cream butter and sugar. Gradually add eggs, one at a time, beating after each addition. Add flour which has been sifted with baking powder and salt.
Add raisins and pecans, mixing well.
Pour batter into greased and lined tube pan or greased and floured bundt pan.
Bake at 325°F. for 1 1/2 hours or until cake is done.
Cool cake on rack.
After cooling, wrap in towel soaked with bourbon and place airtight container.

title: potato soup
directions: In 3 quart saucepan over medium heat cook onion in butter and thyme until tender.
Stir in potatoes, water and salt.
Reduce heat to low, cover and simmer 20 minutes or until tender.
Beat mixture with beater until smooth.
Gradually add milk.
Heat just to boiling.
Makes 5 cups.

title: chicken chip casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Combine all ingredients; sprinkle potato chips on top.
Bake for 30 minutes.
Double recipe for 4.

title: grapefruit cooler
directions: Combine grapefruit
juice,
grenadine,
lime
juice and pour the mixture into a tall glass half filled with ice cubes. Fill the glass with ginger
ale
and
garnish
with a wedge of lime.
Makes 1 drink.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Saute onion in butter.
Combine soup, cheese, mustard and vinegar; leave on heat only long enough to heat through.
Layer in 9 x 9 x 2 1/2-inch pan the broccoli, eggs and cooked mixture, ending with mixture.
Bake, uncovered, 25 minutes at 350°.
Remove from oven and top with French fried onions.
Return to oven for 5 minutes.
Prepare this at least eight hours before baking and refrigerate (best overnight).
It will fill your pan if doubled.

title: sweet and sour green beans
directions: Saut bacon pieces until almost brown (maximum 5 minutes). Add 1/4 cup minced onion.
Add liquid from the beans; cook on medium high until the liquid boils out by half.
Add vinegar and sugar; stir.
Add beans; stir.
Add a couple shakes of pepper. Cook until tender 20 to 30 minutes.

title: vegetable pizza(appetizer)
directions: Spread crescent rolls out on a 13 x 18-inch pan.
Pinch edges together to make solid.
Bake as directed on package; cool.
Mix together cream cheese and Ranch dressing; spread on baked crust. Chop vegetables into small pieces; spread on top of cream cheese. Cut into small bite size pieces.

title: cottage cheese puff dinner rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
In a saucepan, heat cheese over low heat until lukewarm.
Add sugar, salt, soda and eggs; stir into yeast mixture.
Slowly add flour and mix in until dough cleans the bowl.
Let double in a warm place.

title: chili macaroni
directions: Cook and drain macaroni as directed.
Then stir all ingredients over medium heat until thoroughly heated.
Garnish with sour cream, sliced pitted ripe olives and chopped bell peppers, if desired.
Makes 4 servings.

title: chess pie
directions: Beat eggs; stir in sugar.
Add butter and flavoring.
Mix well.
Pour into 8-inch uncooked pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes or until done.

title: jean's mushroom tarts
directions: Cut 2/3
cup of butter into 2 1/2 cups of flour and 1/2 teaspoon
of
salt.
Add
sour cream and egg.
Mix thoroughly. Using 1
teaspoon of dough, press into tiny muffin cups.
Bake at 400°
for
to 15 minutes.
Meanwhile for filling, saute onions and
mushrooms in 1/4 cup of butter.
Stir in flour and salt.
Add heavy
cream,
stirring
constantly,
until thick. Fill shells. Shells
can
be
baked and frozen or filled with mushroom
mixture and
then
frozen.
To
serve frozen filled shells, do not thaw, bake at 400° for 12 minutes, then serve.

title: pecan pie squares
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Mix baking mix and granulated sugar.
Cut in margarine until crumbly.
Press mixture in ungreased rectangular pan, 13 x 9 x 2-inch.
Bake until light brown, 10 to 12 minutes; cool.

title: corned beef and cabbage
directions: Cut the corned beef into small chunks. Place in a 4-quart slow cooker. Sprinkle with pickling spices included with the corned beef. Add onion and potatoes. Cover with water. Add salt and pepper. Place cabbage on top of meat and vegetables. Do not mix in with the rest of the ingredients. Cook on low setting for 8 to 10 hours or on high for 5 to 7 hours.

title: old fashioned greens
directions: Remove all stems from mustard and turnip greens.
Place salt pork in 3 cups water in saucepan.
Cover and bring to a boil.
Add greens and turnips.
Bring to a boil again.
Cook until greens are tender, adding water, if necessary.
Serve with corn pone.

title: pea salad
directions: Drain all canned vegetables.
Put all of the ingredients in a large bowl and cover with dressing.

title: skillet chicken in orange sauce
directions: Melt butter in Dutch oven over medium heat, add chicken and brown on all sides.
Remove chicken from Dutch oven and set aside; reserve drippings in pan. Combine flour and next 4 ingredients and stir into drippings.
Cook over medium-high heat, stirring constantly, 1 minute.
Gradually stir in orange juice and water. Bring mixture to a boil; add chicken.
Cover and simmer 25 minutes.
Place orange slices on top of chicken.
Cover and simmer 10 minutes or until chicken is done.
Serve over rice.
Yield:
4 servings.

title: tabooleh with feta cheese
directions: Soak bulghur in water for 1/2 hour.
Chop scallions, parsley, mint, cucumber and tomatoes very fine.
Drain bulghur and add. Serve with Syrian bread.

title: simple cherry squares
directions: Combine sugar and margarine at high speed until smooth.
Add 1 egg at a time to mixture at medium speed.
Add vanilla, then flour, mixing well.
Spread into ungreased jelly roll pan (10 x 15-inch).
Mark into 2-inch squares.
Spoon 1 to 2 cherries from pie filling into center of each square.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes only until light golden brown.
Do not overbake. When cool, cut into 2-inch squares.
Makes 35.

title: vegetable soup
directions: Cook short ribs with lots of water slowly for 4 to 5 hours. Remove meat.
Add everything except for corn and tomatoes.
Cook 15 minutes after water starts to boil.
Add corn and tomatoes; turn heat down low.
Do not boil after adding corn and tomatoes.

title: date pie
directions: Cream Criso, sugar and salt until light and fluffy.
Stir in eggs.
Add milk.
Stir in dates.
Pour into unbaked pie shell and bake at 450° for 10 minutes; then 325° for 40 minutes longer. Serve plain or with whipped topping.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Saute green pepper, red pepper, onion and mushrooms in

2 tablespoons butter and 1/2 teaspoon garlic powder. Add cooked cubed chicken to mixture. Add celery soup. Cook spaghetti; drain. Add to mixture. Combine. Put in 13 x 9 casserole dish. Pour broth over mixture. You can top with shredded Cheddar cheese and broken potato chips. Bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes.

title: turkey casserole
directions: Cube turkey.
Cook thin spaghetti according to directions. Make white sauce (see Micro Cookbook recipe).

title: 7-layer dip
directions: In serving dish, layer the first 7 ingredients in order listed. Chill and serve with Fritos scoops, corn chips or Doritos.

title: melty moments cookies
directions: Let margarine soften; add flour, sugar, vanilla and pecans. Drop by teaspoon onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 7 to 10 minutes.

title: perfect pancakes
directions: In medium bowl, stir together flour, oat bran cereal, sugar, baking powder and salt.
In small bowl, beat egg whites with electric mixer until stiff.
Stir oil into milk, then add to flour mixture, stirring just until combined.
Fold in egg whites.

title: jellied shrimp salad
directions: Heat together first three ingredients and combine with gelatin.
Add remaining ingredients and pour into mold. Refrigerate until firm.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Mix sugar, salad
oil
and
eggs together.
Sift flour, baking powder, soda, salt
and cinnamon together and then stir in with the mixture of
sugar,
salad
oil and eggs.
Then add zucchini and nuts.
Put
into 2 greased loaf bread pans.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: hawaiian bread
directions: Combine the flour, sugar, salt, baking soda and nuts.
Then add remaining ingredients and blend carefully by hand.
Stir just until blended.
Place in 2 well-greased and floured pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Test with toothpick for doneness.

title: chicken sopa
directions: Mix soup, milk, chilies, chicken, onion and water in pan and heat thoroughly.
Line a large, long casserole dish with tortilla pieces.
Layer soup mixture, cheese, tortilla pieces, etc.
End with cheese pieces on top.
Heat in oven until bubbly.

title: greek veggies
directions: Heat olive oil and garlic; stir in vegetables and stir-fry for 2 minutes.
Add dill and cooking sherry; stir-fry another 1 to 2 minutes.
Add Feta cheese; cover the pot and remove from heat. Let cook in own heat for 2 to 5 minutes.

title: pineapple bake
directions: Blend butter, sugar and eggs. Place torn bread into baking dish. Pour milk over it. Add pineapple, then sugar mixture. Stir. Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: apricot jello salad
directions: Bring gelatin, pineapple, sugar and baby food to boil in medium saucepan.
Cool.
Beat cream cheese with mixer, then gradually add the gelatin mixture.
In separate bowl, whip the chilled evaporated milk until stiff.
Fold it into the gelatin and cream cheese mixture.
Place in an 8 1/2 x 11 1/2-inch pan. Sprinkle with ground pecans.
Serves 15 to 20 people.

title: orange glazed smokies
directions: Put Smokies in iron frypan.
Stir until they are warm.
If there is any fat or water in the pan, blot it out with the paper towels.
Mix the next 2 ingredients together and pour over Smokies.
Keep stirring around until the glaze is almost used up. Stick each one with a toothpick and sit on a plate.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Mix oil, eggs, sugar, orange extract, lemon peel and vanilla. Add zucchini, salt, soda, baking powder, cinnamon and ginger. Finally, add flour; blend well, then add nuts.
Bake in greased and floured loaf pans (2 large loaf pans or 6 small foil loaf pans).
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: chicken cacciatore
directions: Heat
oil
and	margarine
in a 14-inch Dutch oven. Dry thighs with
paper
towels and put in Dutch oven.	Brown well. Add tomato
sauce,
tomatoes,
juice, basil, oregano, garlic, parsley, salt, pepper and bay leaf.
Simmer, covered, 1 hour. Add water and
flour	mix and stir into the sauce.
Add mushrooms and cook for 10 minutes more.

title: pasta pizza
directions: Prepare macaroni by package directions.
Blend milk, Egg Beaters, salt and add macaroni; mix well.
Spread into a 15 x 10-inch baking sheet sprayed with cooking spray.
Combine tomatoes with spaghetti sauce and cooked turkey.
Spread on top of macaroni.
Next, layer the bell peppers, onions and Italian seasoning.
Top this with grated cheese.
Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes.
Let stand 5 minutes before cutting.
Serves 10.

title: katherine hepburn brownies
directions: Melt chocolate and butter over low heat in heavy saucepan. Remove from heat and stir in sugar. Beat in eggs and vanilla. Quickly stir in walnuts, flour and salt. Spread batter on well-greased 8 x 8 pan. Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes. Remove and let cool on rack. Cut into 12 pieces.

title: best barbecue sauce
directions: Mix ingredients in saucepan and bring to a boil, stirring constantly until thick.
Place meat in a single layer in a greased baking dish.
Do not prebrown meat.
Bake about 1 1/2 to 2 hours at 350°.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Mix eggs, sugar and Crisco together.
Mix your sour cream and soda in a cup separate.
Take your egg mixture and add your sour cream mixture and blend together.
Add vanilla.
Take and blend your mixture with flour to make a drop cookie and sprinkle with sugar.
Bake about 20 to 30 minutes.

title: three bean salad
directions: Combine and refrigerate for 24 hours.
Can be doubled.

title: poppy seed bread
directions: Add and mix ingredients.
Batter will be soupy.
Bake in preheated oven, 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.
Makes 2 loaves.

title: flaky biscuits
directions: Mix all ingredients and roll dough in approximately 2 cups dry Bisquick.
Form biscuits and place in skillet greased with butter-flavor Crisco.
Melt 1/4 cup butter-flavor Crisco; brush on top of biscuits before baking.
Bake at 375° until brown.

title: baked fish with lemon butter sauce
directions: Season fish with salt and pepper both sides and arrange fish in buttered baking dish.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Heat remaining ingredients and pour over fish.
Bake uncovered for 30 minutes or until fish flakes.
Sprinkle with paprika and garnish with lemon slices.
This is good using almost any fish.

title: chicken and broccoli casserole
directions: First boil chicken. You can season the broth with whatever you want. Cook broccoli according to package directions. Save 1/2 cup of the chicken broth. Layer the following ingredients: shredded chicken, cream of broccoli soup, 1/2 cup chicken broth and Cheddar cheese. Bake for 20 minutes at 350°. Add French fried onions and bake 5 more minutes.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Boil chicken 45 minutes to 1 hour in salted water.
Remove chicken from bones.
Cook rice in 1/2 chicken broth and 1/2 water. Mix all ingredients well.
Put in casserole, cover and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Simmer 10 minutes.
Makes delicious barbecued beef, chicken or pork.

title: easy apple fritters
directions: Unfold pastry sheets and roll them out into 1 large rectangle.
With short side facing you, spoon pie filling on pastry and roll up jelly roll style.
Place seam side down on a well greased baking sheet.
Brush with mixture of egg and water. Bake for 35 minutes at 375 degrees.
Cool and slice to serve 10.

title: oriental casserole
directions: Brown hamburger and onion.
Mix soup, milk and cheese; heat enough to melt cheese.
Cook noodles for 4 minutes.
Drain.
Add cooked meat and onion to noodles.
Put mixture into 9 x 13-inch greased pan.
Pour soup, milk and cheese mixture over meat/noodles.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Remove from oven.
Sprinkle chow mein noodles and nuts on top.
Continue baking for 10 minutes.

title: simple never-fail yeast rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in lukewarm water in bowl.
Stir in sugar, eggs, oil and salt.
Add flour, 2 cups at a time, mixing to form stiff dough.
Place in oiled bowl, turning to oil surface.
Let rise, covered with damp cloth, until doubled in bulk.
Knead on floured surface until smooth and elastic.
Shape into rolls; place in greased baking pan or muffin cups.
Brush with oil.
Let rise until doubled in bulk.
Bake at 350° for 17 to 20 minutes or until golden brown.
May glaze or brush with melted margarine.
Yield: 36.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Cook at 300°.
I like to use coffee cans to bake this in.
Just grease and flour 3 cans to bake in.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Beat together and freeze.
Put into pie crust, graham or chocolate cookie.
Top with fudge topping or chocolate syrup.
Put in pie crust before freezing.

title: blueberry yum yum
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients; let set.
Pour over cream cheese, sour cream, sugar and pecan mix in mixer.

title: crock-pot stew
directions: Cook all day in slow cooker.

title: custard pie
directions: Combine eggs, sugar and salt.
Add milk, vanilla and nutmeg. Stir until blended and pour into pie shell.
Bake at 400° for 40 minutes or until done.

title: chocolate cheesecake
directions: Preheat oven to 325°
Combine cracker crumbs, sugar and melted butter or margarine.
Pat into bottom of 11 3/4 x 7 1/2 x 1 3/4-inch glass baking dish.
In saucepan, over very low heat, stir together chocolate chips and milk until just melted.
Beat cream cheese and sugar until light and fluffy.
Beat in eggs and vanilla.
Stir in chocolate mixture, then fold in sour cream. Pour into graham cracker crust and bake 40 to 50 minutes or until set in center.
Allow to cool thoroughly.
If desired, spread cherry pie filling over top of cake.
Refrigerate before serving. Serves 12.

title: crock-pot chocolate covered peanuts
directions: Will need 1 yard (3 feet) of wax paper or more.

title: chicken and sausage gumbo
directions: Place flour on baking sheet and bake at 400° for 20 minutes. Stir every 5 minutes.
Flour should be very brown.
(Works well in toaster oven.)
Set aside.
In a large, heavy pot coated with nonstick cooking spray, saute vegetables until tender.
Add browned flour (roux), stirring constantly.
Gradually add water, tomatoes and chicken; bring to a boil, lower heat and simmer 1 hour.
While gumbo is cooking, boil sausage in water in a pot until done.
Slice in 1-inch slices and add to gumbo.
Cook an additional 20 minutes.
Add green onions, cooking 10 more minutes. Skim any fat from surface of gumbo.
Serve over rice.
Yields 10 to 12 servings.

title: make ahead oriental salad
directions: Combine vegetables in a large bowl, stirring gently.
Combine remaining ingredients and pour over vegetables.
Cover and chill 24 hours.
Drain just before serving.
Yields 10 to 12 servings.

title: sweet potato puffs
directions: Mash potatoes.
Add sugar and raisins (coconut if desired). Add flavoring.
Roll in crushed corn flakes and roll into balls. Press down and place on cookie sheet.
Put cherry on top.
Bake at 350° about 20 to 25 minutes.

title: budget steak
directions: Mix ingredients thoroughly.
Shape to look like 1 1/2-inch steak.
Place on broiler.
Broil 10 to 15 minutes on one side. Turn and broil on other side.
May freeze.

title: saucy meat ball casserole
directions: Combine beef, pork, bread crumbs, 1/3 cup evaporated milk, onions and pepper.
Mix well.
Shape by tablespoons into meatballs. Brown.
Cover.
Cook 10 minutes.
Place in 2 1/2-quart casserole. Combine both soups, 1 cup evaporated milk and 1/2 cup water.
Heat until steaming.
Pour over meatballs.
Top with biscuits.

title: catherina's ham
directions: Place ham in roasting pan. Drain juice from pineapple chunks into a measuring cup. Pour into a bowl. Add an equal amount of maple syrup and mix. Pour over ham and cover.
Bake 15 minutes per pound at 350°. Thirty minutes before the ham is done, add pineapple chunks. Cover and finish baking.

title: heath bar cake
directions: Bake cake according to directions (use rectangular pan).
As soon as out of oven, use handle of wooden spoon and poke holes over top.
Pour condensed milk and caramel over cake.
Cool completely.
Cover top with Cool Whip.
Sprinkle with crushed Heath bars.
Keep in refrigerator; gets better with age also. Freezes well.

title: chicken parmesan
directions: Combine bread crumbs, cheese, salt and pepper.
Dip chicken breasts in melted butter, then in bread crumbs; coat heavily. Place breasts, skin side up, in dish and bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes, uncovered.
Do not turn chicken.

title: pam's mega soup
directions: Saute first four ingredients in drippings until onion is clear.
Add Ro-Tel, Worcestershire, water and bouillon.
Bring to a boil; reduce heat and simmer.
Add mixed veggies and potatoes. In separate skillet, brown meat.
Drain fat.
Season generously with salt and black pepper.
Add garlic powder and Italian seasoning.
Simmer a few minutes more.
Add contents of skillet to soup.
Simmer for 40 minutes to 1 hour.
Great as is or serve with rice.

title: pecan graham cookies
directions: Preheat the oven to 350°.
Line cookie sheet with graham crackers.
Melt butter and brown sugar together.
Bring to boil and boil for 2 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Mix in nuts.
Pour over graham crackers.
Bake for 10 minutes.

title: praline grahams
directions: Separate each graham into 4 sections.
Put foil on jelly roll pan.
Arrange crackers with edges touching.
Melt butter in saucepan.
Stir in sugar and pecans.
Bring to boil and cook 3 minutes, stirring frequently.
Spread mixture evenly on crackers. Bake at 300 degrees for 12 minutes.
Be careful, and do not burn. Remove from pan.
Cool on wax paper.

title: swiss steak
directions: Dredge meat with flour.
Brown in hot fat over medium heat. Sprinkle with seasonings.
Add onion and 1/2 cup liquid.
Cover and simmer 1 1/2 hours until tender.
Add second 1/2 cup liquid during cooking.
Yields 6 servings.

title: laura ann's chicken stuff
directions: Line bottom of greased 9 x 13-inch pan with dried beef, cut in strips.
Wrap 1 slice bacon around each chicken breast. Place on top
of
beef.
Mix soup and sour cream together and pour over top.
Be
sure
all
of chicken is covered.
Bake 3 hours at 325°, uncovered.

title: deviled eggs
directions: Cut eggs lengthwise.
Remove yolks and mash yolks well.
Blend all other ingredients, then put the mixture back into the egg white.
Top with an olive or paprika.

title: kidney bean sandwich
directions: Combine beans, pickles, egg and celery lightly.
Add sour cream to salad.
Chill and serve on lettuce leaves or chopped greens.

title: fresh fruit dip
directions: Mix milk, orange juice and pudding together. Let set for 2 to 3 minutes. Add Cool Whip. Chill. Serve with fruit.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: In a 7 x 11-inch greased baking dish, place bread and add cheese.
In medium bowl, beat eggs, salt, pepper and mustard.
Add milk to egg mixture and pour over bread and cheese.
Add meat. Refrigerate overnight.
Bake in morning at 350° for about 50 to 55 minutes.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: coconut sour cream cake
directions: Prepare cake mix according to package directions, making two 8-inch layers.
When completely cool, split both layers.
Combine sugar, sour cream and coconut, blending well.
Chill.
Reserve 1 cup sour cream mixture for frosting.
Spread remainder between layers of cake.
Combine the one cup reserved sour cream mixture with the Cool Whip.
Blend until smooth.
Spread on top and sides of cake.
Sprinkle coconut on top of cake and chill before serving.

title: peanut butter icing
directions: Cream margarine; add peanut butter and salt.
Blend thoroughly.
Add rest and beat.

title: sweet pickled beets
directions: Cook beets until tender.
Combine all other ingredients in 4-quart pot.
Slip skins off beets.
Simmer in mixture for 15 minutes.
Fill scalded jars to overflowing and seal at once.
No processing needed.
Yields 3 quarts pickled beets.

title: easy chili
directions: Brown hamburger with onions.
Drain off fat.
Add chili beans and tomato sauce.
Season with chili powder and pepper to taste. If desired, cooked macaroni can be added.

title: bud's chili
directions: In a large skillet, add meat, chopped onions, garlic and all spices.
Cook until meat is done.
Add remaining ingredients and simmer at least 2 hours.
Adjust spices according to your taste.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Beat until light and fluffy the shortening, white sugar, brown sugar, eggs and vanilla.
Mix together flour, salt and baking soda and add to the mixture.
Then add the quick oatmeal and mix.
Then add the chocolate chips.
Drop on ungreased cookie sheets and bake at 375° for about 10 minutes.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Beat eggs; add all other ingredients.
Add zucchini last. Pour in greased pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: pineapple squares
directions: Mix flour, 1 egg, 1 tablespoon sugar, salt, 1/2 cup butter, 1 tablespoon milk and baking powder.
Roll to fit pan and cover with 1 small can drained, crushed pineapple.
Mix together 1 cup sugar, 2 beaten eggs, vanilla, 1 tablespoon melted butter and coconut and spread on pineapple.
Bake at 350° for about 40 minutes.

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour into greased dish.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: double peanut butter bread
directions: Spoon flour, add all remaining ingredients except nuts.
Stir with wooden spoon thoroughly.
Stir in peanuts.
Spread batter in greased loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 55 minutes.
Cool 5 to 10 minutes in pan.
Cool on rack.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Mix the first 4 ingredients in a large bowl; add flour, soda, cinnamon and salt.
Add this to the first 4 ingredients and mix well.
Stir in 3 cups of apples and nuts.
Bake 1 1/2 hours at 325° in tube pan.

title: chocolate trifle
directions: Bake cake in 9 1/2 x 11 1/2-inch oblong pan.
Grate Heath bars.
Make pudding as directed on package.
Defrost Cool Whip. Cut cake in small square pieces and line the bottom of a bowl (clear glass looks best).
Cover cake with layer of pudding, then a layer of Cool Whip and then a layer of candy.
Repeat until all ingredients are used up.

title: rocky road fudge
directions: Line 13 x 9 pan with waxed paper. Cut another piece of waxed paper to use to help put mixture in pan. Set aside. In glass bowl, put Eagle Brand milk, butter and chips. Melt in microwave. Be careful not to scorch. In a large bowl, put marshmallows and peanuts. Pour melted chocolate into bowl with peanuts and marshmallows. Put in 13 x 9 pan quickly. Use wax paper to help spread. Put in refrigerator until set. Cut into squares.

title: one-step chocolate cupcakes
directions: Put ingredients in bowl in order listed.
Do not mix until last item has been added.
Blend lightly.
Beat well.

title: sweet onion-smothered hamburgers
directions: Coat a large nonstick skillet with cooking spray, and place over medium heat until hot.
Add onion rings; cover and cook 10 minutes or until limp and golden, stirring occasionally.
Reduce heat to low, and stir in 1/4 c chili sauce and grape jelly.
Cover and cook 5 minutes, stirring occasionally.

title: pecan cake
directions: Cream butter; add sugar gradually.
Add beaten eggs, one at a time.
Sift flour with baking powder.
Dredge fruit with part of it.
Add flavoring, then fold in flour.
Add nuts and fruit last. Bake in loaf pan in slow oven at 300° for 1 hour and 45 minutes.

title: pineapple cream salad
directions: Dissolve lime Jell-O in 1 cup boiling water.
Add cream cheese, crushing with fork until almost dissolved.
Add pineapple, evaporated milk and nuts.
Pour into mold and chill until set.

title: caramel nut pound cake
directions: Mix in mixer.
Grease and flour a tube cake pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 to 2 hours.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: microwave brownies
directions: Microwave on Defrost for 7 minutes.
Turn dish and microwave on High (9) for 4 to 5 minutes or until done.
Bake in a 9 x 13-inch glass dish.

title: vegetable pizza
directions: Spread dinner roll dough onto pizza pan.
Bake as directed on package; let it cool.
Mix the cream cheese, sour cream, mayonnaise and Ranch mix in bowl.
Spread mixture onto crust. Cover mixture with tomatoes, broccoli, carrots, onions, cucumbers and green peppers.
Top off with Cheddar cheese.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
In a 10 x 6-inch dish, put cooked broccoli; nicely top with chicken.
In a small bowl, mix soup and milk; pour over chicken.
Sprinkle with cheese.
In a cup, combine bread crumbs and butter; sprinkle over cheese.
Bake for 15 minutes, or until bubbly.

title: chocolate noodle candy
directions: Melt all morsels over hot water.
When melted, add Chinese noodles and nuts.
Drop by teaspoon onto wax paper.
Chill in refrigerator.
I usually double this recipe.
They go fast!

title: chilies rellenos bake(a hearty "hot" chili bake for simple suppers)
directions: Brown beef and onion; drain.
Sprinkle meat with 1/2 teaspoon salt and 1/4 teaspoon pepper.
Halve chilies crossways; remove seeds.
Place half of the chilies in a 10 x 6 x 1 1/2-inch baking dish; sprinkle with cheese.
Top with meat mixture.
Arrange remaining chilies over meat.
Combine remaining ingredients; beat until smooth.
Pour over chilies.
Bake in a moderate oven (350°) for 45 to 50 minutes until knife inserted comes out clean.
Cool 5 minutes before serving.
Makes 6 servings.

title: sausage-velveeta casserole
directions: In a
10-inch
skillet,
brown beef, sausage and onion. Drain fat. Add tomato paste, water, oregano and salt. Simmer 5 minutes.

title: dump cake
directions: Mix together pie filling and pineapple in bottom of a 9 x 11-inch cake pan.
Prepare cake mix as directed on box and pour over mixture.
Melt butter and pour over cake.
Bake at 350° for about 45 minutes.
Serve from pan.

title: taco macaroni salad
directions: Mix in order given.

title: tater tot and beef casserole
directions: Brown beef and onion.
Add seasoned salt to the beef.
Drain beef and spread on the bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cover the beef with Tater Tots.
Dilute the two cans of soup with only 1 cup of water.
Pour the mixture over beef and Tater Tots.
Sprinkle the Cheddar cheese over the top.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.
Serves 12.

title: five cup salad
directions: Mix all ingredients and chill.

title: vegetable soup
directions: Saute celery, carrots and onions in olive oil (about 5 minutes).
Add parsley.
Sprinkle with seasonings (Italian and garlic).
Add parsnip and turnip.
Saute lightly (about 3 minutes).
Add broth and simmer until vegetables are tender (20 plus minutes).
Add barley and cook until tender (about 10 minutes).

title: baked chicken rolls and gravy
directions: Roll 2 to 3 slices of beef and wrap with 1 chicken breast. Wrap 1 slice of bacon around and stick with 1 or 2 round toothpicks to hold all pieces together.
Mix soups and sour cream to make a sauce and pour into baking dish.
Place the 6 chicken rolls into sauce and spoon each roll with the sauce.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°. Pour sauce over each roll every 15 to 20 minutes.
You may want to turn on broiler for a few minutes after chicken is done to brown or crisp the bacon.

title: linguine and clam sauce(a favorite)
directions: Saute onion and garlic in butter or margarine.
Add clams, mushrooms and cream.
Toss with pasta.
Stir in cheese and parsley.
Let set 15 minutes or more.
Makes 8 good size servings.

title: southern style cabbage
directions: In 5-quart Dutch oven or 12-inch skillet, cook bacon over medium heat until browned.
Add cabbage, onion and salt.
Stir to coat cabbage evenly with bacon drippings.
Add water and reduce heat.
Cover and cook 30 minutes, stirring occasionally, until cabbage is tender and lightly browned.

title: edith's squash casserole
directions: May substitute 1 can of cream of celery or mushroom soup for milk and flour.

title: banana bread
directions: Cream butter, honey and eggs.
Beat in bananas.
Add soda, salt and flour gradually; then add broken walnut pieces.
Butter and flour loaf pan.
Bake at 325° for 45 to 50 minutes.
The top will be cracked.

title: chili
directions: In skillet, cook ground beef, green pepper, onion and garlic until meat is browned.
Drain off excess fat.
Stir in undrained kidney beans, tomatoes, tomato sauce, chili powder, salt, dried basil and pepper.
Bring to boil.
Simmer about 20 minutes.
Serve with cornbread or over rice.

title: 5 flavor pound cake
directions: Cream together oil, butter and sugar.
Add eggs.
Sift flour and baking powder.
Add flour alternately with milk.
Add flavorings.
Bake at 325° in greased and floured tube pan for 1 hour and 35 minutes.

title: grape-nuts dessert
directions: Mix vanilla pudding with milk as box directs.
Mix everything together and refrigerate.

title: minced barbecue
directions: Combine all ingredients in deep container.
Cover and cook on high about 20 minutes, then cook on low about three hours, or until thick.
Stir often.

title: machetti
directions: Simmer meat, onion and pepper.
Mix with soups and cooked noodles.
Place in 11 x 13-inch pan or glass casserole dish.
Top with grated cheese, Velveeta or Cheddar.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: raspberry vinegar
directions: Bring vinegar to a boil in non-aluminum saucepan.
Place raspberries in clean, hot 16 ounce jar.
Pour vinegar over berries in jar.
Cover and let stand several days at room temperature in cool, dark place.
If desired, strain into decorative jar and add additional fresh berries.

title: corn salad
directions: Mix all ingredients, adding Fritos last or when ready to serve.

title: vegetable beef soup
directions: Cook beef until tender, then add remaining ingredients, except for the macaroni.
Let simmer for about 1 hour.
Add macaroni and simmer for about 15 minutes or until tender.

title: quick apple betty
directions: Empty pie filling into greased baking dish.
Stir in brown sugar, lemon juice and a sprinkle of cinnamon.
Top with crumbled raisin bread, dot with margarine and sprinkle with sugar and cinnamon mixture.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes, until bubbly hot and slightly browned on top.

title: sugar coated peanuts
directions: Dissolve sugar in water in saucepan over high heat.
Add peanuts and continue cooking on high heat until peanuts are completely coated and no syrup remains, about 30 minutes.
Pour onto an ungreased cookie sheet.
Separate peanuts with a fork. Bake at 350° 15 to 20 minutes.
Stir at 5 minute intervals.

title: sleeping dinosaur sandwiches
directions: Cut toasted bread slices in half and place on a cookie sheet one inch apart.
Boil hot dogs until done, then place 3 or 4 round slices of hot dog on each piece of toast (if using pickle, place one slice on each piece of toast).
Lay 1/2 slice of cheese over each "dinosaur" to form a blanket, then broil for 1 to 3 minutes or until cheese melts.
Remove from oven and stick chow mein noodles under the cheese so that the ends hang out.
This it the dinosaur tail.
Allow to cool and they're ready to eat.

title: carol's crock-pot barbecue
directions: Cook trimmed roast in crock-pot overnight, then chip up the meat.
The next morning, add all other ingredients and let cook 2 hours.
Serve over cornbread or Fritos.
Super good.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour into the 2 uncooked pie shells. Bake at 325° for 35 to 60 minutes.

title: round-up bean casserole
directions: Put 1 teaspoon salt in bottom of a large skillet.
Heat, then add beef and stir until browned.
Add pepper and salt, then other ingredients.
Mix well, then put in a large casserole.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: white russian(non-alcoholic)
directions: Combine all ingredients in blender until frothy. Serves 2.

title: cabbage wedge meal in one
directions: Cut cabbage into 6 to 8 wedges and place in buttered casserole dish or skillet.
Arrange onion, ground beef and rice between wedges.
Combine tomatoes, water and seasonings.
Pour over contents in casserole.
Cover; bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours. Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Cook potatoes until tender.
Mash and measure 1 1/2 cups. Combine potatoes, sugar, cinnamon and salt.
Beat eggs slightly with fork. Stir eggs, milk and butter into potato mixture. Spoon into pastry shell.
Top with nuts. Sprinkle top with butter and sugar.
Bake at 400° until done, 45 to 50 minutes.

title: pineapple upside-down trifle
directions: Stir brown sugar into 3/4 cup pineapple juice until completely dissolved; set aside.
Pour milk into medium bowl.
Add pudding mix.
Beat with wire whisk 30 seconds.
Let stand 2 minutes or until thickened.
Gently stir in whipped topping until smooth. Arrange 1/2 of the cake cubes in 3-quart serving bowl.
Drizzle 1/2 of the juice mixture over cake.
Layer 1/2 of the pineapple chunks, pecans and chopped cherries over cake, then add pudding mix. Repeat layers, ending with pudding mix.
Refrigerate 1 hour. Garnish with pineapple slices and cherries.

title: apple dumplings
directions: Peel and slice apples.
Place in a 9 x 13-inch dish; sprinkle 1/2 cup brown sugar, cinnamon and nutmeg over apples.
Mix second 1/2 cup brown sugar, nuts and cake mix; sprinkle on top of apples. Cut up 1 stick margarine on top of mixture.
Bake for 1 hour or longer at 325°.

title: zucchini, peppers and tomatoes
directions: Wash, trim and slice the zucchini.
Salt and let drain; pat dry.
Heat the butter and oil and saute the onions until wilted. Add the zucchini and peppers and cook 2 to 3 minutes.
Stir in the Parmesan cheese if you like.
Serve either hot or cold.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: scrumptious caramel squares
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Melt caramels and milk in microwave oven for 2 1/2 to 3 minutes on High, stirring often, until melted and smooth.

title: hamburger meat and potato casserole
directions: Brown meat in skillet and pour into 9 x 13-inch baking pan. Slice potatoes and put on top of meat.
Slice onion over potatoes. Salt and pepper to taste.
Mix soup and water.
Pour over onion. Cover and bake at 350° for 1 hour or until done.

title: smoked beef spread
directions: Chop 2 packages of beef and the onion.
Mix all together; roll in the third package of beef last.
Makes 3 balls.
Serve with crackers of your choice.

title: easy coconut cake
directions: Bake cake as directed on box for 2 layers.
After cooled, split each layer to make a total of 4 layers.
Mix sugar, sour cream and frozen coconut.
Reserve about 1 cup of this mixture. Spread remaining mixture between each of the now 4 layers of cake. Combine reserved cup of mixture with whipped topping.
Spread over top and sides of cake.
Cake is supposed to stay in the refrigerator for 3 days before serving, if you can wait that long. Keep refrigerated.

title: corn fritters
directions: Mix flour, salt, sugar and baking powder.
Mix milk and egg; beat well.
Add to flour mixture, stirring only until moistened. Stir in corn.

title: treasure bran muffins
directions: Combine cereal and milk; let stand 2 minutes.
Add oil and egg; mix well.
Add combined dry ingredients, mixing just until moistened.
Fold in raisins.
Spoon into greased and floured medium-size muffin pan, filling each 2/3 full.
Combine softened cream cheese, sugar and egg, mixing well until blended.
Drop rounded tablespoonfuls cream cheese mixture onto batter.
Bake at 375° for 25 minutes.

title: microwave caramel corn
directions: Put in microwave for 2 minutes on High, stir; put in 2 more minutes.
Add baking soda and vanilla; stir until foamy.
Pour over popped corn in a brown paper grocery bag.
Fold top of sack a couple of times, shake.

title: italian beef(good for a crowd, keeps good in crock-pot)
directions: Use a 9 x 13-inch baking pan covered with foil or a crock-pot. Sprinkle both sides of meat with spices and salt and pepper. Place onion slices and pepperoni on top.

title: vegetable salad
directions: Prepare and combine vegetables in a large bowl.
Combine spices and liquids in a pan, bring to a boil.
Let liquid mixture cool, then pour over vegetables.
Marinate for a couple of hours or overnight before serving.

title: cheese ball
directions: Have all ingredients at room temperature and mix well.
Form into two balls or logs and roll in chopped nuts.
Chill until firm.
Wrap in plastic wrap and keep refrigerated until served.

title: death by chocolate
directions: Bake brownies according to directions, adding chopped pecans, if desired.
Bake in 9 x 12-inch pan.
When done, punch holes with fork and pour coffee mixture over the brownies.
Mix chocolate mousse according to directions on box and set aside.

(You can make your own mousse by preparing 2 boxes of instant chocolate pudding according to directions and adding 2 cups of Cool Whip to it.) Crush candy bars and set aside (freezing makes the candy easier to break).
In a large trifle bowl, layer crumbled brownies, mousse, candy and Cool Whip in that order.
Repeat layers three times. Serves 15 to 20 people.

title: jumjills
directions: Mix together to form soft dough.
Roll into 1-inch balls. chill.
This is our children' favorite dessert.

title: cream sauce
directions: Melt butter, stir in flour and seasonings; slowly stir in cream.
Bring to boiling point; boil 2 minutes.
Add paprika.
(A quarter teaspoon dry mustard may be blended with flour for a slightly different taste.)

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Put crust in bottom and up sides. Fill. Lay top crust over. Crimp edges.
Pierce top. Bake at 425° for 35 minutes.

title: orange jello salad
directions: Mix dry jello in cottage cheese with mixer add cool whip fold in fruit. Chill.

title: fresh strawberry pie
directions: In a medium saucepan, combine sugar and cornstarch.
Add the water and lemon juice.
Over high heat, bring to a boil.
Reduce heat.
Cook and stir until slightly thickened and clear (4 to 5 minutes).
Add gelatin.
Stir until dissolved.
Cool to room temperature.
Stir in strawberries; turn into prepared pastry shell.
Chill 4 to 6 hours or until set.
Refrigerate leftovers.

title: blueberry pie
directions: Put layer of bananas in bottom of pie shell.
Mix Dream Whip according to directions.
Add softened cream cheese and sugar. Mix thoroughly.
Spoon into shells and put filling on top. Refrigerate.

title: kahlua trifle
directions: Bake cake according to directions.
Prepare pudding according to directions.
Crumble half of the cake in a large bowl.
Pour half the Kahlua over it.
Place half the pudding on top.
Place half the topping on the pudding.
Repeat.
Top with walnuts.

title: monkey bread
directions: Grease Bundt pan well. Place butterscotch pudding in bottom of pan. Layer the rolls on top. Melt and mix butter, brown sugar and cinnamon. Pour over rolls. Let set in oven overnight. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: party mints
directions: Mix sugar, peppermint, margarine and milk in bowl until well blended (may use a mixer).
Add coloring and mix until it forms a ball.
Knead on foil until mixture is very smooth.

title: zucchini cakes
directions: Mix all ingredients and brown like pancakes in a skillet.
Lay on a cookie sheet and bake at 350° for 15 to 20 more minutes.

title: cajun red beans
directions: Pick over beans and wash well.
Soak overnight.
Boil beans, onion, ham and garlic on high in a heavy pot.
Check often so not to scorch.
When beans are tender, add sliced sausage.
Cook for 30 minutes.
Add water, if necessary.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Serve over steamed rice.

title: chicken basket bake
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Lightly grease a 10-inch pie plate. Sprinkle chicken, mushrooms, onions, salt and cheese in pie plate. Beat remaining ingredients until smooth.
Pour into pie plate over first ingredients.
Bake for 30 to 35 minutes or until golden brown and knife inserted halfway between center and edge comes out clean. Let stand five minutes before cutting.
Can substitute 2 cups fully cooked turkey or smoked ham for chicken.

title: my special fudge
directions: Mix graham cracker crumbs and powdered sugar together.
Then add butter and peanut butter, mix well.
Then press into baking dish and cut.

title: tang salad
directions: Drain pineapple, reserving juice.
Drain remaining fruits. Combine reserved pineapple juice, pudding mix and powdered Tang. Stir well.
Combine fruits and dressing; toss gently.
Chill. Yield:
4 servings.

title: strawberry whip(diabetic recipe)
directions: Wash and hull strawberries.
Into an electric blender, pour hot water, dry gelatin and 1 cup of the strawberries.
Cover; blend 30 seconds.
Add crushed ice; blend 20 seconds longer.
Add remaining strawberries.
Blend about 3 seconds.
Pour into chilled serving bowl.
Chil 1 hour or until partially set.
Spoon into serving dishes and garnish with mint, if desired.

title: vermicelli salad
directions: Cook vermicelli according to package; drain.
Rinse in cold water; drain again.
In large bowl, combine green pepper, celery, green onions, pimientos, black olives, peas and cheese.
Mix well. Add drained vermicelli and combine.
In small bowl, combine lime juice, salad oil and mayonnaise.
Add to vegetable-vermicelli mixture. May be served right away or covered and chilled before serving.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: apricot glaze for ham
directions: Mix together in small bowl.
Spread over ham during the last 20 minutes of baking.

title: chicken broccoli divan
directions: In an 11 x 7-inch baking dish arrange broccoli and chicken.
In small bowl combine soup, milk and 1/2 cheese.
Pour over chicken. In cup combine remaining cheese, bread crumbs and butter; sprinkle over top.
Bake at 450° for 70 minutes or microwave on High for 6 minutes.

title: oven roasted potatoes
directions: Bake in preheated oven at 400° until brown and tender.
Stir as needed.

title: fruit salad
directions: Mix and sit in refrigerator for 8 hours.

title: fruit nut cookies
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Mix all dry ingredients. Divide in 4 parts and shape in long rolls on lightly floured Saran Wrap.
Put on cookie sheet in refrigerator or freezer overnight.
Add fruit after you mix dry ingredients.
Slice thin and bake at 350° for 12 minutes. Dough is very stiff.

title: fiesta beef kabobs
directions: In saucepan, combine first 8 ingredients and 1/2 cup water; bring to boiling.
Reduce heat and simmer 20 minutes.
Cool.
Add meat; toss and coat.
Refrigerate overnight.
Drain meat, reserving marinade.
Use tenderizer on meat according to directions.
Thread meat and peppers alternately on skewers. Broil over coals 20 to 25 minutes, turning once and brushing with marinade.
Heat remaining marinade to pass.
Serves 4.

title: sirloin tips and mushrooms
directions: In a wide skillet, brown meat in 2 tablespoons of butter and the oil.
Add garlic.
Remove meat to a covered casserole.
Add remaining butter to skillet.
Saute mushrooms; add to meat.
Cover and bake slowly at 275° for 1 hour, until meat is tender.
Add broth, wine and soy sauce to pan in which meat was browned.
Boil, stirring up the brownings, until reduced to a glaze.
Blend mustard, cornstarch and cream.
Add to pan.
Boil until thick. Pour off juices from meat into the saucepan.
Boil, whisking until smooth and thick.
Blend with meat.
Sprinkle with parsley.

title: taco casserole
directions: Brown hamburger meat and onion together in skillet.
Mix soup and chilies together.
Add a dash of the next 5 ingredients to soup mixture:
chili powder, Tabasco sauce, garlic flakes, cumin and Worcestershire sauce.
Add meat mixture to soup.
Layer in oblong pan as follows:
meat, tacos and cheese. Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.
Serves several.

title: baked pineapple
directions: Dissolve cornstarch in water.
Mix everything in a small casserole dish with butter.
Sprinkle with cinnamon.
Cover and bake at 350° for 1/2 hour.
Uncover and bake another 1/2 hour, stirring occasionally.

title: ten minute german sweet chocolate cream pie
directions: Heat chocolate and 2 tablespoons of milk in saucepan over low heat, stirring until chocolate is melted.
Beat sugar into cream cheese; add remaining milk and chocolate mixture and beat until smooth.
Fold in whipped topping, blending until smooth.
Spoon into crust.
Freeze until firm, about 4 hours.
Garnish with chocolate curls if desired.
Store any leftover pies in the freezer.

title: savory baked chicken
directions: *If unavailable, use soy sauce.

title: marinated black-eyed pea salad
directions: Drain black-eyed peas and rinse with cold water and drain well.
Add celery and onion.
Combine oil, vinegar, mayonnaise, salt and cayenne.
Mix well.
Pour over peas.
Stir gently.
Allow to chill before serving.
Makes 4 servings.

title: chicken pie
directions: Bring chicken, chicken soup and broth to a boil.
Pour in a 12 x 9 x 2 inch sheet pan.
Mix flour, baking powder, black pepper, milk and margarine; pour over chicken in pan.
Bake at 425° for 30 minutes or till brown.

title: excellent oatmeal chocolate chip cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375.
Combine flour, baking soda and salt in small bowl.
Beat butter, granulated sugar and vanilla in large mixer bowl.
Add eggs one at a time beating well after each addition.
Gradually beat in flour mixture.
Stir in oats.
Stir in morsels and nuts.
Drop by rounded tablespoon onto ungreased cookie sheets.
bake 9 to 11 minutes or until golden brown.
Let stand for 2 minutes.
Remove to wire racks to cool completely.

title: cheese sauce
directions: Heat margarine over low heat until melted. Blend in flour, mustard and salt. Cook over low heat until mixture is smooth and bubbly, stirring constantly. Remove from heat and stir in milk. Heat to boiling, stirring constantly, for 1 minute. Stir in cheese. Cook and stir over low heat until cheese is melted.

title: chicken and broccoli quiche
directions: Put cooked chicken, broccoli, cheese, onion and celery into pie crust.
Combine eggs,
half and half, salt, sugar and cayenne.
Pour into pie pan.
Bake 15 minutes at 450°.
Reduce oven to 300° and bake 30 minutes or until knife inserted in center comes out clean.

title: hash brown potato casserole
directions: Mix ingredients well.
Put in casserole and top with crushed potato chips or corn flakes.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: sugared peanuts or pecans
directions: Put nuts, sugar and water in saucepan on medium heat and bring to a boil.
Let boil until water boils out.
Spread on cookie sheet and bake 1 hour at 250°.

title: oven stew
directions: Make hamburger into walnut-size meat balls; put in bottom of roaster.
Top with potatoes, large onion, carrots and tomato soup. Pour undrained peas over all.
Add bay leaves.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Bake at 300° for 2 1/2 to 3 hours.

title: apple cobbler
directions: Line 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan with pastry, letting pastry cover sides also.
Peel and slice apples.
Cover pastry with 1 cup sugar.
Place apples over the sugar.
Cover with 1 cup sugar and sprinkle cinnamon over it.
Sprinkle with brandy extract and butter flavoring.
Dot with butter.
Cover with top pastry, cutting slits in top.
Brush with cream and sprinkle sugar over top.
Cook in 350° oven for about 45 minutes.

title: cowboy cookies
directions: Sift first 4 ingredients; add remaining ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: chicken divan
directions: Grease a 13 x 9-inch baking dish with butter, margarine or cooking spray.
Simmer chicken until tender.
Let cool.
Remove all meat and cut up.
Thaw frozen vegetables or run under hot water.
Put broccoli on bottom of buttered dish and add chicken.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Fry bacon and crumble.
Cut up broccoli into small pieces.
Mix with bacon, seeds, cheese and chopped red onion.
Mix mayonnaise, vinegar and sugar.
Pour over salad and mix; chill and serve. Enjoy!!

title: pumpkin nut loaf
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Spray 9 x 5-inch loaf pan with Baker's Joy baking spray.
In medium bowl, combine flour, baking soda, baking powder, salt, cinnamon and nutmeg.
Set aside.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Mix all ingredients, except cheese and potato chips.
Spoon into ungreased baking dish.
Sprinkle with cheese and chips. Bake, uncovered, at 450° for 10 to 15 minutes, or until bubbly.

title: key lime pie
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Pour into the graham cracker crust and freeze.

title: chilled cucumber salad
directions: Using a glass-like container, mix salt and water and pour over cucumbers and onions.
Let sit for 2 hours.
Drain but don't rinse.
Mix sugar and cider vinegar; pour over cucumbers and onions.
Mix and marinate until well chilled.
May also be frozen.

title: popcorn balls
directions: Boil sugar, syrup, water, butter and salt until it spins a thread.
Add vanilla.
Pour over popcorn.
Butter hands so popcorn will not stick to them.
Shape into balls.

title: creamy potatoes au gratin
directions: Preheat oven to 375°. Coat 1 1/2-quart baking dish with cooking spray. Arrange 1/3 of potatoes over the bottom of the dish, overlapping slightly. Top with 1/3 cup Mozzarella and 2 tablespoons Parmesan cheese. Repeat layering twice with more potatoes, remaining Mozzarella and the Parmesan. Top with remaining potatoes. Pour broth and dressing over all. Sprinkle with remaining Parmesan. Bake at 375° until top is golden and potatoes are tender, approximately 1 hour.

title: holiday appetizer pie
directions: Let cream cheese soften.
Beat with 2 tablespoons of milk. Add green pepper, onions and dried beef.
Stir in sour cream; top with nuts.
Put in shallow pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes, until bubbly.
Serve with chips or crackers.

title: old fashioned raisin pie
directions: Put orange juice and water in a saucepan and bring to a boil. Remove from heat and stir in raisins.
Let stand 2 hours.
Add sugar, flour, lemon juice and salt to raisin mixture.
Cook over low heat, stirring frequently, for 10 minutes or until thickened. Heat oven to 425°.
Roll out half of the dough and line 9-inch pie pan.
Pour raisin mixture.
Roll out remaining dough and a lattice top.
Crimp together top and bottom dough.
Bake for 10 minutes. Lower temperature to 350°.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes or until top is browned.

title: german potato salad
directions: Mix potatoes, celery, onions and eggs. Cut bacon in small pieces and fry until done (little crispy). Do not drain fat.

title: spaghetti sauce
directions: Brown onions in hot oil; add meat and seasoning.
Brown lightly.
Cover; simmer 10 minutes.
Add soups; cover and simmer 45 minutes.
Serves 10.

title: velvet fudge cake
directions: Use tube pan; heavily butter bottom and sides.
Put in 1/2 of nuts and spread.
Measure all other ingredients together in mixing bowl for 4 minutes, except for chocolate chips.
By hand, put in remainder of nuts and chips.
Pour in pan; put in 350° preheated oven for 70 minutes.
Cool and turn out.

title: baked custard
directions: Mix Eagle Brand milk and hot water.
Pour gradually over eggs, stirring constantly.
Add salt and vanilla.
Pour into baking dish or custard cups which have been greased with oil.
Sprinkle with nutmeg.
Place in pan filled with hot water to a depth of 1 inch. Bake in slow oven at 325° about 1 hour or until custard is set (a knife blade inserted will come out clean when custard is done.)

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Mix shortening, butter, peanut butter, sugars and egg together. Blend in flour.
Mix well.
Cover and chill thoroughly.

title: crab stuffed mushrooms
directions: Remove stems from mushrooms.
Brush mushroom caps with oil and place in buttered baking dish.

title: frosted molasses creams
directions: Cut 3 apples into small pieces.
Add 1 c. sugar to them and 1/2 c. nuts.
Beat 2 eggs add 1 c. flour, 1 tsp soda, 1/2 tsp cinnamon, 1/2 tsp salt and 1 tsp vanilla.
Melt 3 Tbsp butter and add mixture.
Spread into pan and bake for 25 minutes in 350° oven.

title: sour cream cookies
directions: Mix shortening, sugar and eggs.
Stir in sour cream and vanilla.
Stir in flour, soda, baking powder and salt.
Chill at least 1 hour.
Bake at 400° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: tuna quiche
directions: Combine and mix well the first 4 ingredients.
Stir in tuna, cheese and onions.
Pour into an unbaked pie shell and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: seafood linguine alfredo
directions: Cook linguine to desired doneness as directed on package. Drain; rinse with hot water.
Put shrimp in a pot and cook excess water off shrimp.
Put to the side.
In a Dutch oven, melt margarine.
Put crabmeat and shrimp in with melted butter.
Warm in butter for about 2 minutes.
Stir in whipping cream and pepper. Cook over low-medium heat for about 5 minutes or until mixture thickens slightly, stirring frequently.
Stir in Parmesan cheese and cook over low heat just until cheese is melted, stirring constantly.
Immediately stir in linguine; toss to coat with sauce.
If sauce begins to separate, stir in a little more cream and cook over low heat until smooth.

title: whoopie pies
directions: Sift together all dry ingredients.
Add shortening, egg yolks, melted chocolate, vanilla and milk.
Mix well and bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: 5 cup fruit salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together and refrigerate.

title: go for "2" chili
directions: Brown ground beef, onion and green pepper, adding black, red and crushed pepper.
(Drain fat when done.)
Combine remaining ingredients.
Simmer about 20 minutes.
Add meat to mixture.
Let cook another 30 minutes or so.
Serve with oyster crackers, cheese or a dash of sour cream.
Enjoy!!!

title: peanut butter balls
directions: Blend margarine, sugar and peanut butter by hand.
Shape into 1/2-inch balls.
Refrigerate overnight.
Melt chocolate and wax together over hot (not boiling) water.
Let cool slightly.
Use a slotted spoon to dip candies into chocolate mix.
Push off spoon with a cheese spreader onto wax paper to dry.
Makes about 250 pieces.

title: root beer float cake
directions: In mixing bowl, combine dry cake mix, 1 1/4 cups root beer, oil and eggs. Beat on low speed for 2 minutes or stir by hand for 3 minutes. Pour into a greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch cake pan. Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes or until a toothpick inserted into center comes out clean.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Mix broccoli, onions, raisins and bacon together gently.
Blend mayonnaise, sugar and vinegar thoroughly.
Fold dressing into vegetables mixture and refrigerate 1 to 2 hours before serving.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Mix all together and pour in pie crust and bake at 325° until done.

title: toasted coconut pecan pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Thoroughly combine eggs, sugar, butter, lemon juice and vanilla.
Stir in coconut and nuts.
Pour into pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes or until filling is set.
Cool.
Garnish with sweetened whipped cream and pecan halves if desired.

title: crunchy cookies
directions: Cream first 5 ingredients.
Combine the salt, flour and soda and add to the creamed mixture.
Add remaining ingredients.
Use an ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 12 minutes.

title: divinity
directions: Boil the sugar, Karo and water until it reaches soft ball stage.
Add marshmallow cream and nuts.
Beat until it will mound up.
Drop by spoonfuls onto waxed paper.

title: indian fry bread
directions: Divide into little balls.
Let rest 10 minutes.
Make hole in middle and fry in 1/2 inch hot oil.

title: hamburger corn pone pie
directions: Cook meat and onion and drain.
Add seasonings, tomatoes and water.
Cover and simmer for 20 minutes.
Add kidney beans.
Pour into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: savory spinach souffle
directions: Grease 1 1/2-quart souffle dish or casserole; coat with 2 tablespoons cheese.
In saucepan, saute onion in margarine. Blend in flour.
Add milk, salt, pepper and nutmeg.
Cook, stirring constantly until thickened.
Stir in remaining cheese. Add egg yolks, one at a time, beating after each addition.
Blend in spinach.
Cool.
Beat egg whites until stiff but not dry.
Fold into spinach mixture.
Pour into prepared dish.
Bake in 375° oven 35 minutes.
Serve immediately.

title: buttermilk pie
directions: Mix ingredients well.
Pour into a 9-inch pie shell and bake at 350° for 1 hour or until firm.

title: pinehurst muffins(from plaza club)
directions: Sift together flour, cinnamon, salt, sugar and baking soda. Mix well eggs, vanilla and oil.
Add raisins, pecans, carrots, coconut and shredded apple to egg mixture.
Add dry ingredients, a little at a time.
Place in greased muffin tins/paper cups. Bake at 350° for 5 to 10 minutes, or until an inserted toothpick comes out clean.
Yields approximately 18 muffins.

title: sugar-free apple pie
directions: Line pie plate with one uncooked pie crust.
Set aside.
Mix apples, apple juice concentrate, cornstarch and spices.
Stir until apples are well coated.
Add lemon juice.

title: old-fashioned chocolate pudding
directions: Beat egg yolks; add milk.
Sift dry ingredients together and place in double boiler.
Stir in 1/3 cup milk and egg yolks.
Mix and stir; add remaining milk.
Cook until thick, then add butter and vanilla.
This can also be used for a pie.
I use miniature marshmallows for my topping.

title: vegetable rice casserole
directions: Place oil in large skillet; add green pepper, 1/2 cup chopped onion, cauliflower, broccoli and garlic.
Cook on high for 5 minutes.
Stir in thyme.
Remove from heat.
Dissolve bouillon granules in water in 2-quart casserole dish.
Stir in rice, 1/2 cup chopped onion and soy sauce.
Cover and bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Remove casserole from oven and stir in vegetable mixture..
Cover, bake an additional 10 to 15 minutes or until all liquid is absorbed.

title: crab-stuffed chicken breasts
directions: Pound chicken to flatten.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper. Cook onion and celery in margarine until tender.
Remove from heat.
Add wine, crab and stuffing.
Toss.
Divide mixture among breasts.
Roll up and secure.

title: poppy seed chicken
directions: Place chicken in bottom of casserole dish.
Mix soup and sour cream together and spread over chicken.
Melt butter and add Ritz crackers.
Mix well and spread over top.
Top with poppy seed. Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: ziti bake
directions: Cook
pound of ziti.
Drain.
While ziti is cooking, brown hamburg with chopped medium onion.
Remove from heat and add
the Ricotta
cheese,
the slightly beaten egg and grated cheese.
Add all to cooked ziti and mix.
Add spaghetti sauce and
mix.
Place in
x
9-inch
casserole.
Sprinkle with grated
Mozzarella. Bake in 375° oven for 20 to 25 minutes or slightly
brown
oven,
if in glass pan.
Heat extra sauce to serve with it.

title: hot corned beef sandwiches
directions: Mix all ingredients together and put on hamburger buns.
Wrap each sandwich in foil and put in oven for 15 to 20 minutes at 375°.
Makes 12 sandwiches and you can double the recipe.
(Use cookie sheet.)

title: banana split cake
directions: In a 9 x 13-inch baking pan, melt margarine. Stir in crumbs. Pat mixture firmly into pan.
Prepare pudding according to package directions. Spread over crumb mixture.
Layer bananas, strawberries and pineapple. Spread whipped topping over pineapple. Refrigerate overnight.
Garnish with strawberries, if desired. Serves 12 to 15.

title: tea punch
directions: Use 6 tea bags to brew 2 quarts tea.
Add frozen juice and 2 cans of water.

title: pumpkin-raisin-rum pie
directions: Combine raisins, rum and water in a small bowl; let stand 20 minutes.
Combine brown sugar, flour, salt and spices in large bowl, stirring well.
Add raisin mixture, pumpkin, eggs and milk; stirring well.
Pour filling into pastry shell.
Bake at 450° for 20 minutes, reduce heat to 350° and bake additional 30 minutes or until set.
Cool.
Serve with whipped cream topping.

title: buckeyes
directions: In a large bowl mix butter, peanut butter, sugar and Rice Krispies. Keep mixing until it sticks together well enough that you can make balls about the size of English walnuts and they are smooth and don't crumble.
Otherwise, work the mixture more.
When balls are made, set aside.

title: coconut pie
directions: Beat eggs, add sugar, flour and salt.
Next, add milk, then coconut and other flavorings.
Pour mixture in an unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 375° for approximately 20 minutes, until when pie is slightly shaken the pie filling is firm.

title: apple-snickers salad
directions: Peel, slice and cut apples into bite-size pieces.
Cut candy bars into small pieces.
Blend in Cool Whip and stir apples and candy bars until coated.
Serve immediately.

title: hamburger stroganoff
directions: In large skillet, cook and stir meat and onion in butter until meat is brown and onion is tender.
Stir in flour, salt, garlic, pepper and mushrooms.
Cook 5 minutes, stirring constantly. Reduce heat.
Simmer uncovered for 10 minutes.
Stir in sour cream.
Heat through.
Serve over noodles.

title: banana split cake
directions: Pat crumbs and 1/2 cup margarine in pan.
Mix 1/2 cup margarine, sugar and eggs; beat in mixer no less than 15 minutes. Pour over crumbs.
Place sliced bananas on top, pour can of crushed pineapple (drained) over bananas.
Cover with Cool Whip.
Decorate top with 1 cup chopped nuts and cherries.
Chill several hours before serving.
Can be made the day before serving.
Serves 15. Use a 13 x 9 x 2 1/2-inch pan.

title: heath bar cake
directions: Bake according to package directions in a 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: watergate cake
directions: Combine first six ingredients.
Beat 4 minutes at medium speed of electric mixer.
Pour batter into a greased and floured 10-inch tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.
Turn out on wire rack to cool.
Frost with Pistachio Frosting and garnish with pecans.

title: bean casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish. In a large bowl, combine all ingredients.
Pour into casserole; bake 1 hour or place in crock-pot for 3 hours on medium-high.

title: cherry cheese cake
directions: Cream together cream cheese, sugar and vanilla.
Add sugar and sour cream.
Put in pie shell.
Top with cherry filling.
Chill and serve.

title: lemon pie
directions: In a medium bowl, combine milk and juice.
Let stand a few minutes; stir in Cool Whip.
Spoon in pie crust and chill until firm.

title: dutch apple coffee cake
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients (flour, brown sugar, white sugar, cinnamon, salt and margarine) until crumb consistency.
Reserve 1 1/2 cups of crumbs.
To the remainder, add egg, buttermilk and soda.
Spread in a greased pan.
Slice 2 to 3 apples on the top and spread with crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: strawberry divinity
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients in a heavy 3-quart saucepan; cook over low heat, stirring gently, until sugar dissolves.
Cover and cook over medium heat 2 to 3 minutes to wash down sugar crystals from sides of pan.
Uncover and cook over medium heat, without stirring, to hard ball stage (258°).
Remove from heat.
With an electric mixer, beat egg whites in a large bowl at high speed until stiff peaks form.
Pour hot syrup mixture in a thin stream over egg whites while beating constantly at high speed until mixture holds its shape (3 to 4 minutes).
Quickly stir in pecans and drop mixture by rounded teaspoonfuls onto wax paper.
Let cool.
Yield:
4 1/2 dozen.

title: best raisin bran muffins
directions: Blend flour, sugar, baking soda and salt in a large mixing bowl.
Stir in cereal.
Add buttermilk, oil, eggs and nuts. Blend until dry ingredients are moistened.
Do not stir batter again.
Mixture may be stored, covered, in a non-metal bowl for up to 6 weeks.
As needed, fill lightly greased muffin pans 2/3 full. Bake at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes.
If desired, lightly brush melted butter over batter and sprinkle with cinnamon before baking.
Best if sets overnight before baking.

title: spaghetti casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 375 degrees.
Spray 2-quart casserole dish with vegetable spray.

title: grandma millard's rice pudding
directions: Add all ingredients and stir.
Do not cover.
Bake at 425°. Do not overcook.
Stir while baking.
Remove from oven when rice begins to soften.

title: cherry cream cheese spread
directions: Mix ingredients, adding 1 or 2 tablespoons of maraschino cherry juice until spreadable. Serve with Town House or Ritz crackers. Refrigerate leftovers.

title: potato n' cheese casserole
directions: Alternate layers of half of potatoes, cheese and mushroom soup in greased casserole.
Repeat.
Sprinkle with onion, salt and pepper.
Dot with margarine.
Pour milk over all.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.
Yield: 8 servings.

title: tartar sauce
directions: Mix all ingredients together in a bowl.
Serve with fried seafood or salad.
Makes 1 1/2 quarts.

title: easy chicken pie
directions: Place cooked chicken, cut into pieces, in a shallow casserole dish.
Add chicken soup and broth.
In a separate bowl, mix flour, milk and margarine.
Pour evenly over chicken and bake at 375° for 1 hour.
Also may add mixed vegetables.

title: five bean-bacon bake
directions: Fry bacon until done, not crisp; drain and set aside.
Reserve 2 tablespoons bacon drippings in skillet.
Reduce heat; add onions, brown sugar, vinegar and garlic powder to skillet.
Stir well.
Cover; cook for 2 minutes, or until onions are slightly soft.

title: venison swiss steak
directions: Rub the steaks with a mixture of flour, garlic powder, paprika and black pepper.
Brown the meat in a large skillet along with the chopped onion.
Add the mushroom soup and a can of water. Stir and bring to a boil.
Cover and simmer for 1 hour or until tender.
Remove the meat and add mushrooms to the liquid in the skillet.
Simmer until tender and add the sour cream.

title: cranberry relish mold
directions: Drain pineapple; reserve syrup.
Add water to make 1/2 cup. Dissolve Jell-O and sugar in 1 cup hot water.
Add syrup and lemon juice.
Chill until partially set.
Add fruits and nuts.
Chill until set.

title: tested recipe for preserving children(any amount)
directions: Into the field pour children and dogs, allowing to mix well. Pour brook over pebbles until slightly frothy.
When children are nicely brown, cool in a warm tub.
When dry, serve with milk, fresh baked bread and jelly.

title: tuna spaghetti
directions: In saucepan cook garlic in margarine until golden brown.
Stir in half and half, basil and oregano.
Heat to boiling.
Stir in tuna, olives and cheese.
Boil and stir 1 minute.
Pour over hot spaghetti.
Sprinkle with parsley and serve.
Makes 4 servings.

title: forgotten beef roast
directions: Put meat in 13 x 9-inch pan.
Add cream of mushroom soup; put on top of meat.
Add dry onion soup.
Put in 1/2 cup water.
Wrap foil over pan tightly.
Bake at 325° for 3 hours.

title: cheese cake
directions: Mix in blender cream cheese and milk.
Pour on cracker crust. Top with cherry pie filling.
Double recipe to use all of can.

title: herb bread
directions: Combine all but first two ingredients into paste.

title: holy smoke
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients.
Spread in bottom of 9 x 12-inch baking dish.
Bake at 300° for 25 minutes.
Cool.

title: tangy salad dressing
directions: Put all ingredients in a blender and blend for at least 1 minute.
Lasts a few weeks if kept in refrigerator.
Recipe can be doubled.

title: fillet of sole with crabmeat stuffing
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Butter a baking dish large enough to hold the fillets in 1 layer.
Mix the bread crumbs, crabmeat and sherry together in a bowl.
Then add the lemon juice.
(The mixture should be moist, but not wet.)
Place one-fourth of the stuffing on each fillet and roll the fillets up around the stuffing, keeping it tucked inside.
Secure with a toothpick. Place the rolls in the prepared baking dish, seam side down. Sprinkle them lightly with paprika and dot each with 1 tablespoon butter.
Bake for 10 minutes at 350° or until fish flakes when gently prodded with a fork.
Serve immediately.
Serves 4.

title: apple fritters
directions: Mix flour and baking powder.
Beat egg yolks with the sugar and salt.
Heat the milk (do not boil).
Add the milk slowly to the egg yolk mixture, then add flour and egg whites; stir all together and put in slices of apples.
Drop batter and apples by spoonful into hot lard and fry to a light brown.
Serve with maple syrup.

title: ham and wild rice casserole
directions: Cook rice according to directions.
Set aside.
Saute onions and mushrooms in oleo.
Layer in greased baking dish in this order: rice, sauteed ingredients, ham and cheese.
Pour canned milk over it and bake at 350° until bubbly (at least 30 minutes).

title: beef stew
directions: Drain all vegetables except tomatoes.
Combine all ingredients in a large casserole.
Cover and bake at 250° for 6 to 7 hours. Makes 8 to 10 servings.
Make sure that the tapioca, sugar and bread crumbs are on top of the meat so that the liquids will soften them.
I stir it all up and cut up the tomatoes a little as I'm stirring.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Mix together all ingredients.
Place in 2 quart casserole dish.
Bake uncovered at 350 degrees for approximately 20 minutes.

title: quiche
directions: Mix together the eggs, mayonnaise, flour and milk. Cut the Swiss cheese into small cubes and dice the onion.
If using bacon, cook first and then break into small pieces.
Add the cheese, onions and other ingredients to first mixture and pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake in 350° oven for 40 to 50 minutes.

title: egg, milk, butterless cake
directions: Boil all ingredients on stove for 3 minutes, then cool.
When cool, put in 1 scant teaspoon of baking soda and 2 teaspoons of vinegar.
When mixed, add to cooled ingredients.
Mix flour and other dry ingredients in with other ingredients and pour into small, scalloped tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes or until toothpick comes out clean.
Top with powdered sugar sifted over top and top with candied fruit, cherries or ?

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Boil chicken;
put
a
little salt and pepper in water. When done, set aside.
Cook noodles in the same chicken broth; drain. Do not rinse off noodles.
Pick chicken off bone.
Put soups, stewed
tomatoes,
Ro-Tel
and cheese together.
Saute onions, green
onion and celery until tender.
Put vegetables together in sauce.
Put chicken and noodles in sauce.
