Cook 10 minutes in oven or cook on top of stove.

title: frosted pecans
directions: Beat egg white and water until frothy.
Add sugar, cinnamon and salt.
Pour over pecans and stir until well coated.
Place on a buttered cookie sheet.
Bake at 225° for 1 hour.

title: broccoli dip
directions: Saute onion and celery; add drained mushrooms.
Cook the broccoli and drain.
Add grated lemon peel to broccoli.
Mix garlic cheese and mushroom soup; mix this with the broccoli, onion and mushrooms.
You may add 1 teaspoon of Worcestershire sauce or a few drops of Tabasco and almonds or water chestnuts.
Serve warm with Fritos, crackers or Melba toast.

title: sausage brunch
directions: Brown sausage and drain.
Beat eggs and add remaining ingredients.
Mix.
Stir in cheese and sausage.
Put in 9 x 13-inch glass baking dish.
Cover with Saran Wrap and refrigerate overnight or 8 hours.
Remove 1/2 hour before baking.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: brunswick stew
directions: Prepare and cook chicken in crock-pot all night.
The next morning bone and cut up chicken.
Mix all ingredients and cook on low in crock-pot all day or until thick.

title: zesty vegetables
directions: Place carrots in a wok and stir-fry 5 minutes in 1 tablespoon margarine.
Drain.
Place carrots and remaining vegetables in a plastic sealable bag.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: In a large frypan, melt oleo with onion and broccoli. Cook until tender.
Add cooked rice, soup and Cheez Whiz. Stir together.
Put in oblong casserole and top with French fried onion rings.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes until golden brown.

title: marinated pork roast
directions: Combine sauce ingredients.
Place roast in clear plastic bag in deep bowl.
Pour marinade in bag and close.
Marinate 2 to 3 hours at room temperature or overnight in the refrigerator. Occasionally turn bag so marinade completely covers meat.
Remove meat from bag; place on a rack in shallow roasting pan.
Roast, uncovered, at 325° for 35 minutes per pound, or until meat thermometer registers 170°.
Baste with marinade during baking.

title: green rice
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Chop green onions.
Saute green onions, frozen broccoli and butter.
Meantime, boil water and add rice; cook 15 minutes or until tender.
Warm soup and Velveeta until cheese is melted.
In large baking dish, combine all ingredients, mix well.
Bake uncovered for 30 to 45 minutes or until cheese on top is light golden brown.

title: oatmeal chocolate chip cookies
directions: Cream together shortening, white sugar, brown sugar, vanilla and eggs.
Add in flour, soda and cinnamon.
Fold in oatmeal and chocolate chips.
Bake at 350° approximately 12 minutes, maybe less.

title: mom's party chicken
directions: Place chicken in ovenproof baking dish.
Top each breast with slice of cheese.
Add mushrooms.
Mix wine with soup and stuffing seasoning.
Crumble stuffing over top.
Dribble with melted butter.
Bake at 350° for one hour.
Sprinkle with parsley just before serving.

title: million dollar fudge
directions: Mix the following in large container: broken candy bars, chips, oleo, marshmallow cream and vanilla.
Mix the following in large saucepan: large can of milk and 4 1/2 cups sugar.
Let sugar and milk come to a boil.
After it starts to boil, cook for 6 minutes.
Pour mixture of sugar and milk over chocolate and blend until smooth and creamy.
Add pecans.
Pour in large cookie sheet (greased).

title: apple cobbler
directions: Mix ingredients together and set aside.
In an 8 x 8-inch square Pyrex dish, slice thinly about 1-inch apples.
Remove the crust from white bread and slice into 1-inch strips.
Place strips of bread, meeting in center of dish, close together.
Pour or spoon the margarine mixture over the bread strips and bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
If using Stamen or Winesap apples, bake 45 to 50 minutes.
Peaches or strawberries can be used.

title: breakfast sausage-egg casserole
directions: Cook sausage in skillet over medium flame until done, stirring to crumble; drain on paper towels.
Combine cooked sausage and remaining ingredients, mixing well.
Pour mixture into a well-greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
Refrigerate, covered, overnight.
Uncover and bake in a 350° gas oven for 1 hour. Yield:
8 servings.

title: rice lasagna(low-fat)
directions: Cook rice according to package; cool.
Add Egg Beaters and part of Parmesan cheese; mix and set aside.
Preheat oven to 375°. Combine cheeses, reserving 2 tablespoons of Parmesan cheese; mix well.
Brown meat in microwave for about 4 to 5 minutes, covered with waxed paper, in a small bowl.
Drain off any visible fat. Add spaghetti sauce and mushrooms; heat mixture in the microwave for 1 minute.
Spoon half of the rice mixture into an 8-inch square casserole dish that has been sprayed with nonfat cooking spray.
Cover with half of the meat sauce.
Repeat layers.
Top with remaining 2 tablespoons Parmesan cheese.
Bake for 20 minutes, or until thoroughly heated.
Serves 8.

title: big mac cookies
directions: Take 1/2 box of vanilla wafers, brush top of wafer with little lite Karo; sprinkle with sesame seed.
Take other 1/2 of box of wafers and leave plain.
Mix 1/2 cup Crisco, 1/4 cup warm water, add 1 pound confectioners sugar to make icing.
Divide frosting in half; add 1 drop of green food coloring to half of frosting so that you keep 1/2 white and 1/2 green.
Unwrap small mint patties; frost bottom of wafer with the sesame seed with green frosting.
Frost bottom of plain wafer with white frosting; insert mint patty. Walla, you now have a BIG MAC.

title: taffy apple salad
directions: Mix egg, flour, sugar, pineapple juice and vinegar in a small saucepan and cook slowly until thick.
Set aside and let cool. Add Cool Whip to cooled mixture.
Mix drained crushed pineapple and apples (unpeeled and cut into bite size cubes).
Combine with Cool Whip mixture.
Add honey roasted peanuts and mix through the salad, saving some to sprinkle on top.

title: german cake(fruit filled)
directions: Cream together margarine and sugar.
Add eggs and vanilla and beat until smooth and creamy.
Add flour and salt and blend until well mixed.
In a 13 x 9 x 2-inch sheet cake pan, spread a little more than 1/2 of batter on bottom of ungreased pan.
Spread fruit pie filling (I use cherry or blueberry) over top of batter in pan. Drop by spoonfuls the remaining batter onto the pie filling. Bake at 325° for approximately 1 hour.
Top will be light golden brown.
Test cake with toothpick for doneness.
Can be served warm and with whipped cream or ice cream.

title: deviled crab quiche
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
In mixing bowl, combine flour, salt and chili powder.
Cut in butter until mixture resembles bread crumbs. Combine with cheese and mix well.
Add cold water and mix to form a fairly firm dough.
Knead gently on floured surface and roll out to fit a 10-inch flan pan (removable bottom).
Press pastry into pan and trim edge.
Prick base with fork and bake 15 to 20 minutes until dry and golden brown.
Fry bacon for 3 minutes; add onion and cook additional 2 minutes.
Remove from heat and mix with crabmeat.
Spoon mixture into pastry.
Whisk eggs, half and half, mustard and cayenne.
Pour over dry mixture in pastry shell.
Set flan pan on baking sheet.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes until set and top is lightly browned.
Can be served warm or cold.
Garnish with slices of tomatoes.

title: one-meal dish
directions: Slice potatoes in bottom of greased 1 1/2-quart casserole and sprinkle with 1/2 teaspoon salt and 1/8 teaspoon pepper.
Add rice and then ground beef.
Sprinkle in 1 teaspoon salt.
Add onions and carrots, sliced.
Pour tomato juice over all.
Cover and bake 1 1/2 hours at 350°.

title: dill dip
directions: Combine ingredients and mix well. Refrigerate for intensified taste.

title: microwave roasted pecans
directions: Melt butter in oblong glass dish on High for 30 seconds.
Add pecans and toss to coat.
Microwave on High for 3 to 6 minutes, stirring every 2 minutes.
Drain on paper towel and add salt to taste.

title: holiday eggnog
directions: Beat all ingredients, except cream, together in blender or with electric hand mixer.
Chill in refrigerator.
Fold in whipped cream before serving and top bowl with nutmeg.

title: crab and spinach quiche
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Prepare crust, following directions for 9-inch shell.
Bake in preheated oven at 425° for 5 minutes or until set.
Place on wire rack.
Cook spinach, following label directions and drain and squeeze out excess water.
Beat eggs with yogurt, flour, salt and pepper in medium size bowl.
Stir in spinach and crab meat.
Sprinkle mushrooms, cheese and onions over crust.
Pour in spinach mixture.
Bake at 425° for 15 minutes. Lower heat to 350° and bake 30 minutes longer or until knife inserted in center comes out clean.

title: blueberry bread
directions: In saucepan, melt butter in boiling water.
Add orange juice and ring.
In bowl, beat egg well.
Add sugar and beat until fluffy.
Sift flour, baking powder, soda and salt together.
Add to egg and sugar alternately with juice, rind and butter combination.
Fold in blueberries.
Bake in paper lined 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan at 325° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Remove from pan.
While still hot, spoon glaze over top of loaf and immediately wrap in foil until cold.

title: easy egg custard
directions: In a mixing bowl, put flour, sugar, eggs and milk and mix well.
Melt butter.
Add to mixture with flavoring.
It will make its own thin crust.

title: angel biscuits
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Mix all ingredients together. Stir until well mixed.
Put in refrigerator for about 30 minutes. Spoon onto baking sheet as needed.
Store unused portion in the refrigerator.
Will keep 3 or 4 days.
Bake 18 to 20 minutes at 400°.

title: monkey bread
directions: Cut biscuit into quarters.
Mix sugar and cinnamon.
Dip biscuit pieces into sugar mixture or shake in plastic bag.
Put pieces in a well-greased angel food or Bundt pan.
Melt butter or margarine; do not boil.
Pour over pieces in pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Cool 10 minutes.
Turn upside down on plate. Tear off or cut into slices.

title: corn fritters
directions: Chop the corn very fine and add salt, pepper, well-beaten egg, melted fat, milk, flour and baking powder.
Fry 2 to 3 minutes in deep fat (360° to 370°).

title: artichoke dip supreme
directions: Combine all ingredients stir and mix well by hand.
Pour into greased baking dish. Bake in preheated 350° oven until bubbly. Stir to get even heat as cooking.
Garnish with paprika and parsley.
Approximate cooking time is 15 to 20 minutes.
You can cheat and bake in microwave oven.
Serve with assorted crackers or king-size Fritos.

title: broccoli soup
directions: Bring 5 cups water to boil.
Add onion, broccoli (can be fresh or frozen; if frozen, equal to one head of broccoli, more, if desired).
Reduce heat and simmer uncovered for 10 minutes.
Add Cheez Whiz and seasoning, stirring until Cheez melts.
Stir in half and half and butter; cook over low heat.
Combine flour and cold water, stirring until smooth.
Gradually add to broccoli mixture, stirring constantly.
Cook over medium heat until thickened, stirring constantly.

title: mrs. percle's onion dip
directions: Mash cream cheese and mayonnaise together until as smooth as possible.
Stir in onion.

title: lemon ice cream pie
directions: Combine crumbs, sugar and butter. Line pie tin or freezer ice tray. Press crumb mixture firmly into tin forming the crust. Cook at 300° for a few minutes.	Mix lemon juice, rind, 1/2 cup sugar and butter. Cook until sugar and butter melt. Add beaten egg and cook until it thickens. Cool. Then spread over ice cream and freeze. The ice cream is the pie crust. Serve with a thin slice of lemon twist.

title: egg noodles
directions: Beat egg yolks and vinegar together; work in flour, 1/2 cup at a time.
Roll out on a floured surface.
Roll up jelly roll style and slice thin.
Spread out and dry until needed.
I like to add a dash of salt and pepper with my first 1/2 cup flour to give it more taste.
Noodles are delicious with stewed boned chicken or beef.

title: stuffed celery
directions: Cream the cream cheese and add seasonings and enough mayonnaise to spread.
Fill chilled celery stalks with mixture. Chill.

title: pineapple cake
directions: Mix well.
Bake at 350° until brown.

title: in-a-hurry bread
directions: Combine water, yeast and sugar, and let stand for 10 minutes. Add salt, oil and 5 cups flour and knead (adding other 1/2 cup, if needed).
Place dough in greased bowl, cover and let rise in slightly warm oven until double in size.
Punch down and allow to rest 15 to 20 minutes.
Divide in half and shape in 2 greased loaf pans.
Brush loaves with margarine and bake 30 to 35 minutes at 350°.
Remove from pans immediately.
Yields 2 loaves.

title: mexican caviar
directions: Mix all ingredients together. Let sit overnight in refrigerator.

title: three bean salad
directions: Mix all ingredients and stir well.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Sift all dry ingredients twice.
Beat eggs and sugar together. Add oil and vanilla; mix well.
Combine with sifted dry ingredients.

title: cranberry crumb bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.

title: cucumber salad
directions: Blend all ingredients except sour cream.
Pour over cucumbers and marinate 2 hours; drain.
Blend in sour cream well.

title: vegetable dip
directions: Mix all together.
The longer it sets, the better it gets.

title: candied pretzels
directions: Melt almond bark in microwave.
It's best to do a small amount at a time.
Dip pretzels in melted bark and put on wax paper to dry. Can be stored several weeks.

title: beef burgundy
directions: Put all ingredients in covered casserole dish.
Bake for 2 hours at 325°.
Stir after 1 hour.

title: marinated black-eyed pea salsa
directions: Mix the oil, vinegar, salt, pepper and garlic.
Pour over the remaining ingredients in a large bowl.
Cover and refrigerate at least 2 hours -- but no longer than 24 hours, stirring occasionally.
Serve with chips.
Excellent!

title: quail, pheasant or duck
directions: Brown birds in a large frying pan with butter and shallots until browned. Put olive oil in roasting pan, swish to cover bottom.
Put in bay leaves, onions, carrot, juniper berries, and 2 thinly sliced, unpeeled mandarins.
Sprinkle birds with cinnamon, rosemary and tarragon.
Place in pan with vegetables.
Place in 350° oven and roast for 3 hours, basting with mandarin juice and honey.
Remove birds from pan, strain sauce and serve on the side.

title: brownies
directions: Mix together.
Put in oven and bake.
Cut up and eat them.

title: buckeye candy
directions: Mix in a large bowl the confectioners sugar, peanut butter and oleo.
Form into balls (size of walnuts).
Melt in double boiler the chocolate bits and paraffin.
Dip walnut-size balls by toothpicks into chocolate and place on wax paper until chocolate hardens.
(Leave tops without chocolate.)
Store in cool place. Makes approximately 200 to 300 Buckeyes.

title: chicken parmesan
directions: Mix all together. Take chicken and dip in milk; roll in mixture. Place in baking pan and dot with oleo. Sprinkle with parsley. Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: hearty manicotti
directions: In a covered 5-quart Dutch oven over medium heat, in 1/4 cup water, cook sausage links 5 minutes.
Uncover; brown well.
Drain on paper towels.

title: meat loaf
directions: Grease pan with canola oil.
Also rub a little oil on top of meat loaf to form a crust.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes.
Then at 400° for 15 minutes.

title: cheese grits
directions: Cook grits in boiling water until thick; add butter, seasonings and cheese, stirring until melted.
Beat eggs lightly and stir into grits mixture.
Pour into buttered casserole dish and bake for 1 hour at 325°.
(Placing a sheet of foil under the pan seems to prevent it from sticking.)

title: chicken breast casserole
directions: Place beef in the middle of chicken breast.
Wrap with bacon. Place all chicken in a casserole dish.
Cover with soup (undiluted) and dollop with sour cream.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: ham biscuits
directions: Cut ham and cheese into small pieces.
Mix remaining ingredients.
Split rolls; spread mixture on both halves of rolls, then put ham and cheese on rolls.
Put back together.
Bake at 375° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: mini meat loaves
directions: Mix
ingredients and add the onion soup mix.
Make into 4 loaves.
Bake 50 to 60 minutes at 350°.

title: poppy seed bread
directions: Combine
the
first
5 ingredients in a large bowl; mix until blended.
Sift
together
the 3 dry ingredients.
Blend into
egg mixture.
Add
poppy
seed and vanilla.
Beat until smooth.
Bake in
3 greased and floured loaf pans at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes. Makes 3 loaves.
Freezes well.

title: sugar-free raspberry pie
directions: In medium saucepan, combine Jell-O, pudding and water.
Cook until boiling; cool.
Will thicken as it cools.
Add raspberries and pour into pie shell.
Refrigerate for at least 2 hours.

title: bread pudding
directions: Break bread in small pieces.
Put in mixing bowl with 1 cup sugar, evaporated milk, 2 cups milk, vanilla, egg yolks and melted butter.
Mix well.
Pour in 10 x 8 x 2-inch pan.
Bake at 450° for 15 minutes.

title: squash fritters
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Form into pancakes; fry in hot oil until brown on each side.

title: cowboy cookies
directions: Beat together sugars and shortening.
Add eggs. Add flour, soda, salt and baking powder.
Add vanilla, oatmeal and chips. Drop by spoonfuls onto cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: cornish game hens with brandy apricot glaze
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Rinse hens and pat dry.
Mix rice and orange rind in a bowl.
Stuff each hen with rice mixture.
Place hens, breast sides up, on a rack in roasting pan.
Cover loosely with foil and roast 45 minutes.
Heat jam and brandy in saucepan. Remove hens from oven and remove foil; brush hens with jam mixture. Lower temperature to 325° and roast an extra 30 minutes.
Baste. Arrange with extra rice, crab apples, watercress or parsley.

title: sour cream cookies
directions: Cream shortening, sugar, eggs, sour cream and vanilla; blend well.
Stir dry ingredients into creamed mixture.
Blend well.
Add nuts.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: oyster spoon bread
directions: Heat oven to 325° and grease a 2-quart casserole dish.
In a 2-quart saucepan, over medium heat, mix first three ingredients; bring to boil for 2 minutes.
Remove from heat and add next three ingredients.
In small bowl, mix next three ingredients and beat into first mixture.
Stir in next three ingredients.
Fold in egg whites, pour into casserole and sprinkle with paprika.
Bake approximately 1 1/2 hours, until knife inserted in center comes out clean.

title: oat bran muffins
directions: I take plain oatmeal, putting small quantities at a time through the blender, to make oat bran.
Bake at 350° until done. Makes 1 dozen.

title: fish italano
directions: Top fish with sauce, onion, green pepper and last Mozzarella cheese.
Bake at 400 for 15 to 20 minutes.
Serves 3 or 4.

title: lemon pie
directions: Place Cool Whip in freezer for about 15 minutes. Have lemonade at room temperature. Mix all together. Add food color. Pour in pie crust and chill.

title: pineapple banana cake
directions: Mix dry ingredients together.
Add diced bananas, oil, vanilla, eggs and crushed pineapple and juice.
Stir to blend, but do not beat.
Pour into a greased 9-inch tube pan and bake at 350° for 1 hour and 20 minutes.
Let cool in pan on rack.
This cake is served without frosting.

title: pig cake
directions: Prepare cake mix according to directions, substituting liquid from oranges and pineapple.
Add oranges, oil, eggs and pudding. Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: ricotta pie
directions: Remove sausage from casing, crumble and cook.
Let cool.
Mix together eggs, Ricotta, Parmesan and Mozzarella cheese.
Add cooled sausage.
Place pie crust into a 9-inch pan following package directions.
Fill with cheese mixture and top with second crust.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour.
Let cool before cutting.

title: granny's cookies
directions: Mix together. Roll into 1-inch balls and flatten with a fork. Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: cherry cheese pie
directions: Line pie pan with rolled pie crust.
Spread filling evenly in crust.
Place vented or lattice top crust over filling.
Bake at 425° for 10 minutes; reduce heat to 350° and continue baking for 25 to 35 minutes, until golden brown.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: heilmans cole slaw
directions: Shred cabbage and refrigerate about 1 hour.
Then mix in the rest of the ingredients, pouring the whipping cream in last.
Keep chilled until ready to serve.

title: pasta e fagioli
directions: In soup pot in olive oil, saut onion, garlic and celery until onions are about clear.
Add canned tomatoes, navy beans and Italian seasoning and simmer over medium-low heat for about 15 minutes.
Next, add potatoes and water until pot is about 2/3 full.
When it comes to a boil, add bouillon and simmer/boil over medium heat for 10 minutes.
Add pasta.
Continue to cook for 2 or 3 minutes.
Turn heat off.
Let sit until pasta is tender, but not mushy.
Enjoy!

title: happiness cake
directions: Mix thoroughly and add tears of joy, sorrow and sympathy. Flavor with little gifts of joy.
Fold in 4 cups of prayer and faith to lighten all other ingredients and raise texture to great heights of character.
After pouring this into your daily life, bake well with the heat of human kindness.
Serve this with a smile anytime and it will satisfy the hunger of starved souls.

title: chili tortilla bake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. In a large skillet, brown ground beef over medium-high heat; drain. Add tomato sauce, beans, corn and green chilies. Stir in next 5 seasonings. Bring to a boil and reduce heat. Simmer, uncovered, 15 minutes. In a 2-quart baking dish, coated with cooking spray, place 3 flour tortillas to cover bottom. Overlap as needed. Layer with half of cheese. Top with remaining tortillas, meat mixture and cheese. Bake 30 minutes. Serves 8.

title: french dip
directions: Melt butter, then stir in flour and onion.
Add broth, horseradish and salt.
Cook until thickened and smooth.
Serve over beef or use as French Dip.

title: easy peach cobbler
directions: Combine peeled and sliced peaches with sugar and water and set aside.
Mix together 1/2 cup sugar, flour, baking powder, salt, milk, melted butter and vanilla and
pour into greased 8 x 12-inch baking dish.
Spoon peaches over the mixture and pour remaining water (and syrup) on top.
Bake for 20 to 25 minutes or until golden brown in preheated 400° oven.

title: cold soup
directions: Put ingredients in blender and blend.

title: molasses cookies
directions: Bring to boil brown sugar, molasses, ginger, cloves and cinnamon.
Stir in soda.
Pour over butter in large bowl.
Stir until melted.
Add egg and flour.
Knead until smooth.
Refrigerate 2 hours.
Roll out on wax paper until 1/4 inch thick.
Cut with desired cookie patterns.
Bake in 325° oven for 15 minutes.

title: *bustan tava (ghiuveci)(vegetable casserole)
directions: Place in a large pan (larger than 9 x 13-inch) the onions, eggplant, peppers, string beans, garlic, zucchini and okra. Sprinkle with 1/2 cup olive oil over all.
Toss lightly so vegetables are covered with oil.
Pour the tomatoes and tomato sauce over the vegetables. Add the black pepper, salt, paprika and dried
parsley. Toss again, lightly.
Drizzle 1/4 cup olive oil on top.
Bake at 400° about 1 1/4 hours or until all liquid is gone except for traces of the oil.
Bake, uncovered.
Halfway through baking, gently turn vegetables over with large spatula.

title: potato-corn soup
directions: Combine and simmer onion, water, potatoes, carrots and bouillon cubes until potatoes are tender, about 15 to 20 minutes. Stir in milk, corn and pepper.
Continue simmering.
Mix flour and cheese, then add to soup, simmer and stir until cheese is melted. Great with cornbread.

title: chocolate chip meringue cookies
directions: Beat egg whites until stiff, gradually adding sugar and salt. Stir in chips.
Bake at 225 degrees for 35-45 minutes on greased wax paper over greased pan.

title: crispy beef casserole
directions: Brown ground beef and onion in skillet.
Cook celery and onions in small amount of water in saucepan until tender.
Place layer of beef mixture, peas, celery and carrots in 1-quart casserole.
Repeat procedure.
Mix soup, milk and Worcestershire sauce.
Pour over other ingredients.
Top with potato chips.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: sweet peach pickles
directions: Scrub fuzz from peaches.
Boil all ingredients, but peaches, for 5 minutes.
Put peaches in a few at a time.
When they are done enough, take them out and put into a jar.
Put others in to cook.
Repeat until all peaches have been done.
Boil syrup down and pour over peaches.
Seal hot.

title: strawberry cake
directions: Mix well the cake mix, Jell-O, oil and juice. Add beaten eggs and mix well. Pour into greased and floured oblong pan. Bake at 350° for about 40 minutes. Check with toothpick for doneness.

title: crab dip
directions: In a bowl, mix the first 10 ingredients until smooth.
Spread in a 9-inch pie plate.
Sprinkle with bread crumbs.
Cover and bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until bubbly.
Uncover and bake 5 minutes more.
Serve with crackers or raw vegetables.
Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: cherry cheese pie
directions: Beat the cream cheese until light and fluffy.
Add sweetened condensed milk; blend thoroughly.
Stir in lemon juice and vanilla.
Pour into graham cracker crust.
Chill 3 hours or until firm.
Top with pie filling and serve.

title: turkey or chicken casserole
directions: Combine cooked and drained macaroni with turkey and stir in celery, onion, walnuts, lemon juice, salt and pepper.
Blend in Miracle Whip and peas.
Top with 1 cup crushed potato chips.
Bake for 1/2 hour at 350°.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Combine and cream first 4 ingredients.
Mix all other ingredients and add to first mixture.
Blend well.
Roll dough into ball and refrigerate at least 1 hour.
Flour rolling surface pin. Roll to 1/4 inch to 1/8 inch thick.
Cut with cookie cutters. Place on cookie sheet.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes at 350°.
Decorate with sprinkles.

title: buffalo chips
directions: Mix butter and sugar. Add eggs and vanilla; mix well. Stir in oats and corn flakes. Sift together flour, soda and baking powder and stir into mixture. Stir in pecans and drop by spoon onto ungreased cookie sheet. Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes. Makes 5 to 6 dozen.

title: christmas salad
directions: Mix together in a saucepan the sugar, vinegar, celery and mustard seed.
Bring to a boil.
Mix shredded cabbage, grated carrots, chopped peppers and onions together.
Pour hot vinegar mixture over slaw and let cool.
Refrigerate overnight or put into freezer cartons and freeze for future use.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Mix Miracle Whip, sugar and vinegar together.
Combine all other ingredients in a medium bowl.
Pour mixture over all other ingredients.
Refrigerate 2 hours.

title: blueberry crunch
directions: In a 9 x 12-inch pan, layer pineapple, berries and dry cake mix.
Dribble margarine on top of cake mix.
Add nuts and sprinkle with sugar.
Bake at 325° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: mushroom and onion roast
directions: Season roast with salt and pepper, A.1. sauce and dehydrated soups.
Add water.
Seal in foil and bake at 350° for 3 hours.

title: clogger salad(10 to 21 servings)
directions: Breakup ramen noodles (do not cook).
In large bowl combine noodles, coleslaw vegetables, almonds, sunflower seeds and green onions.

title: infallible rice in the microwave
directions: Saute onion and butter in microwave until transparent.
Heat broth and onions for 6 to 7 minutes on High.
Add rice.
Cook, covered, for 10 minutes on High.
Allow to remain covered 10 minutes longer.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: ida craver's cooked german slaw
directions: Shred cabbage as for slaw.
Heat bacon drippings and add flour.
Brown as for gravy.
Add vinegar and some water.
Add cabbage and cook until limber.
You may need to add more water and vinegar according to taste or you may need to delete some vinegar.

title: spicy clams and rice
directions: Drain clam liquid into large measuring cup.
Add water to equal 2 cups.
Set aside.
In 3-quart saucepan, saute onion and garlic until onion is transparent.
Stir in paprika, parsley, white pepper, crushed pepper, wine and clams.
Add rice and clam juice/water mixture and bring to a boil.
Cover and simmer until all liquid is absorbed (15 to 17 minutes).
Serves 4 to 6.

title: easy beef stroganoff
directions: Slice beef across grain in very thin strips.
Brown 1/2 meat in skillet on high heat with 1 tablespoon margarine and 1/2 onion. Cook until no pink is showing; set aside.
Repeat with remaining butter, beef and onion.
Return all mixture to skillet.
Stir in soup and paprika.
Heat through.
Stir in sour cream.
Serve over cooked noodles.
Serves 6.

title: beet salad
directions: Drain beets and then dice. Boil egg and cut up.
Dice onion and add mayonnaise.
Mix well.

title: peanut butter muffins
directions: Batter will be lumpy.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes in a 400° oven. Let stand for 5 minutes.
Makes 16.

title: punch
directions: Bring sugar and water to boil.
Let cool, then add lemonade, orange juice, pineapple juice and mashed bananas.
Freeze.
Take out of freezer about 1 1/2 hours before using and thaw to slush. Add ginger ale.
Ready to serve.

title: west virginia meat loaf
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Mix meat well with next 5 ingredients. Soak bread in milk. Add eggs and beat with fork. Combine meat and egg mixtures. Form into 2 loaves and roll in dried bread crumbs. Place in shallow baking pan. Completely cover tops of loaves with ketchup. Pour 1/2 cup boiling water around loaves. Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 1 hour. Serves 8 to 10 people.

title: yeast biscuits
directions: Dissolve yeast in water.
Sift flour, soda and sugar together. Put in a pan to mix.
Add oil, milk and yeast.
Mix together. Cook as needed by rolling into desired size and placing on greased pan.
Dough will keep in refrigerator.
Bake at 450° until light brown.

title: cherry fudge cake
directions: Beat altogether and pour into floured and greased cake pan (9 x 13-inch).
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Put a chocolate frosting on when cooled.

title: armadillo eggs
directions: Mix together the Monterey Jack and sausage.
Add biscuit mix. Work together.
The cheese and sausage will hold dough together. Divide dough into 15 equal parts.
Stuff peppers with a slice of Cheddar cheese.
Pat cheese and sausage mixture into small pancake shape.
Completely cover each pepper with mixture; make sure all edges and ends are sealed.
Roll back and forth in hands to form egg shape.
Roll egg in the Shake 'n Bake, then fry until golden brown.
Can be frozen before frying.

title: luncheon loaf
directions: Grind meat, crackers and cheese; blend well.
Beat egg and milk together.
Add to meat mixture.
Place in greased loaf pan and bake in 350° oven for 35 minutes.

title: pineapple upside-down carrot cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Melt margarine in 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan in oven.
Sprinkle with brown sugar.
Spoon pineapple over brown sugar; spread evenly.
Prepare cake mix as directed on package. Pour over pineapple.
Bake 35 to 40 minutes.
Cool 10 minutes. Invert onto heatproof platter; remove pan.
Cool cake completely. Serve with sweetened whipped cream if desired.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: I use an electric skillet on medium.
Dust steak with fork; brown in oleo with mushrooms and onions.
Add broth, soup, salt and pepper.
Cook, covered, until meat is tender, adding water as needed.
Mix with cooked egg noodles; put into a large casserole dish.
You can add sour cream right before serving if you desire.

title: flavored vinegar
directions: You will need an old bottle (the cruets with stoppers make the herb vinegar a beautiful gift).

title: german chocolate brownies
directions: Prepare brownie mix per package directions.
Cool.
Cover with frosting.
Melt chocolate chips and drizzle over frosting.

title: pretzel salad
directions: Press into a 9 x 10-inch pan, 3 tablespoons sugar, pretzels and butter (melted).
Bake 10 minutes in a 350° oven.
Cool.

title: peach salad
directions: Bring pineapple, water and sugar to a boil; remove from heat and add gelatin.
Chill until partially set.
Whip slightly before adding other ingredients.
In a separate bowl, beat cream cheese with milk; add Cool Whip and fold into gelatin mixture.
Pour into pan and chill until set.

title: scampi linguini
directions: Heat oil in a large skillet.
Add garlic and shrimp.
Cook and stir until shrimp turns pink.
Add wine, lemon juice, basil and parsley.
Cook 5 minutes longer.

title: pot of black-eyed peas
directions: Place ham hocks in 2 quarts of water in a 4-quart pot and boil slowly for 15 minutes.
Add frozen black-eyed peas and simmer for about 1 hour until peas are tender.
Salt to taste.
Serve over rice with a dash of hot pepper sauce.

title: aunt ruthie's chili relleno casserole
directions: Grease square casserole pan.
Cover with Jack cheese and then Cheddar cheese.
Add flour and milk to beaten eggs, blending together.
Add to casserole.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Top with tomato sauce and heat through.

title: cucumber stick pickles
directions: 1st Day:
Peel and cut cucumbers into strips, removing seed section.
Soak 24 hours in 2 gallons of water with 2 cups lime.

title: chocolate drops
directions: Mix together well. Drop by teaspoon on lightly greased cookie sheet. Bake at 350° for about 10 minutes.

title: carrot cake
directions: Beat the sugar, oil and eggs with a mixer.
Add dry ingredients.
Fold in the carrots, pineapple, coconut and nuts. Also add vanilla.
Bake in greased and floured 13 x 9-inch pan or glass dish (I use a Bundt pan) at 350° for 1 hour.
Frost with cream cheese frosting, Cool Whip or whatever you like.

title: microwave fudge
directions: Put all ingredients, except vanilla, in a microwave safe bowl.
Microwave for 3 minutes, stirring thoroughly every 30 seconds.
Remove from microwave and stir in vanilla.
Immediately pour into 8-inch square pan lined with foil and well buttered. Refrigerate overnight.
Cut into squares.

title: cool whip dessert
directions: Drain pineapple well. Sprinkle dry Jell-O over cottage cheese. Mix well.
Add other ingredients.
Add nuts if desired.
Chill. Use as salad or dessert.

title: fruit bars
directions: Cream sugar, shortening and eggs; add vanilla, flour, powder and salt. Fold in dates, walnuts and cherries. Bake in a well-greased 13 x 9 pan at 350° for 45 minutes or until done.

title: mom's meat ball stew
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Make meat balls by mixing together well ground beef, 2 tablespoons chopped onion, green peppers, cornmeal, salt, chili powder, dry mustard, milk and egg.
Roll into balls and roll in 4 tablespoons flour; then brown in oil in large skillet.

title: pineapple graham cracker pie
directions: Prepare crust. Mix graham cracker crumbs and sugar. Then mix in butter. Pack into a 9 inch pie plate and bake 375 degrees for about 8 minutes. Heat pineapple and add marshmallows allowing them to
melt. Add 2 Tbsp. jello powder. Stir until dissolved. Cool until it begins to stiffen then add cream. Add 2 Tbsp. powdered sugar to cream. Pour into graham cracker crust and refrigerate.

title: blueberry jello salad
directions: Drain all fruit.
Keep 1 cup of juice.
Dissolve jello in hot water; add liquid from fruit.
Add fruit and let set.
Beat cream cheese, sour cream, vanilla, and sugar until smooth.
Spread over jello.
Sprinkle with nuts.
Keep refrigerated.

title: seasoned oyster crackers
directions: Combine Ranch salad dressing.
Mix with dill weed, lemon pepper, garlic salt and oil.
Pour over crackers.
Stir to coat. Place in warm oven at 300° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Stir gently halfway through baking.
Adds a nice surprise to soup.

title: easy enchiladas
directions: Brown ground beef and onion.
Add seasoning, tomato sauce and 1 can of enchilada sauce (with a little water if needed).
Heat and set aside.
Heat 1 can enchilada sauce and chili.
Dip tortillas in chili mixture.
Put meat mixture on tortillas with shredded cheese and roll up.
Place in casserole dish.
Pour any remaining chili mixture on top of enchiladas and top with more cheese.
Heat at 350° for about 30 minutes.

title: carrot cake
directions: Grease and lightly flour a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
In a large mixing bowl, stir together flour, sugar, baking powder, baking soda, salt and cinnamon; add carrots, oil and eggs.
Mix until moistened; beat at medium speed of electric mixer for 2 minutes.
Pour into preferred (13 x 9 x 2-inch) baking pan.
Bake in a 325° oven for 50 to 60 minutes or until wooden pick inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool thoroughly on wire rack.
Frost with Cream Cheese Frosting.
Serves 12 to 15.

title: molasses cookies
directions: Mix and chill.	Roll into balls, roll in sugar.
Bake at 375° for about 12 minutes.
These cookies burn easily on the bottom, so it's best if you use parchment paper.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Peel potatoes, slice and boil.
Put
in
large
bowl
to mixer on low speed; mash
well.
Add
butter while potatoes are warm. Add sugar, egg, milk and vanilla.
Pour into unbaked pie shell and bake in moderate oven until filling is set and begins to brown. Do not preheat oven.

title: nachos and dip
directions: Whip sour cream and cream cheese in a mixing bowl.
Spread on bottom of round pie or quiche dish.
Top with finely chopped lettuce and plum tomatoes.
Sprinkle shredded Cheddar cheese on top.
Dip and enjoy!!
Serve cold.

title: mocha nut butter balls
directions: Cream the butter, sugar and vanilla until light.
Add next 4 ingredients and mix well.
Add nuts. Shape into 1-inch balls and place on ungreased cookie sheets.
Bake in preheated slow oven at 325° for about 15 minutes. Cool and roll in confectioners sugar. Yields 6 dozen.

title: lemon nut cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs and beat well.
Add flour, baking powder and lemon extract.
Beat.
Stir in cherries, raisins and pecans.
Bake at 275° for 2 hours or until done.

title: german slaw
directions: Boil oil, vinegar and sugar 3 minutes and pour over cabbage. Keeps several days under refrigeration.

title: stir-n-drop sugar cookies
directions: Heat oven to 400°. Beat eggs with a fork; stir in oil and vanilla. Blend sugar until mixture thickens. Measure flour, baking powder and salt. Stir in mixture. Drop by teaspoonfuls. Bake 8 to 10 minutes.

title: chili beans
directions: Cook pintos.
Chop vegetables and tomatoes.
Brown beef.
Add other ingredients and mix with pintos and simmer 1 hour.

title: french toast
directions: Place all ingredients except bread in blender.
Blend on medium speed until thoroughly mixed.
Pour into shallow bowl. Preheat griddle to high.
Dip bread into mixture and brown both sides.
Sprinkle powdered sugar over and serve with syrup.

title: pecan millionaires
directions: Mix Marshmallow Creme and Kisses.
Set aside.
Melt margarine. Combine with milk and sugar.
Cook and let come to a boil.
Boil for 8 minutes.
Pour over Creme and Kisses mixture.
Stir until Kisses mixture is melted.
Add pecans.
Pour into waxed paper.
Cut when cooled.

title: unbelievable salad
directions: Pour the pineapple with its juice into a glass measure. Microwave on High for 2 to 2 1/2 minutes, until boiling. Carefully remove from microwave.
Add the gelatin.
Stir with a wooden spoon until dissolved.
Chill in refrigerator until it is cool and begins to thicken.
This will take about 2 hours.
Remove from refrigerator and stir in oranges, cottage cheese and whipped topping.
Pour into square dish.
Refrigerate until firm.
Cut into squares and serve on lettuce leaves.

title: blueberry dump cake
directions: Butter a 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
Add in layers the undrained pineapple, blueberries, sugar and dry cake mix.
Do not stir. Drizzle melted butter over cake mix; sprinkle with pecans.
Bake at 350° for about 45 minutes.

title: unbelievable easy fudge
directions: Combine ingredients in microwave safe dish. Cook in microwave for 2 minutes. Stir until all the mixture is mixed together. Pour into a buttered pan. Refrigerate for a few minutes and slice.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook the squash until tender. Scoop out inside and mash.
Add egg, crackers, cheese and salt and pepper.
Heat in oven until cheese melts.

title: lemon meringue pie
directions: In saucepan, mix sugar, cornstarch and salt, using a wire whisk.
Still using whisk, gradually blend in cold water. Place over heat and cook until it starts to thicken, stirring constantly.

title: applesauce cake doughnuts
directions: Beat eggs. Stir in sugar and shortening, then blend in applesauce and vanilla. To this mixture, add remaining dry ingredients, gradually blending in until dough is well mixed.
For easier handling of the dough and to ensure that the doughnuts will hold their shape when cut, chill the dough in refrigerator for about 2 hours.

title: croutons for fruit soups
directions: Cut bread into 1-inch cubes.
Dip cubes into cream.
Quickly saute in butter.
Roll in sugar.

title: quick and crumbly peanut butter fudge
directions: Boil sugar, cream and margarine to soft ball.
Add vanilla and peanut butter.
Beat.

title: taco salad
directions: Mix the first 5 ingredients.
Before serving, crush 1/2 bag of nacho cheese Doritos.
Mix taco sauce and salad dressing.

title: fudge marble bars
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Set aside cocoa packet.
Combine cake mix, 1/4 cup water, eggs and butter in large bowl.
Add cocoa packet, chocolate chips and 1 teaspoon water.
Stir until blended.
Add nuts to yellow batter.
Spread in pan.
Spoon chocolate batter randomly on top.
Swirl with knife. Bake at 350° for 22 to 27 minutes or until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool; cut into bars, 2 x 1 1/2-inch.

title: reuben sandwich
directions: Place one slice of the corned beef and one slice Swiss cheese on one piece of bread.
Heap on sauerkraut and spread the dressing on top.
Top with the second slice of bread.
Melt butter in a large skillet over medium-low heat.
Spread butter on outside of bread.
Grill sandwich in skillet or on griddle until lightly browned on both sides.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Mix all the ingredients.
Shape into balls, then press into baking sheet.
Crisscross with imprint of a fork.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: gob cake
directions: Line 2 cookie sheets with aluminum foil, shiny side next to mix or up.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: quiche
directions: Mix together all ingredients.
Pour into shells, dot with butter.
Sprinkle remainder of bacon on top.
Bake 20 to 30 minutes in 350° oven.

title: congo bars
directions: Mix ingredients in order given; mix well after each egg addition.
Spread into greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
(Do not overbake; this has a brownie texture.) Cool in pan; cut into bars or squares.
Yields six dozen.
(There is no liquid other than the eggs and melted margarine.)

title: oyster delight mix
directions: Put all ingredients in plastic bag and mix completely.
Let set at least 3 hours.
The longer it sits the better.

title: shrimp mold
directions: In large saucepan over low heat, heat tomato soup and cream cheese, stirring, until cream cheese melts.
Dissolve gelatin in cold water; stir into hot mixture.
Remove from heat; blend in mayonnaise.
Add the diced onion, celery, green pepper and shrimp. Pour mixture into a greased salad mold; refrigerate until firm. The flavor is better if allowed to set overnight.
Serve as a salad or hors d'oeuvre with crackers.

title: mom's favorite hash brown casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients and spread in a lightly buttered casserole dish.

title: fish stew
directions: Boil fish in salt water, dry and shred.
Mix all other ingredients together.
Bring to boil, then simmer.
Add fish and let simmer approximately 30 minutes.
Note:
Several dashes of Tabasco may be added for flavor.
This recipe is great served over rice.

title: pasta salad
directions: Cook pasta (not well done; firm).
Marinate overnight with lemon juice, oil, salt and Accent.
Next day, add olives, green peppers, celery, pimento, red onion and mayo.
Can be doubled for large group.

title: mexican salad
directions: Drain juice from beans.
Add beans, Fritos and Catalina dressing to salad.

title: hamburger soup
directions: Simmer hamburger, salt, pepper and onion.
Add beef broth.
Add noodles and diced potato.
Cook until potato is done.
More water may be needed.

title: nutty ham
directions: Melt garlic and butter or margarine.
Add 1/2 teaspoon sugar. Simmer about 3 minutes.
Bake ham at 350° to 400°.
Bake ham in covered pan for about 3 or 4 hours.
Simmer almonds in pineapple juice, about 10 minutes.
Take whole sliced pineapple on top of ham and let bake until brown.
Place on ham with toothpicks.
Take out and baste for about 30 minutes.

title: cheddar squash bake
directions: Place bacon in a skillet; fry until crisp.
Drain bacon and set aside, after crumbling.
Place squash and onion in a saucepan; cook until squash and onion are tender.
Drain and cool slightly. Beat egg yolks until thick and lemon-colored; stir next 5 ingredients.
Beat egg whites until stiff peaks form; fold into yolk mixture.

title: lumpia
directions: Cook chicken breast until tender, do not trim fat or skin. Remove from broth and cut into very small pieces, return to broth. Add bouillon cubes and simmer until dissolved.

title: chocolate-peanut butter pizza
directions: Spray a large pizza pan.
Mix the first 6 ingredients and bake for 10 minutes at 375°.
Add the remaining ingredients to the partially baked crust.
Continue to bake 5 to 8 minutes.

title: coconut pound cake
directions: Cream butter, sugar and Crisco until fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well.
Sift flour, baking powder and salt.
Fold in flour and milk alternately, until both are mixed in.
Stir in flavor.
Bake in preheated oven at 325° for 1 hour and 15 minutes. Cake should be baked in 10-cup greased and floured tube pan.

title: baked cabbage
directions: Brown onion and chopped cabbage until soft.
Melt butter in an 8 x 11-inch dish.
Layer onion and cabbage on bottom.
Next layer ground beef, then rice and cabbage on top.
Mix spaghetti sauce and 3 cups of water in pan; warm.
Pour over top.
Bake, covered, at 350° for 1 hour.

title: spaghetti casserole
directions: Cook spaghetti and drain.
Saute beef and margarine until brown; add tomato sauce, salt and pepper.
Remove from heat. Combine sour cream, cottage cheese, cream cheese, scallions and green pepper.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Boil chicken until tender and set aside to cool slightly.
Mix the next 3 ingredients together.
Add all bread stuffing, except 1 cup.
Cut up chicken in bite-size in a casserole dish.
Add cream mixture and bread stuffing on top of chicken.
Top all this with the one cup of leftover bread stuffing.
Bake in 350° oven for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: diet salad
directions: Drain liquid from corn, peas and green beans.
In large bowl, mix
all
ingredients and chill for 2 hours before serving.

title: meat loaf
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Combine all ingredients except ground beef and mix well.
Add ground beef; mix lightly, but thoroughly.
Pres into an 8 x 4-inch loaf pan.
Bake 1 hour.
Drain and let stand 5 minutes.

title: butterscotch haystacks
directions: Melt butterscotch morsels.
Mix peanuts and noodles in large bowl.
Pour in melted butterscotch.
Mix until all peanuts and noodles are covered.
Drop by teaspoonfuls on waxed paper.
When cool, store in tight container.

title: julekaka(christmas bread)
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Bake at 350° until hollow sound to tap on top.

title: texas sheet cake
directions: Melt margarine, add water and cocoa.
Bring to boil.
Remove from heat.
Add flour, sugar and baking soda in a large bowl. Pour in cocoa, margarine and water mixture.
Add sour cream, eggs and vanilla.
Baking time is 40 to 45 minutes at 350°.

title: potato pancakes
directions: Puree the onion, eggs, salt, pepper and flour in a blender or food processor fitted with the steel blade, scraping down the sides of the bowl as necessary.
Add the potato cubes and process until the potatoes are finely chopped, but not pureed.
Scrape the mixture into a mixing bowl and press a sheet of plastic wrap directly into surface of batter to prevent discoloration.
Allow the batter to sit for 15 minutes.

title: spareribs and sauerkraut
directions: Brown pork ribs in pressure cooker. Add rest of ingredients. Pressure cook for 25 minutes.

title: magic pickles
directions: Drain pickles.
Slice pickles 1/2-inch thick.
Put pickling spice and vinegar in 1/2 gallon jar.
Add drained pickles.
Pour 3 cups sugar on top (do not stir).
Close jar and let stand 8 days. After pickles are drained, add another quart of drained pickles and 1 cup sugar.
Let stand 10 days.

title: easy brunch pancake
directions: Slowly melt butter.
Mix together the milk and flour.
Add eggs; mix, leaving some lumps.
Pour into heavy baking pan which butter has been melted in.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar; squeeze fresh lemon over.
Add marmalade.

title: spinach dip
directions: Mix well and store in glass container.
It will keep for quite a long time.
Use vegetables to dip into it.

title: apple pound cake
directions: Beat eggs in a large bowl.
Add oil and vanilla.
Mix well. Add sugar and flour.
Mix and add apples, cinnamon and nuts.
Mix well.
Bake in oiled tube pan for 1 hour at 325°.

title: ratatouille
directions: Heat 1/4 cup of the oil in large frying pan over high heat. Add onions and garlic.
Cook, stirring until onions are soft, but not browned.
Stir in eggplant, zucchini, peppers, 2 teaspoons of salt, basil, minced garlic and parsley.
Add oil as needed to keep vegetables from sticking.
Cover and cook over medium heat (can use Dutch oven) for 30 minutes, stirring to prevent sticking. Add the tomatoes to vegetables and stir to blend.
Add more oil to prevent sticking.
Cover and cook for 15 minutes.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Saute onion in butter or margarine; stir in flour until dissolved, then add the broth and the rest of the ingredients. Cook until	thick and bubbly.
Prepare crust per directions on box; pour bubbly mixture in lined pie plate.
Place a crust on top, sealing
edges.
Score
the
center
of the crust several times for steam
to escape.
Bake at 425° for 20 minutes (with foil ring
around
pie
plate).
Bake an additional 15 minutes without foil until golden brown.

title: apple crisp
directions: Mix the first 4 ingredients together and put in a 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Mix remaining ingredients well and spoon on top of apple mixture.
Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour or until bubbly.

title: ziti and broccoli
directions: Wash broccoli.
Peel the stems; cut in halves or quarters. Cut off florets in 2-inch lengths and set aside.

title: pear cream cheese salad
directions: Drain and dice pears, reserving syrup.
Add water to syrup to make 1 1/2 cups; bring to a boil.
Dissolve gelatin in boiling measured liquid.
Add ginger ale and lemon juice.

title: artichoke dip
directions: Cream
together
mayonnaise
and
cream
cheese.
Add Parmesan cheese.
Add
Worcestershire, lemon juice and garlic. Fold in artichoke
(chopped good).	Bake uncovered at 350° for 20 to 25
minutes.
Serve warm with crackers.	Grease may form on top after baking.
Can be spooned off.

title: seven layer salad
directions: Mix together the celery, onion and bell pepper.
Layer ingredients in order given.
Refrigerate overnight in tight container.

title: butter cake
directions: Put all ingredients in bowl and mix for 10 minutes at medium speed.
Pour into two 9-inch greased and floured pans or one 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for approximately 45 minutes.

title: mulneix meatball sauce
directions: Combine sauce ingredients in pan and heat until melted.
Place meatballs on bottom of a large casserole dish.
Pour sauce on top and heat on low until the meatballs are cooked through (approximately 30 minutes with oven set at 350°).

title: beef-barley soup
directions: Brown meat in oil or butter.
Cover with water and simmer for several hours until tender.
Cool meat and chop.

title: merry berry salad mold
directions: Dissolve gelatin in water; add berries, nuts, lemon juice and spices.
Pour into oiled 7 x 11 x 2-inch pan; chill until firm. Combine mayonnaise and sour cream; spread over top of gelatin. Chill until served.

title: ray's chop suey
directions: Cube meat.
Chop vegetables.
Saute meat in small amount of oil and soy sauce.
Place small amount oil in large pan; cook onions and celery until slightly tender.
Add meat to vegetables. Dissolve the bouillon cubes in 1 cup water (hot); pour over meat and vegetables.
Add bean sprouts.
Thicken with mixture of cornstarch and 1 cup water.
Serve over noodles or rice.

title: pretzel salad
directions: Mix all ingredients and press in bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: fettucini with basil and tomatoes
directions: Mix tomatoes, onions, garlic, basil, olive oil, salt and pepper.
Let stand at room temperature for 1 hour.
Drain the cooked fettucini.
Toss with sauce.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Serve at once.

title: broiled grapefruit
directions: Wash and dry grapefruit.
Cut in half crosswise.
Cut pulp away from membrane in each section with small, sharp pointed knife.
Cut out membrane at core.
Sprinkle each half with 1 tablespoon brown sugar and dot with 1 teaspoon butter or margarine.
Place on rack in broiler pan and place pan in oven with grapefruit 3 inches from browning unit.
Broil from 5 to 10 minutes or until sugar melts and top of grapefruit is slightly browned.
Top with maraschino cherry, raisins or chopped nuts, if desired.
Serve hot.

title: 4 layered dessert
directions: 1st Layer:
Combine oleo, pecans and flour and mix well.
Put into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 15 minutes in moderate oven.
Cool completely.

title: boyfriend cookies
directions: Cream shortening, slowly beating in sugars.
Add unbeaten eggs and vanilla.
Beat until fluffy.
Sift flour with soda.
Add to mixture.
Add oats.
Stir into first mixture.
Stir in peanuts and chips, mixing well.
Drop by rounded teaspoonfuls onto ungreased sheet.
Bake 12 minutes at 375°.
Makes 6 dozen.

title: lemon apricot cake
directions: Combine cake mix, oil, nectar and eggs.
Beat at high speed 2 minutes.
Pour into greased and floured tube pan or 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour (35 minutes for 13 x 9-inch pan).
Prick top of cake with fork.
Mix confectioners sugar and lemon juice until smooth.
Pour over hot cake.
Sprinkle top with lemon peel.

title: spanish rice
directions: Brown hamburger and onion in a skillet. Stir in remaining ingredients and bring to a boil. Turn the heat down and simmer 30 to 40 minutes, stirring occasionally. Serves 4 to 5.

title: mexican dip
directions: Mix taco seasoning, 1 package taco cheese and 1/2 package Co-Jack cheese with the beans.
Spread on bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix sour cream and salsa; spread on top.
Sprinkle with rest of Co-Jack cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Let set for a few minutes before serving.

title: real cool pops
directions: Fruit kebobs are a breeze to make.
Simply spear bite size pieces of fresh fruit on wooden sticks and stash in the freezer until you feel the urge for something cold.
Use freezer friendly fruits:
grapes, peach slices, strawberries, melon balls, cherries, pineapple cubes and banana slices.
Store wrapped in plastic wrap, single layers.

title: shortcake
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Bake at 425° about 12 minutes.
Top with fresh fruit such as strawberries and peaches.

title: meatless manicotti
directions: Heat oil in large saucepan. Add onion and garlic; cook 2 to 3 minutes, stirring constantly. Stir in tomatoes, tomato paste, basil and 1/2 teaspoon salt. Bring to boil; reduce heat, cover and simmer 20 minutes, stirring occasionally.

title: pineapple cake
directions: Drain pineapple, reserving syrup.
Using the syrup as part of the liquid and the eggs, prepare cake according to package directions.
Pour into greased and floured 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
Bake as directed.

title: taco salad
directions: Just before serving, add 1/2 bag Doritos nacho chips, crushed. Add 1 large bottle Catalina dressing and just enough water to rinse bottle. Toss and enjoy.

title: pumpkin cheese cake
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients; put in bottom of spring-form pan.
Beat cheese until fluffy and gradually add milk.
Add other ingredients and mix well.
Pour over crust and bake 1 hour and 15 minutes at 300° until edge springs back.

title: taco salad
directions: Brown meat with soup mix; set aside to drain and cool on paper towels.
Mix remaining ingredients except dressing.
When meat cools, add to salad mixture.
Just before serving add dressing to taste.
Mix well.

title: cheesy green beans
directions: Cook bacon until crisp; reserve 1/4 cup drippings.
Crumble bacon.
Reserve 2 tablespoons.
Microwave beans as directed on package.
Add mushrooms and onion to reserved 1/4 cup drippings in skillet.
Cook and stir on medium heat.
Add bacon, hot cooked green beans and pepper; mix lightly.
Spoon into 2-quart serving dish.
Microwave cheese as directed.
Pour over beans.
Sprinkle with reserved bacon.

title: frozen peanut butter pie
directions: In a large bowl, whip the cream cheese until soft and fluffy. Add sugar and peanut butter. Slowly add milk, then fold in Cool Whip.
Pour into pie shell. Drizzle chocolate over top. Cut across the lines with a sharp knife to make a grid. Freeze until firm, several hours or overnight.
Remove from freezer about 30 minutes before you are ready to serve.

title: make ahead mexican layered casserole
directions: Brown meat with onion, chili powder, cumin, garlic powder, salt and pepper.
Drain fat.
Layer in extra large Pyrex baking dish:

first layer, half of meat mixture; second layer, 6 corn tortillas; third layer, second half of meat mixed with the canned beans; fourth layer, Monterey Jack cheese; fifth layer, Ro-Tel tomatoes; sixth layer, grated Cheddar cheese and seventh layer, cream of chicken or mushroom soup.
Cover and refrigerate 24 hours.
Uncover and bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: cherry nut bread
directions: Sift together flour, sugar and baking powder.
Cut in shortening; stir in eggs, orange juice, orange peel and cherry juice.
Fold in cherries and nuts.
Pour into greased loaf pan. Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes or until done.

title: meat and potato pie
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Lightly mix hamburger, 1 1/3 cups dry Potato Buds or flakes, egg, salt, pepper, onion, catsup and milk. Spread in 9-inch pie pan.
Bake 35 to 40 minutes.

title: spinach and rice casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Defrost spinach.
Saute onions and mushrooms in oil.
Combine with flour, cottage cheese, egg whites, egg substitute, uncooked spinach, cooked rice and seasonings.
Pat into a shallow 9 x 12-inch baking dish and top with sesame seed and Parmesan cheese.
Bake for 40 to 50 minutes until bubbling hot.
Makes 8 servings.

title: steamed chinese broccoli
directions: Rinse broccoli.
Peel tough outer stalks, pulling up from ends of stalks.
Slice diagonally into bite-size pieces.
Steam about 5 minutes or until barely tender.
Heat the oil and soy sauce.
Toss in broccoli.
Heat 1 to 2 minutes longer.
Place in serving dish. Sprinkle with toasted sesame seed and red pepper slices and serve. Makes 4 servings.

title: irene's hot borscht(servings: 8)
directions: Peel beets; add to water in a large pot and bring to a boil. Cook until done, about 45 minutes. Add salt. Remove beets from water and set aside to cool. Peel potatoes and cut into 1/8's. Add to beet water. Cook until almost done.

title: tortillos
directions: Measure flour by dip-level-pour method or by sifting.
Combine ingredients in bowl.
Beat with rotary beater until smooth.
Spoon three tablespoons batter into a medium-hot ungreased griddle to make a very thin 6-inch pancake.
Turn tortillos when edges begin to look dry, not brown.
Bake other side; keep warm in covered pan. Makes 12 tortillos.

title: strawberry mold
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in boiling water; add still frozen strawberries and pineapple.
Put 1/2 in ring mold; let set and spread sour cream over.
Add remaining Jell-O mixture and refrigerate.
Or chill all of mixture until jelly like; whip sour cream about 5 minutes and fold into mixture.

title: grapelets
directions: Let 1 cup puree and Knox gelatine soak for 30 minutes.
In large kettle, add remaining ingredients.
Boil until thick. While it boils, use a wooden spoon to skim foam.
Add 1 teaspoon vanilla and 3/4 cup chopped nuts.
Put in buttered 8-inch square pan.
Let stand overnight.
Cut in little squares and roll in powdered sugar.

title: asparagus casserole
directions: Thin
cream
of
chicken or mushroom soup with water or juice from
canned
asparagus.
Using 9 x 9-inch baking dish, layer Ritz
crackers, asparagus, sliced eggs, soup and cheese slices, ending
with
crackers.
Top
with	butter.
Bake
30 minutes at 350° (watch closely to prevent burning).

title: mayonnaise cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together; pour into a greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for approximately 1 hour, or until toothpick inserted comes out clean.
Let cool; frost with cream cheese or sour cream icing.

title: super cheeseburger pie
directions: Heat oven to 425°.
Prepare pie crust in quiche dish or pie pan.
Bake 15 minutes.
Cook and stir beef, onion and garlic until brown; drain.
Sprinkle with salt and flour.
Stir in pickle liquid, milk, pickles and 1 cup cheese.
Bake 15 minutes; sprinkle with 1 cup cheese.
Bake until crust is golden brown, about 5 minutes longer.

title: cream cheese frosting
directions: Mix together cream cheese, butter and vanilla in mixing bowl, slowly adding confectioners sugar.

title: scottish shortbread
directions: Soften butter to room temperature.
Combine butter, sugar and flour.
Mix with hands until ball forms.
Divide dough in half. Place in two 9 inch pie tins.
Pat down firmly.
Press around edges with fork and prick all over with fork.
Bake at 325° about 45 to 50 minutes, until golden brown.
While still warm, score through into pie shaped wedges.
When completely cool,
gently cut through original cuts and carefully remove from plate.
Delicious alone or served with tea or coffee.
Good with fruit or ice cream.

title: heavenly chocolate ice cream
directions: Combine
candy
and sweetened condensed milk in a large saucepan.
Cook
over
low
heat,
stirring
constantly, until candy
melts;
cool.
Stirring occasionally, add about 1 quart milk
to candy mixture; beat until well blended.
Pour mixture into freezer; can stir in chocolate syrup.
Add enough milk to fill container.
Freeze until firm.

title: zita chicken
directions: Cook zita according to directions.
Cut chicken to bite size and cook until done.
Heat Ragu.
Serve zita noodles and chicken; cover with Ragu.

title: easy coconut pie
directions: Mix together, fold in 1 large tub Cool Whip.
Pour into cooled, baked pie shell.
Sprinkle with coconut.
Chill.

title: marinated chicken breasts
directions: Cut off the fat and clean chicken breasts.
Put them in a rectangular food container.
Pour the chicken broth and the Viva Italian dressing over the chicken.
Store in refrigerator overnight.
Cook on low for 5 to 10 minutes on grill until done.

title: baked squash from the black-eyed pea
directions: Cut off tips of squash. Cut squash into 3 or 4 pieces.
Place in pot and add water to just cover squash. Cook until tender. Drain in colander.
Mash and add other ingredients.
Pour mixture into ovenproof dish and cover with a light layer of bread crumbs. Bake at 350° until lightly browned.
Makes 10 servings.

title: "first prize" tea cakes
directions: Cream sugar, margarine, oil and eggs together.
Add all other ingredients and mix well.
Drop dough by teaspoon onto cookie sheet and bake at 325° for 15 minutes.
Makes 3 dozen.

title: chocolate munchies
directions: Melt chocolate and butterscotch bits over double boiler.
Stir in other ingredients.
Drop by spoon onto wax paper or cookie sheets.
Chill.

title: no bake cookies
directions: Cook sugar, cocoa, butter and milk.
Bring to boil for 2 minutes.
Then add vanilla, peanut butter and quick oats.

title: cornish hens with apple stuffing
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Rinse the Cornish hens and open each cavity for the stuffing.
Combine the rest of the ingredients in a bowl.
Toss to mix.
Fill hen cavity with the stuffing.
Place hens breast side up in a shallow pan and roast 40 to 50 minutes or until tender.
Makes 4 servings.
One serving = 189 calories. Contains 22 g.
protein, 24 g. carbohydrates, 7 g. fat, 199 mg. sodium.
One serving = 3 low-fat protein, 1 starch, 1 bread and 1/2 fruit.

title: banana smoothie
directions: Combine all ingredients in an electric blender.
Process until smooth.
Serve immediately.
Yields 2 cups.
Contains 116 calories and 0.3 g fat per 2/3 cup serving.

title: tom's chili
directions: Brown meat; drain.
Add onions and green peppers.
Cook until tender-crisp.
Add all other ingredients. Simmer for 1 hour. Serve over rice.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix and roll in nuts.

title: ice cream cake
directions: Melt butter in a 9 x 13-inch dish.
Add Oreos.
Spoon in softened ice cream on top of cookies. Chill.
Then add a layer of fudge frosting.
Chill.
Top with Cool Whip. Keep in freezer.
It is important to chill between layers.

title: sauerkraut salad
directions: Press sauerkraut almost dry.
Combine remaining ingredients and chill 24 hours.
Can substitute other chopped raw vegetables. Combine oil, sugar and vinegar to suit your taste.

title: fruit pizza pie
directions: Press slices of cookie dough evenly into pizza pan.
Bake at 375° for 8-12 minutes.
Cool.
Mix cream cheese, sugar and vanilla.
Spread over cooled cookie cake.
Decorate with assorted fruit.
Refrigerate.
When ready to serve, if you wish, you can sprinkle dessert
with marmalade mixed with 1 tablespoon of water.

title: orange cookies
directions: Grate rind of orange in batter and dissolve soda in buttermilk.
Mix into other ingredients.
Bake at 375° for 12 to 15 minutes.
These are cake cookies.

title: snickerdoodles cookies
directions: Beat sugars and butter until fluffy; add eggs and mix well. Blend together dry ingredients; add to fluffy mixture and mix well.
Drop onto greased cookie sheet.
Combine 1 tablespoon sugar and 1 teaspoon cinnamon in small bowl; sprinkle lightly on every cookie before baking.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Cool for 7 minutes.

title: grandma's texas bean bake
directions: Brown bacon; drain fat.
Add ground beef and brown.
Add onions and cook until brown.
Add garlic, mustard and vinegar. Simmer 20 minutes, then add beans and mix.
Pour into 2-quart casserole and bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: lemon crisp cut-outs(christmas cookies)
directions: In a large bowl, cream butter; gradually add sugar and beat until light and fluffy.
Add egg, cream, lemon rind and vanilla; beat thoroughly.
Sift together flour, baking powder and salt. Gradually add to creamed mixture.
On lightly floured surface, roll out to 1/8-inch thickness.
Cut into desired shapes with floured cookie cutters.
Place on cookie sheets.
Bake at 350° for 7 to 9 minutes or until lightly browned.
Remove to wire rack to cool. Decorate as desired.
Makes 8 dozen.

title: cranberry-cherry punch
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water in a large bowl. Add lemonade concentrate; stir until dissolved. Stir in 3 cups water and remaining ingredients. Serve over ice. Yield: 3 quarts.

title: cheese cake cupcakes
directions: Combine sugar and softened cream cheese.
Add beaten eggs and vanilla flavoring.
Beat with mixer until fluffy.
Place a paper holder in muffin tin.
Place a vanilla wafer in each cup.
Spoon 3 tablespoons of mixture in each section.
Bake for 12 to 15 minutes at 375°.
Cool the cupcakes and add any fruit pie filling. Everyone loves these.

title: no bake cheese cake
directions: With electric mixer, mix softened cream cheese and condensed milk until smooth.
Add the lemon juice and mix.
Pour into graham cracker crust and chill.
Top with blueberries, cranberries or strawberries if desired.

title: apple cinnamon oat bran muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Spray muffin pan or use paper baking cups.
Mix oat bran, brown sugar, cinnamon, baking powder and raisins in a large bowl.
In another bowl, mix skim milk, apple juice concentrate, egg whites and oil.
Add to dry mixture and mix.
Fold in chopped apple.
Fill cups with batter.
Bake 17 minutes.
Makes 12 muffins.

title: peppermint pie
directions: Heat milk and marshmallows (halved) and a little salt.
Let melt, then cool.
Crush cookies and add enough melted margarine to hold cookies together.
Press or pat cookies to form a crust into the pie plate.
Add a few drops of food coloring to milk and marshmallows, then peppermint extract, taste and add more, if desired.
Add the whipped cream and pour into pie crust slowly. Return to refrigerator until set.
Serve with whipped cream on top or evenly spread whipped cream over the whole top.

title: pinto bean stew
directions: Cook pinto beans with ham bone and hot pepper sauce until tender, approximately 1 to 1 1/2 hours. Heat bacon fat in large skillet. Cook onion and garlic until golden. Add all remaining ingredients. Cover and cook about 40 minutes, stirring frequently. Combine tomato mixture with beans. Simmer, covered, over low heat another 15 minutes. Remove ham bone before serving. Makes 6 to 9 servings.

title: lemon meringue pie
directions: Mix dry ingredients together; add water.
Follow with beaten egg yolks, lemon juice and grated lemon peel.
Cook over boiling water, stirring until thick.
Cool and add to baked pie crust.

title: peanut clusters
directions: Melt almond bark and chocolate chips until smooth.
Add peanuts and mix.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto wax paper.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Mix together and bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until done.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Mix sugar, eggs and oil together.
Add rest of ingredients. Blend in loaf pan for 1 hour at 350°.
Makes 1 loaf.

title: applesauce squash medley
directions: Combine applesauce, squash, brown sugar, nutmeg, salt, butter, eggs and milk.
Mix well.
Pour into buttered baking dish. Sprinkle with nuts and bread crumbs.
Bake at 375° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Serve hot.

title: grandma fullers mac and cheese
directions: Pour hot milk over soft bread crumbs and cheese.
Cover until cheese melts, then add macaroni, beaten egg yolks, parsley, salt, onions and melted butter.
Beat egg whites until stiff but not dry.
Fold into mixture.
Pour into well-greased casserole and bake in a preheated 350° oven for 35 to 45 minutes (must be eaten immediately or it will fall).
Good dish for the Fridays of Lent.

title: rhubarb cake
directions: Mix cake according to directions.
Put in 9 x 13-inch greased pan.
Mix rhubarb and sugar and place on top of cake batter.
Pour 1 pint unwhipped cream over top.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until done.

title: low-fat cheesecake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Combine cracker crumbs, sugar and margarine; mix well.
Pat crumbs mixture into the bottom of a 9 or 10-inch pan and set aside.

title: chicken broccoli divan
directions: Arrange broccoli with flowers
toward the sides of an 8 x 11-inch Pyrex
dish.
Combine
soup, mayonnaise, lemon juice and curry powder.
Top
broccoli
with
the chicken, then soup mixture, then cheese.
Bake
at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: uncooked pasta sauce
directions: Dice tomatoes as small as possible.
In bowl, put tomatoes, then add all ingredients and toss well.
Let it marinade at least 2 hours at room temperature.
If it has been chilled, remove at least 2 hours before using.
Mix with cooked pasta.

title: toasted cereal snacks
directions: Heat oven to 250°.
Mix cereals, pretzels and nuts in baking dish, 13 x 9 x 2-inch.
Blend butter and seasonings.
Pour over cereal mixture.
Bake 30 minutes, stirring gently after 15 minutes. Makes about 8 cups.

title: orange cookies
directions: Cream sugar and shortening.
Add eggs and then add orange rind, orange juice and milk to the creamed mixture.
Mix in dry ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Cool and ice with powdered sugar icing.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Mix mayonnaise, vinegar, raisins, onions and broccoli.
Let it set overnight.
Next day, when ready to serve, fry bacon and crumble in salad.

title: ranch baked beans
directions: *Must be this brand.

title: hush puppies
directions: Make into balls and deep fry until golden brown.

title: potato and ham casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Mix potatoes as directed on the package.
In a 2-quart ovenproof dish, mix together ham, peas, onion, green pepper and celery.
Stir in potato mixture. Sprinkle cheese on top.
Bake 30 minutes.
Serve hot.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: kluski po pulski
directions: Saute onion in butter in large fry pan and add Kielbasa. When heated or lightly browned, add cabbage and seasonings.
Cover until cabbage is cooked through.
Add noodles and sour cream. Heat and serve.

title: spaghetti beef casserole
directions: Cook noodles with garlic salt as directed; drain.
Brown beef; drain, leaving some drippings to saute celery, onions and green pepper until tender.
(Add some butter as needed.)
Mix all ingredients in a large bowl.
Place in casserole dish and cover with grated cheese.
Bake at 325° for one hour.

title: corn chowder(lo-fat)
directions: In a 4-quart pot, over medium-high heat, bring stock, water, potatoes, onion, garlic, basil, pepper and thyme to a boil. Cook 10 minutes or until potatoes are tender.
Let cool a few minutes, then
ladle half the vegetables and about 2 cups of the liquid into a blender.
Add 1 cup corn.
Process 30 seconds or until coarsely pureed.
Return to saucepan. Stir in zucchini and remaining 2 cups corn. Cook over medium heat 8 minutes or until zucchini is tender.
Stir in milk and heat briefly.
Makes 8 servings.

title: green bean salad
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients.
Mix together the next 4 ingredients and add to bean mixture.
Cover and chill overnight if possible.

title: bread and butter pickles
directions: Cover the onions, cucumbers and peppers with boiling water and 1 cup table salt.
Soak 3 hours or overnight.
Strain and heat in weak vinegar water (enough water to cover and 1/2 cup vinegar) until they turn color.
Strain.

title: baked chicken with wild rice
directions: In greased 9 x	13-inch
pan, mix rice, water, mushroom and onion soup together.
Layer
chicken
in
rice mixture and sprinkle seasoning on top.	Bake 1 1/2 hours in 350° oven.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Blend cream cheese and mayonnaise until creamy.
Add celery, onions and shrimp.
Garnish with your favorite vegetables, crackers or chips.

title: reuben roll-ups
directions: Unroll crescent roll dough; separate into 8 triangles.
Snip drained sauerkraut in can to cut up long strands; combine with salad dressing.
Place 1 slice of corned beef across wide end of each triangle.
Spread 2 tablespoons of sauerkraut on beef; top with 2 strips of cheese.
Beginning at the wide end, roll up each triangle.
Bake on ungreased baking sheet at 375° for 10 to 15 minutes or until golden brown.

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix flour with sugar.
Stir in remaining ingredients and pour in buttered dish.
Place dish in pan of water and bake at 350° for 45 minutes. Yields 4 servings.

title: lasagne florentine for microwave
directions: Combine spaghetti sauce, tomatoes with liquid and water in bowl.
Stir to blend and break up the tomatoes; set aside. Combine Ricotta cheese, 1/2 cup Mozzarella, egg and garlic powder in bowl; mix well.
Spread 1/3 spaghetti sauce mixture in bottom of microwave-safe baking dish (about 12 x 8 x 2-inch).
Place 3 noodles on top of sauce.
Spread half Ricotta mixture over noodles.
Layer with half of the spinach and 1 cup Mozzarella. Repeat layers (sauce, noodles, Ricotta, spinach and Mozzarella). Cover with the remaining noodles; pour on remaining sauce mixture.

title: shrimp ring
directions: Combine soup and cheese and cook on simmer until cheese melts, stirring constantly.
Pour this mixture while hot over gelatine which has been dissolved in cold water.
Add mayonnaise.
Grind together celery, cucumber, green pepper and onion.
Add to mixture with shrimp.
Pour into mold and let chill.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: hearty kidney bean stew(heart healthy)
directions: In blender container, puree 1 cup beans with 1 cup vegetable broth until smooth.
Set aside.
In large saucepan, heat water and saute onion and garlic until softened.
Mix seasonings, except parsley and stir.
Add bean puree and simmer, covered, for 10 minutes.
Add potatoes and carrots; cook for 5 minutes.
Add reserve beans and cook for an additional 5 minutes.
Add reserved beans and cook for an additional 5 minutes.
Sprinkle with parsley and serve.
Makes 4 servings.

title: citrus punch
directions: Mix and pour over ice in punch bowl.
Makes 24 servings.

title: hot pineapple salad
directions: Mix sugar, flour, cheese and pineapple.
Place in oblong dish. Crush Ritz crackers to cover.
Drizzle melted oleo over cracker crumbs.
Bake 20 to 30 minutes at 325°.
Serve warm.

title: chicken parmigiana
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Drop chicken into egg and then bread crumbs, coating thoroughly.
In medium skillet, heat olive oil. Cook chicken in oil until done and well browned.

title: shanghai fried rice(philippine shanghai style fried rice)
directions: In a 10 or 12-inch frying pan, fry garlic and shallots in oil. Add sausages, pork and shrimp.
Season with soy sauce and parsley.
Add rice.
Continue frying and turning for 5 to 10 minutes to blend all ingredients.
When done, garnish with scallions.
Serves 8.

title: creamy chive and garlic mashed potatoes
directions: Place potatoes in a large saucepan and cover with water; add 1 teaspoon salt.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat; cover and cook for 25 to 30 minutes or until tender.
Drain.

title: layered crab and cream cheese dip
directions: Cream together the cheese, lemon juice, mayonnaise, Worcestershire sauce and green onion.
Chill.
Shape into a patty. Mix together cocktail sauce, horseradish and Tabasco.
Pour this mixture over the patty.
Spread over this the crabmeat.
Press down on top of cheese and sauce.
Sprinkle with chopped parsley.

title: rice souffle
directions: Separate eggs; beat egg whites until they form stiff peaks. In another bowl combine egg yolks, cold rice, milk and cheese. Gently fold in egg whites.
Butter baking dish; gently spoon in mixture.
Bake at 300° for 30 to 40 minutes or until top is golden brown.

title: chicken salad
directions: Mix drained chicken and mayonnaise until creamy.
Add celery, nuts and grapes.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Chill before serving.
Served best with croissants.

title: beth's oatmeal cookies
directions: Cream together butter and sugars.
Beat in eggs.
Add vanilla. Sift together flour, soda and spices.
Add to creamed mixture and stir in oats.
Cover dough and let set at room temperature for 2 hours.
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes.

title: simply delicious chicken casserole
