directions: Boil the chicken. Cut into bite sized pieces. Combine all ingredients (EXCEPT THE CHIPS) in a large bowl and mix well. Once the mixture is stirred, thoroughly, crush the chips and add to casserole mixture. Pour into a 9 x 13 baking dish and bake for 60 minutes at 300 degrees.

title: pineapple-garlic pork chops
directions: Combine all ingredients except chops.
Mix well.
Pour over chops and marinate overnight.
Remove from marinade and broil 4 to 5 minutes each side.

title: chocolate icing
directions: Beat egg whites until stiff but not dry.
Cook sugar, Karo and water with margarine until it forms a soft ball when dropped in cold water.
Pour slowly over beaten egg whites.
Add melted chocolate and vanilla.
Beat until thick enough to spread.

title: ortega cheese roll
directions: Cut Velveeta (dental floss works really well for this) in half lengthwise.
Roll out to 1/4-inch thickness.
Spread with cream cheese and green chilies.
Roll up; refrigerate.
Serve with wheat thins.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook vegetables 10 to 15 minutes.
Add soup and sour cream. Melt butter in casserole dish with 1/2 of dressing.
Add vegetables and soup mixture.
Cover top with remaining dressing. Bake at 300° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: nanny's traditional soup
directions: In large pan, stir together soups, then broth and milk.
Add cornstarch mixed with water.
Heat, stirring constantly, until slightly thickened.
Place about 2 tablespoons cheese in bottom of each bowl before adding soup.
This is a great snack for special holidays.

title: coconut cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs.
Sift flour, soda and salt; add gradually.
Add sour cream, vanilla and extract.
Pour into Bundt pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Drizzle a glaze while warm.

title: salmon dip
directions: On two pizza pans, layer in this order:

title: homemade dumplings
directions: Put Crisco in bowl; add hot broth and stir until Crisco is melted.
Then add flour.
Make a ball and roll out and cut in strips.
Add to boiling broth.
One can cream of chicken soup makes it better.

title: clam chowder
directions: In large soup pot; cook onion in butter with garlic, cayenne, and bacon until onion is tender.
Pour in the rest of the ingredients.
Bring to a boil, reduce heat and simmer for 20 minutes or until carrots are tender.
Stir occasionally.

title: sausage and mushroom quiche
directions: Crumble sausage in large skillet.
Add mushrooms.
Cook over high
heat
about
15 minutes, stirring frequently, until meat and mushrooms
are lightly browned and liquid from mushrooms has evaporated.
Drain off excess grease.
Add parsley. Beat eggs with cream and cheese.
Blend into mushroom mixture; stir
in salt. Pour mixture into pastry.
Bake at 400° for 25 to
minutes, until well browned.
Let stand for 10 minutes before serving.

title: mexican squash
directions: Cook squash until barely tender.
Drain well.
In a 2-quart glass casserole, layer squash, tomato, onion and chilies.
Drizzle with butter.
Toss together remaining ingredients.
Sprinkle over vegetables.
Bake in a 375° oven for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: hamburger pie
directions: Lightly brown beef and onion.
Season.
Cook until tender. Add beans and soup.
Pour into greased casserole.
Top with mounds of mashed potatoes and sprinkle with grated cheese.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes at 350°.

title: vi's pork sausage casserole
directions: Brown sausage and drain.
Put croutons in bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cover with cheese and then sausage.
Beat eggs. Add milk, mustard and soup.
Pour over mix in pan.
Refrigerate overnight.
Cover to refrigerate, uncover to bake.
Bake for 1 1/4 hours at 300°.

title: perch florentine
directions: Thaw and skin the fillets.
Cook the spinach according to package directions and drain thoroughly.
Blend the flour, salt, pepper and nutmeg into fat in a saucepan.
Add milk gradually and cook until thick and smooth, stirring constantly.
Add the cheese and Worcestershire sauce and stir until blended.
Arrange half the fillets in casserole dish and layer spinach and cheese mixture. Repeat until all is completed.
Bake in oven at 350° for 1 hour.

title: gladys starr's chocolate frosting
directions: Mix sugar, cocoa, milk, syrup and salt together.
Cook on medium heat until it forms a soft ball when dropped in cold water. Remove from heat.
Add margarine and vanilla.
Beat until cool.

title: strawberry jam
directions: Mix strawberries and Sure-Jell together with electric mixer on slow speed until well mixed; let stand for 20 minutes.
Add syrup and sugar to strawberry mixture.
Stir with a spoon until sugar is dissolved.
Place in containers; store in freezer.
Allow to set about 2 weeks before using.
This jam is good on toast or biscuits and makes a delicious topping for ice cream.
Yields about 10 (8 ounce) containers.

title: zucchini bake
directions: Mix all ingredients except the butter.
Put into greased casserole dish.
Melt butter and pour over top.
Bake 30 to 40 minutes at 350°.

title: hot spiced cider
directions: Combine ingredients in large saucepan. Bring to boil, stirring. Simmer 20 minutes. Let cool. Strain. Serve with a wedge or 1/4 slice of orange. Makes 1/2 gallon.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Beat butter, sugar, corn syrup, lemon juice and eggs on medium until creamy.
Gradually add flour and salt.
Beat until well mixed.
Cover and chill about 20 minutes.

title: cheesecake
directions: Mix together; add a little milk and pour over a graham cracker crust.

title: sweet potato pone
directions: Grate the raw potatoes, then the lemon and orange rinds.
Beat eggs and sugar. Add potatoes, spices, molasses, milk and butter. Put mixture into
buttered baking dish and bake slowly for 1 hour. Serve hot with meat course or cold, cut in slices.

title: giant popovers
directions: Beat eggs, milk and butter with a whisk.
Add flour and salt. Beat until light, not foamy.
Let batter stand for 5 minutes. Heat muffin pan, coated with cooking spray, in a 400° oven for 3 minutes or until very hot.
Spoon 1/2 cup batter into each cup of pan or fill area 1/2 full.
Bake for 55 minutes.
Cut a 1 1/2-inch split in the top of each popover and bake 5 additional minutes. Serve immediately.

title: bacon cheese dip
directions: Cook bacon until crisp and crumble.
In a mixer with paddle attachment, beat cream cheese until softened.
Slowly add buttermilk to cream cheese.
Continue to beat until smooth; add salt, garlic powder, Tabasco, Worcestershire sauce and bacon.
Mix well.

title: oriental green beans
directions: Saute onion in butter and add salt and pepper to taste.
Mix ingredients.
Reserve some onion rings for top.
Bake in greased 9 x 13-inch dish 30 to 35 minutes at 350°.

title: casserole delight
directions: The day before or at least 4 hours before preparing casserole, combine cream cheese, sour cream and onions.
Refrigerate.
Brown the ground beef.
Add garlic salt, salt, pepper, sugar and tomato sauce.
Simmer for 15 minutes.
Cook the noodles.

title: herbed rice pilaf
directions: In large skillet, cook the rice, celery and onion in butter; stir constantly until rice browned.
Stir in remaining ingredients; bring to a boil.
Reduce heat; cover and simmer for 15 minutes.
Remove from heat and let stand.
Cover for 10 minutes.

title: crescent delight
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Spray 9 x 13-inch pan with Pam.
Spread 1 can rolls on bottom of pan.
Mix cream cheese, egg yolk, sugar and vanilla.
Spread over rolls.
Spread second can of rolls on top.
Whip egg whites.
Spread over top and sprinkle with cinnamon and sugar.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Let cool.
Can be glazed with powdered sugar and milk.
Very good without glaze.

title: easy homemade ice cream with oreo cookies
directions: In large bowl, beat egg yolks; stir in milk, water and vanilla.
Fold in cookies and whipping cream.
Pour into aluminum foil-lined 9 x 5-inch loaf pan or other 2-quart container.
Cover; freeze 6 hours or until firm.
Scoop ice cream from pan or peel off foil and slice.
Return leftovers to freezer.

title: marinated carrots
directions: Mix all ingredients together and marinate overnight.

title: applesauce cake
directions: Cream butter, sugar and eggs together until fluffy.
Sift dry ingredients.
Add raisins and nuts.
Add alternately with applesauce to the butter and sugar mixture.
Mix thoroughly and turn into well-buttered pan and bake.

title: miniature pizza(party food or appetizer)
directions: Combine flour, softened cream cheese and oleo.
Make into small balls and press into bottom and up sides of tiny muffin tins.
Bake until very light brown at 400°.
Remove from pans and cool.

title: all-season shortcake
directions: Cut a piece of waxed paper to fit the bottom of a 9-inch square baking pan.
Lightly oil pan sides and paper.
Preheat oven to 350°.
With a mixer, beat together egg whites, sugar, orange peel and vanilla until light and fluffy.
In a small saucepan, heat the milk and margarine until hot, then stir into the egg mixture.
In a bowl, stir together the flour, baking powder, salt and nutmeg.
Add to the batter and stir to blend well.
Pour batter into prepared pan.

title: beans with molasses, catsup and pork(makes 12 servings)
directions: Place beans in a large bowl or pot.
Cover with cold water and soak overnight.
Drain beans.

title: cream cheese pie without a crust
directions: Combine cream cheese and butter.
Add sweetener.
Add egg and beat well.
Add vanilla and lemon juice.
Whip the cream and fold into mixture.
Pour into 6 single-serving custard cups.
Chill at least 6 hours.
It can be frozen.
Serve with fresh strawberries.

title: four-layer chocolate pie
directions: Mix the melted oleo, flour and nuts together.
Press firmly into a 9 x 13-inch Pyrex pan.
Bake at 350° until lightly browned, then cool completely.
Mix chocolate pudding with milk; cook until thickened.
Let cool completely.
Mix together cream cheese, powdered sugar and 1/2 of the Cool Whip.

title: turtle cookies
directions: Mix all together and drop by teaspoon on hot waffle iron set on medium heat.
Frost with favorite chocolate frosting.

title: taco dip
directions: Spread cream cheese on large platter.
Top with onion, pepper, tomatoes and Cheddar.
Pour taco sauce over top.
Serve with taco chips.

title: cowboy beans
directions: Place ground beef, onions and green pepper in a skillet.
Cook until done and drain.
Combine all beans, undrained, with barbecue sauce and add to ground beef mixture.
Cook over medium heat for 1 hour or in a crockpot for 4 hours.
This freezes very well.

title: spaghetti and meat balls
directions: Place 3/4 cup chopped onion and 2 cloves garlic in oil in deep heavy pan and cook until tender (but not brown).
Drain off remaining oil and add rest of ingredients.
Simmer while making meat balls.
After sauce has simmered for 3 to 4 hours, remove bay leaf and serve with Romano cheese.

title: banana pudding
directions: With a mixer, combine cream cheese and condensed milk.
Add milk, pudding mix, vanilla and one-half of the Cool Whip.
Blend until thick.
In a 9 x 13 inch baking dish, layer half of the vanilla wafers, half of the bananas and half of the pudding mixture.
Repeat layers.
Top with remaining Cool Whip and chill until set.

title: fruited champagne punch
directions: Thaw all frozen juices.
Stir pineapple juice into concentrates and undiluted lemonade.
Add water; mix well.
Chill.
To serve, slowly pour champagne into juices in punch bowl.
Garnish with thin slices of fruit of your choice.
Makes 28 cups.

title: waldorf crown salad
directions: Dissolve the gelatin in the boiling water. Stir in the cold water.
Chill until thickened. Fold in the apples, celery and walnuts.
Pour into a 5-cup ring mold. Chill until firm. Unmold; surround with lettuce.

title: spinach & orzo pasta
directions: Cook orzo pasta.
In large bowl add chopped garlic, spinach; chopped, and cherry tomatoes cut in half.

title: potato pinwheel candy
directions: Boil potato until done.
While still hot, mash thoroughly. Add powdered sugar, small amounts at a time, until potato and powdered sugar mixture is at a rolled dough stage.
Roll out to 1/4-inch thickness.
Spread evenly with peanut butter and roll up. Chill 5 to 6 hours or overnight.
Slice into 1/4 or 1/2-inch pieces.
Serve cold.

title: beef stew
directions: Cut up vegetables and meat into bite size pieces.
Boil water and add Gravy Master and bouillon cubes.
Add vegetables.
Cook on medium heat for 1/2 hour.
Add meat an cook for another 1/2 hour.

title: baked beans
directions: Mix all ingredients in baking casserole.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes.

title: spiced tea
directions: Mix well and use 1 heaping teaspoon to 1 cup hot water. Increase to suit taste.

title: louisiana shrimp
directions: Heat oil in large skillet over medium heat.
Add shrimp, onion, pepper and celery.
Cook and stir until shrimp is pink. Add tomatoes, sauce, hot pepper sauce, thyme and garlic powder. Bring to boil.
Stir in rice.
Cover, remove from heat and let stand 5 minutes.
Fluff with fork.
Serves 4.

title: tuna dip
directions: Saute onions; add celery and bell pepper; add mushrooms and tuna.
Cover
and
simmer
for one hour.
Add chow chow to taste. Serve warm.

title: cheese triangles
directions: Beat eggs with electric mixer until fluffy. Add cream cheese, cottage cheese, Romano cheese and flour. Continue beating until well blended. Crumble Feta cheese with fork and combine with egg mixture.

title: chicken cacciatore
directions: Heat oil in a large nonstick skillet over medium-high heat. Add oregano and garlic and saut 30 seconds. Add tomatoes, onions, 2 tablespoons parsley and juice.
Cook 2 minutes or until heated.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Cream butter and sugars in large bowl.
Add eggs and beat in pumpkin.
Combine flour, pumpkin pie spice, baking powder and baking soda in small bowl.
Add to pumpkin mixture.
Mix until just blended.
Pour into 2 greased and floured loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 10 minutes.

title: banana bread
directions: Cream oleo and sugar.
Add egg, bananas and vanilla.
Beat in flour, salt, soda and baking powder.
Add nuts; beat well.
Bake in greased loaf pan at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: truly different cupcakes
directions: Melt chocolate and butter in a heavy pan.
Add butter flavoring and pecans and stir to coat pecans.
Remove from heat.

title: potato soup
directions: Boil potatoes, onions, celery, and carrots.
Drain. Mix all ingredients together.
Simmer on medium heat until it starts to boil. Turn heat down and simmer 2 minutes or until thick in texture.
Serve hot.

title: chicken-mushroom spaghetti salad with red grapes
directions: Break spaghetti into thirds and cook.
Drain and rinse with cold water.
Combine Miracle Whip, mustard, salt and sugar.
Stir into cooked spaghetti and remaining ingredients.
Cover and chill well or overnight.
Good summer salad.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Pound flour, salt and pepper into steak.
Cut into bite size pieces.
Brown with the onions in butter.
Add tomato paste and consomme and simmer 2 hours.
Add 1 can mushrooms and the sour cream before serving.
Serve on cooked rice or noodles.
Serves 4.

title: blueberry pancake syrup
directions: Combine blueberries, water, sugar and cornstarch.
Heat to boiling, stirring occasionally.
Stir in lemon juice.
Serve warm or chilled.
Makes about 1 3/4 cups.

title: saucy short ribs
directions: Trim excess fat from ribs.
Heat fat in Dutch oven.
Roll ribs in flour.
Brown in hot fat; spoon off fat.
Season.
Add water. Cover; simmer on top of range or slow in oven (325°) until tender, about 2 hours.
Add extra water if needed.
Put meat on warm platter.
Keep hot.
Make onion gravy.
Makes 6 servings.

title: coconut pie
directions: Beat eggs.
Add sugar, melted butter, salt, milk, vanilla and coconut.
Pour into pastry lined pie plate.
Bake at 350° for 25 or 30 minutes.

title: taco-mac salad
directions: Cook pasta according to package directions; drain well and cool.
Brown meat and drain fat.
Add taco seasoning.
Cool. Combine pasta, meat, green pepper, onion, cheese, tomatoes and seasonings in large bowl.
Chill.
Just before serving, stir in dressing and corn chips.
Can also add chopped lettuce if desired.

title: sausage cheese grits casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Coat 3-quart baking dish with cooking spray.
Bring water and salt to a boil in a large saucepan. Slowly stir in grits.
Cover, reduce heat and cook for 5 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Remove from heat.
Stir in cheese and margarine until melted.
Add egg substitute, milk and sausage; blend well.
Pour mixture into prepared dish.
Bake 1 hour or until set.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: dilly dip for raw vegetables
directions: Blend all
ingredients	together and chill before serving.

title: beef stew
directions: Brown meat in 2 tablespoons shortening.
Add 2 cups hot water and next 9 ingredients.
Cover and simmer for 1 1/2 hours.
Remove bay leaves and garlic.
Add vegetables; cover and cook 30 to 45 minutes.

title: chess pie
directions: Mix together and pour into unbaked pie crust.
Bake at 350°. Makes 2 deep dish pies.

title: hard times dessert
directions: Spread butter on saltine cracker and sprinkle sugar on butter. Place in mouth and enjoy!

title: pork chop casserole
directions: Combine rice, seasoning packet of rice mix and hot water; place in lightly greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Set aside. Sprinkle pork chops with pepper and place over rice mixture. Cover and bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Uncover casserole.
Combine soup and milk and pour over casserole.
Bake casserole uncovered 15 minutes or until thoroughly heated.
Yield:
6 servings.

title: baked green beans(green beans ferier)
directions: One hour before serving, cook green beans; drain and put in 1 1/2-quart casserole.
In a 2-quart saucepan, cook bacon and onions over medium heat until bacon is crispy and onions are soft.
Stir in flour.
Gradually add 1 1/2 cups water, bouillon and pepper. Cook to thicken, stirring constantly.
Gently mix in with the beans.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.
Makes 8 servings.

title: popcorn balls
directions: Combine sugar, corn syrup, water, salt and vinegar.
Cook slowly to hard-boil stage.
Remove from heat and add butter and vanilla.
Slowly pour over popped corn and mix well, stirring constantly.
Grease hands and form balls.

title: gelatin party salad
directions: Stir Jell-O in boiling water until dissolved.
Combine rest of ingredients.
Pour into greased salad mold or rectangular Pyrex dish.
Make 16 servings.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Place in greased 2-quart casserole dish. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Top with 2 cups of grated cheese. Bake for 5 more minutes.

title: oven stew
directions: Layer the ingredients in the order given, in an ovenproof Dutch oven with a lid, and bake for five (5) hours at 275°. Sprinkle top with salt and pepper.

title: black bottom cupcakes(great!)
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients.
Add chocolate chips and set aside.
In large bowl, mix remaining ingredients well.
Fill muffin tins, lined with cupcake papers, 1/3 to 1/2 full with this mixture.
Drop large spoonfuls of cheese mixture in center of each cup.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes at 350°.
Makes 20 to 24 cupcakes.

title: cheese cake
directions: Dissolve jello in hot water.
Cool.
Mix in sugar, cream cheese, vanilla, salt and whipped cream.
Add jello and cream cheese mixture.
Beat until smooth.

title: cheese secrets(biscuits)
directions: Mix yeast in 1/4 cup warm water. Add milk, butter, sugar and salt.
Mix in flour, 1 cup at a time.
(Let rise once its double size, about 15 minutes.)
Pull apart into 12 pieces. Tuck one cube of cheese in each piece and close.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes or until golden brown.

title: special pea salad
directions: Mix together the first 5 ingredients in a small bowl and chill.
In a large
bowl, combine the remaining ingredients.
Add chilled dressing. Toss lightly.

title: earthquake cake
directions: Grease 9 x 13-inch pan.

Put in 1 cup coconut and 1 cup nuts. Mix cake mix according to directions, pour over nuts and coconut. Melt butter, cream cheese, confectioners sugar and vanilla. Mix thoroughly and pour over top of cake.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes (baking time may vary according to your oven).

title: squash cakes
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Fry in hot oil, browning both sides.

title: skillet supper
directions: Combine onion, green peppers and ground beef in a 10-inch skillet.
Cook over medium heat until meat is brown.
Add tomatoes, salt, pepper and chili powder; stir to blend.
Cover; reduce heat and simmer for 10 minutes.
Add beans; combine until heated.
Garnish with corn chips.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: cheese spread
directions: Mix softened Velveeta cheese with softened cream cheese.
Add garlic.
Mix well.
Roll into several balls.
Roll the balls in chili powder so it covers.
Also, if desired, roll each ball in nuts (pecans).
Spread on crackers.

title: quick buttermilk rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm buttermilk.
Sift dry ingredients together and blend in shortening.
Add buttermilk and mix well. Knead for a short while on a floured board.
Place in a greased bowl.
Cover.
Let rise to double in bulk. Shape into rolls. Place in greased 9-inch pan.
Let rise to double in size.
Bake at 360° until brown.

title: macaroni casserole
directions: Brown beef, onion and green pepper.
Drain.
Cook macaroni. Drain.
Mix meat, macaroni and remaining ingredients in casserole dish.
Cover with cheese slices.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: chocolate angel cake
directions: Sift flour and measure; add cocoa and sift twice.
Beat egg whites and salt until foamy; add cream of tartar and continue beating until stiff and peaks form; add flavoring while beating. Fold in sugar a little at a time.
Fold in flour and cocoa mixture in the same way.
Pour batter into an ungreased tube pan.
Drop pan 3 to 4 times from a height of 6 inches to remove air pockets. Bake 40 minutes at 350°.
Remove from oven and invert pan onto a plate.
Remove cake when cold.

title: vegetable bars(pizza)
directions: Press crescent rolls in 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan or larger.
Bake according to directions.
Let cool.
Beat cream cheese, mayonnaise and dressing.
Spread on cooled rolls.
Press vegetables and cheese on top.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: sunshine salad
directions: Dissolve jello in water.
Stir in salad dressing; blend with mixer.
Let set in refrigerator until slightly thickened.
Add remaining ingredients.
Pour in mold.
Congeal.

title: chipper oatmeal cookies
directions: Cream
margarine,
Crisco,
brown sugar and white sugar until fluffy
and
light.
Blend	in
eggs
and vanilla.	Add combined dry ingredients.
Mix well.
Stir in oatmeal, chocolate bits and nuts.
Drop by rounded teaspoonful of dough onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes or until golden brown. Makes about 5 dozen.

title: chicken breasts in many mustards
directions: Set chicken breasts aside.
Mix all remaining ingredients in bowl with a whisk to emulsify.
Marinate chicken 2 to 4 hours in mustard mixture.
Grill or cook chicken.

title: chicken and rice dinner
directions: Grease a 9 x 13-inch oblong pan with vegetable oil.
Put uncooked rice, cream soups and water in pan.
Mix well.
Place chicken pieces on top of rice and soup mixture.
Cover pan with lid or foil.
Bake for 1 to 1 1/2 hours at 350°.

title: paradise cake
directions: Combine sugar, shortening and eggs until fluffy.
Sift flour, soda, baking powder and salt together 3 times.
Add to sugar mixture, blend well.
Add pineapple, vanilla, nuts and cherries, blending well.
Bake for 1 hour at 350° in an angel food pan.

title: raspberry pie
directions: Cool pie crust. In a small saucepan, combine water, sugar, salt and cornstarch. Bring to a boil. Simmer, stirring, until clear and thickened. Remove from heat. Stir in 1 tablespoon of butter and nutmeg. Chill. Then spread bottom and sides of pie crust with remaining tablespoon of butter. Fill pie crust with raspberries and pour syrup mixture you prepared over the berries. Chill until set. Serve with whipped cream.

title: finger jello
directions: Soften gelatin in cold water.
Dissolve jello in hot water. Add lemon juice and gelatin. Pour into dish and refrigerate.
Cut into cubes or shapes with cutters.

title: seafood casserole
directions: Make white sauce (blend 1/4 cup butter, flour and milk). Arrange a layer of sliced eggs in a buttered 8-inch square pan. Cover with some sauce, layer of shrimp, sauce, tuna, sauce, mushrooms, sauce, crabmeat and sauce.
Sprinkle sauce with cheese; cover with buttered crumbs.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: cinnamon pinwheels
directions: Cut margarine into flour pastry blender.
Stir in sour cream; cover and refrigerate at least 8 hours.
Mix 3 tablespoons sugar and cinnamon.
Divide dough into halves.
Roll 1/2 into rectangle, 20 x 7-inches, on sugared, well floured cloth-covered board. Sprinkle half of sugar cinnamon mixture on top of rolled dough. Roll up tightly, beginning at small end.
Roll other half of dough into rectangle, 20 x 7-inches, sprinkling with remaining sugar cinnamon mixture.
Place loose end of roll on 7-inch side of rectangle; pinch edges to seal.
Continue to roll up tightly.
Wrap and refrigerate at least 1 hour, but no longer than 48 hours.
Heat oven to 350°.
Cut roll into 1/4-inch slices.
Place about 2 inches apart on ungreased sheet.
Mix 3 tablespoons sugar and the water; brush over cookies and bake 20 to 25 minutes.

title: grandma lippert's cashew nut brittle
directions: In a large pot, cook sugar, syrup and water until completely dissolved.
Add butter and cook to the thread stage.
Stir constantly throughout cooking!
(Lift your spoon to see if the mixture threads down from spoon to pot, stirring constantly.)
At thread stage, add candy thermometer.
At soft ball stage (234°), add cashews.
Cook to soft crack stage (274°).
Remove from heat and quickly add baking soda; mix thoroughly.
Pour out into buttered pans and stretch thin.
Let cool and crack into pieces.

title: caramel biscuit ring-a-round
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Generously grease a 12-cup fluted tube pan.
In a small saucepan, combine all ingredients except for the biscuits.
Heat until margarine melts.
Separate biscuit dough into 20 biscuits.
Cut each biscuit into quarters and place them in a large bowl.
Pour sauce over biscuits and toss lightly.
Spoon biscuits into tube pan and bake in preheated oven for 20 to 30 minutes or until golden brown.
Let stand for 3 minutes.
Invert onto serving plate and serve warm.
Yields 10 servings.

title: chocolate thumbprint cookies
directions: Cream 1/2 cup butter, 2/3 cup sugar, egg yolk, 2 tablespoons milk and 1 teaspoon vanilla in bowl until light and fluffy.
Add mixture of flour, cocoa and salt; blend well.
Chill for 1 hour. Shape into 1-inch balls.
Dip into beaten egg white.
Coat with mixture of chopped nuts and 2 tablespoons sugar.
Place on lightly greased cookie sheet.
Make indentation in center of each.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes, or until set.

title: sweet potato souffle
directions: Scald milk with salt, sugar, butter and nutmeg. Add potatoes, nuts and raisins. Beat egg yolks.
Add to mixture.
Mix well. Fold in egg whites and pour in 1 1/2-quart casserole dish. Bake at 325° for 45 minutes until set. Top with marshmallows. Return to oven until marshmallows are melted and slightly brown.

title: cheddar cheese potato casserole
directions: Take shredded hash browns (thawed) and add sour cream, Cheddar cheese and the can of soup.
Saute onions in the butter and add to potato mixture.
Add milk and salt and pepper to taste.

title: salsa
directions: *Yellow and/or red peppers may be used; 3 medium, one of each, may be used.

title: coconut cheese drops
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Using teaspoon, shape into balls; place 1-inch apart on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 325° until golden, about 8 or 9 minutes.
Cool on racks.
Delicious when dipped in chocolate!

title: dill pickles
directions: Put into a large kettle and bring to boil.
Fill jars with cucumbers as desired and dill (may be dried or fresh).
Garlic or hot peppers may be added also as taste desires.
Pour boiling liquid over cucumbers.
Fill jars to neck and seal.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix together soup and 1/2 can milk.
Add broccoli, French fried onions, chicken, salt and cheese. Blend well. Spread in greased casserole (2 1/2 to 3-quart capacity). Heat in oven at 325° for 10 minutes.

title: vegetable pizza
directions: Spread crescent rolls in 9 x 13-inch or larger pan and bake as directed on package.
Set aside to cool.
Mix cream cheese, mayonnaise and Ranch dressing.
Spread on top of crescent rolls. Chop cauliflower, green onions, broccoli and tomatoes.
Toss together and spread on top of cream cheese mixture.
Sprinkle Cheddar cheese on top.
Let set overnight.

title: pralines(club member: brigitte magee)
directions: Mix and cook all together in iron skillet on medium heat. Stir constantly until it forms a soft ball. Remove from heat; pour in a glass bowl. Add a stick of Parkay margarine. Set in cold water and beat until real thick.
Drop on wax paper.

title: macaroni and tuna
directions: Mix first five ingredients together and put in baking dish. Lay cheese slice on top add crushed potato chips on top and Bake at 350 degrees for 30 minutes.

title: spicy broiled potatoes
directions: Scrub potatoes with soft brush. Cut lengthwise in half and then in quarters. Spread skin side down on baking sheet.
Drizzle with butter and sprinkle with seasonings. Broil 4 to 6-inches from heat until a fork glides in easily, 15 to 25 minutes, depending on thickness.

title: reese's peanut butter squares
directions: Mix crumbs and sugar.
Add melted margarine and peanut butter. Press in a large jelly roll pan (15 1/2 x 10 x 1-inch).
Melt chocolate and spread over mixture.
Cool.
Cut in squares.

title: breaded veal cutlets
directions: Beat egg with water.
Season cutlets with salt (half teaspoon), Old Bay and paprika.
Dip cutlets in egg and water mixture, then in bread crumbs and salt (half teaspoon).

title: cut it short torte
directions: Mix and bake in pound cake pan.
Cool and split cake into 3 layers.
Spread 1/3 of Cool Whip and 1/3 of pie filling between each layer and on top.

title: tuna cheese ball
directions: Squeeze out as much oil from the tuna as possible.
Blend tuna with cream cheese; add grated onion to taste.
Mix thoroughly. Shape into a ball with hands.
Refrigerate until served.
May be rolled in finely chopped fresh parsley or chopped nuts before refrigerating.
Serve with crackers.

title: homestyle frank and cheese dinner
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cook noodles according to package directions.
Meanwhile, in a medium skillet, melt butter and cook onion until tender.
Stir in flour, salt and mustard blended with milk and Worcestershire sauce.
Bring to the boiling point, then simmer, stirring constantly, until sauce is thickened, about 5 minutes.
Stir in 1 1/4 cups cheese until melted.

title: broccoli-cauliflower
directions: Mix vegetables, Cheez Whiz and seasoning.
Place into crock-pot.
Put croutons on top.
Cook on medium for several hours.

title: cowboy soup
directions: Brown ground beef and onion.
Add remaining ingredients and bring to a boil.
Simmer 1 1/2 hours.

title: applesauce cake
directions: Dissolve soda in coffee.
Mix applesauce with beaten margarine and sugar.
Sift flour, spices, salt, chopped raisins and nuts. Add soda with coffee and beaten eggs.
Mix well.
Bake 2 hours at 325°, maybe longer.

title: nutritious zucchini cookies
directions: Mix oleo, honey, zucchini and beaten egg.
Sift flour, soda, spices and salt.
Stir into creamed mixture.
Stir in oats, walnuts, dates and coconut.
Drop by teaspoon on oiled sheet. Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: sweet tater pie
directions: Combine all ingredients and place in unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 425° for 15 minutes, then reduce heat to 350° and cook additional 1 hour and 20 minutes.

title: pineapple cheese ball
directions: Mix together ingredients saving enough pecans to roll the ball in.

title: cheesy potato casserole
directions: Mix half package of cheese with soup, sour cream and potatoes. Pour into a casserole dish or a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Add milk to desired consistency.
Layer remaining cheese on top.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Bake at 375° covered for 45 minutes; uncovered 15 minutes longer.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: corn & broccoli casserole
directions: Parboil broccoli until almost tender.
Mix all together except the cracker crumbs and oleo.
Layer the crumbs and the vegetable mixture in a greased casserole.
Save 1 c. of crumbs.
End with vegetable mixture on top.
Dot top with the oleo.
Bake in a 350° oven for 30 - 40 minutes.
Put the reserved crumbs on top a few minutes before the casserole is finished cooking.

title: rice casserole
directions: Mix all together.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: cheesy vegetables
directions: Mix all ingredients; bake at 350° for 30 minutes with cover on, then 30 minutes uncovered.

title: sunday special corn bread
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Grease and heat a 9-inch baking pan or skillet.
Combine ingredients and pour into prepared pan.
Bake for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: dumplings
directions: Combine
flour and salt; cut in shortening.
Add enough milk to	make
a
stiff	dough.	Roll
very thin and cut into squares. Drop dumplings a few at the time into boiling broth. Sprinkle with
black pepper.
When broth boils over the dumplings,
add more
dumplings.
Repeat
until
all the dough is used.
Boil
10 to	15 minutes.
These are good in ham broth, potato
broth, chicken broth or neck bone broth or any kind of broth.
Just
boil something	and throw some dumplin's in the broth!

title: pudding pecan pie
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Stir pudding mix into corn syrup in medium bowl until well blended.
Stir in evaporated milk and egg.
Mix in pecans.
Pour into pastry shell.
Bake for about 45 minutes, or until top is firm and just begins to crack.
Cool at least 3 hours before cutting.
Garnish with whipped topping.
Store leftover pie in refrigerator.

title: orange salad
directions: Boil pear juice and dissolve Jell-O.
Add softened cream cheese and dissolve.
Add Cool Whip and chopped nuts.
Chill.

title: potato chip cookies
directions: Beat butter (room temperature) for a long time until light and fluffy.
Add sugar.
Beat well.
Add vanilla and flour gradually. Crush potato chips and add them last.
Drop by teaspoons onto Pam coated cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° until lightly brown.
Check, 3 to 6 minutes usually.
Store after completely cool.
Enjoy!

title: mississippi mud pie
directions: Crush cookies.
Save 1/2 cup.
Press on bottom of a 9 x 13-inch dish.
Melt margarine and pour over.
Cool 1/2 hour in refrigerator.
Mix cream cheese, sugar and Cool Whip.
Spread over cookies and refrigerate 1/2 hour.
Mix pudding and spread over mix.
Refrigerate 1/2 hour.
Cover with Cool Whip. Sprinkle cookies on top.

title: huntsville church cake
directions: Pour
the
boiling
water
over the raisins; boil for 5 minutes.
Put
in
a
large bowl.
Add the lard or shortening, sugar, water and baking soda.
Sift the flour, cinnamon, salt, cloves
and
nutmeg
together; dredge the nutmeats.
Bake in a dripping pan at 350° for 45 minutes.
Can be served with Lemon Sauce.

title: any day meat loaf
directions: Mix hamburger and egg; add salt and pepper.
Mix well.
Add onion, parsley flakes and milk.
Stir.
Add soup, then add remaining ingredients.
Mix well and put in greased loaf pan and bake at 375° for 1 hour.
Last 20 minutes, drain off excess fat and spread top of meat loaf with ketchup or barbecue sauce.

title: baked almond chicken
directions: Coat chicken pieces with flour.
Blend celery salt, paprika, salt, curry powder, oregano and pepper with butter, coating all sides.
Arrange chicken in single layer in a baking dish (9 x 13-inches).
Sprinkle evenly with almonds.
Pour light cream between pieces.
Bake, uncovered, in a moderate 350° oven for 45 minutes.
Uncover.
Spoon 1/2 cup sauce from pan into sour cream and mix together.
Pour evenly over chicken.
Sprinkle with bread crumbs.
Bake, uncovered, about 15 minutes longer or until chicken is tender.
Makes 6 servings.

title: green apple cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into a greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: julie's green beans
directions: Drain water from green beans and add fresh water.
Add a little oil or fatback to beans.
Add sugar, vinegar and salt to taste.
Cook until almost dry, stirring occasionally.
Very tasty!

title: millie's chicken
directions: Line pan with foil; arrange chicken.
Combine all ingredients. Pour over meat and marinate at least 1/2 hour.
Bake at 350° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.

title: transparent cake
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients and spread (mixture will be stiff) into a greased 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
This is your crust.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Cook water, sugar and cornstarch until thick.
Add Jell-O and strawberries.
Pour into cooled crust.
Let set.
Add Cool Whip on top.

title: angel flake biscuits
directions: Sift together dry ingredients in mixing bowl.
Cut in 3/4 cup shortening.
Add yeast dissolved in 1/2 cup lukewarm water.
Add 2 cups buttermilk.
Work together with large spoon until all flour is moistened.
Cover bowl and store in refrigerator.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Mix butter with sugars, vanilla, salt and eggs, then add peanut butter.
Sift flour in and mix well.
Roll into small balls and dip in the sugar.
Lay on pan and with a fork, press down slightly.
Make imprints on cookie.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 13 minutes according to different heat level or until done.

title: mrs. larsen's maple squares
directions: Mix and spread on greased shallow pan.
Press down.

title: fish creole
directions: In a medium-sized saucepan, bring broth, salt, pepper and basil to a boil over moderately high heat.
Add okra.
Reduce heat to moderate.
Cover and cook about 5 minutes until just tender and still bright green.
Add tomatoes and their juice, then arrange fish fillets on top.
Cover and cook about 3 to 5 minutes longer or until fillets are done.
Makes about 5 cups.

title: pink banana blizzard
directions: In electric blender, mix half of ingredients.
Blend 15 to 20 seconds until smooth.
Pour into chilled glass.
Repeat with remaining ingredients.

title: crispy rice treats
directions: Melt margarine in large saucepan over low heat.
Add marshmallow creme and stir until well combined.
Remove from heat. Add rice cereal.
Stir until well coated.
Using buttered spatula or waxed paper, press mixture evenly into 13x9x2-inch pan coated with cooking spray.
Cut into 2x2- inch squares when cool.

title: chicken dish
directions: Mix soup, sour cream and water chestnuts.
Pour over chicken breasts which have been wrapped with the bacon.
Bake at 350° for 2 hours.
Pour chicken mixture over cooked rice and serve.

title: diet herb chicken bake
directions: Sprinkle chicken with salt, pepper and garlic salt.
Place in shallow pan or casserole and sprinkle with the remaining ingredients.
Bake uncovered for 30 minutes in 325° oven.
Turn after 15 minutes.
Baste occasionally.
Turn skin side up.
Cover and bake 30 minutes longer or until tender.
Serves 3 to 4 people.

title: karmen's chicken casserole
directions: Mix chicken, soup, milk and 1/2 noodles.
Crush remaining noodles on top.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: holiday salad
directions: Melt red hots in boiling water.
Add gelatin and stir in applesauce.
Chill until firm in an 8-inch ring mold.
Unmold on plate.
Fill center hole with sour cream.
Yields 16 to 18 servings.

title: red snapper veracruz
directions: Mince the garlic and mash it with the salt, forming a paste. In a bowl, stir together well the garlic paste and the lime juice.
With a sharp fork, poke holes in each side of the snapper several times.
Put the snapper in a large, shallow dish and pour the lime juice mixture inside the cavity and over the snapper. Let the snapper marinate, covered and chilled for 2 hours, turning it once.

title: meat loaf
directions: Combine all ingredients thoroughly and pack firmly into a loaf pan.
Bake in oven at 375° approximately 40 to 45 minutes.

title: broccoli corn bread
directions: Mix everything but muffin mix well.
Add muffin mix and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Blend together with electric mixer.

title: speed-easy yeast rolls
directions: To sweet milk add egg and mix with yeast and sugar dissolved in warm water.
Cut shortening into flour.
Mix flour and liquid to form soft dough.
Knead gently on well floured board.
Form dough into small balls 3/4-inch in diameter.
Place 3 balls in each greased muffin cup.
Brush generously with melted butter. Cover with towel and allow to rise for 2 hours at room temperature until double in size.
Bake at 400° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: chicken dinner in the pot
directions: Place chicken breasts in a large, heavy ovenware pot (an enamel coated cast-iron pot is best).
Peel carrots; quarter lengthwise and cut into 2-inch lengths.
Cut ends off of green beans (or separate frozen beans), and place in the pot with onion and carrots.
Sprinkle contents of pot with parsley flakes. Season lightly with pepper. Pour sherry over all.
Cover tightly. Bake at 300° for 2 hours, or until vegetables are tender.
A good, one-pot dinner, and the kids like it, too.
Makes 2 to 3 servings. Doubles nicely.

title: mashed potato balls
directions: Mix mashed potatoes, minced onion and grated American cheese. Shape into balls; roll slightly in corn flake crumbs.
Bake on greased cookie sheet at 400° for 20 minutes.

title: world easiest piegroves, texas
directions: Crumble butterfingers and mix in Cool Whip.
Pour into pie crust.
Refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: hash brown potato casserole
directions: Shred potatoes, cheese and onions.
Melt butter.
Mix all ingredients and pour in casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes or until golden brown.

title: easy cocktail meatballs
directions: Mix ground meat, beaten egg and milk; make meatballs.
Heat grape jelly and barbecue sauce.
Pour over meatballs and simmer until done.

title: bunko chicken nuggets
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Mix together 1/2 cup mayo, milk and seasonings.
Lightly dip chicken into mayo mixture.
Coat well with crumbs.
Place on a greased cookie sheet.
Bake 18 to 20 minutes.
Mix remaining mayo with salsa.
Serve with nuggets on toothpicks.

title: southern burgers
directions: Brown beef and onion in a little hot fat.
Stir in ketchup, mustard and soup.
Simmer until mixture has thickened a little, about 15 minutes.
Spoon over toasted buns.
Makes 6 servings.

title: chioppino
directions: *Sea bass, grouper, etc. can be substituted or combined.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Layer ingredients as listed.
Tear bread into small chunks and place on top.
Cover with melted butter.
Bake at 350° until cheese melts and bread crumbs brown.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Beat eggs well.
Blend in oil, sugar, vanilla and zucchini. Add dry ingredients.
Bake in two greased pans at 375° for about 1 hour.

title: spaghetti slaw
directions: Cook spaghetti as directed.
Cool with cold water.
Combine with green onions, green peppers, cucumber, salt and cabbage. Combine mayonnaise and sugar and pour over the ingredients.
Chill overnight before serving.
Good use for leftover spaghetti.

title: creamed cabbage
directions: Chop cabbage. Cook in boiling water about 20 minutes. Drain; add flour, butter and milk. Stir until boiling. Add salt and pepper. Heat carefully and serve.

title: party mints
directions: Combine all ingredients in a large mixing bowl.
Beat at high speed of electric mixer until well blended; then knead until smooth.
Shape mints in rubber candy molds and place on baking sheets.
Cover with a paper towel and let stand overnight to harden.
Yield:
8 1/2 to 9 dozen mints.

title: toffee squares
directions: Melt butter.
Take off heat.
Add brown sugar and mix well until all are dissolved.
Add 1 cup flour.
Add eggs, then the other cup of flour.
Grease large cookie sheet, pat mixture evenly. Bake at 350° approximately 15 to 20 minutes (no more).
Be careful that it does not burn.
Crumble chocolate and spread on top of crust.
If not melted, turn heat off and put back in oven so chocolate will melt.
Sprinkle finely chopped nuts on top.
Cut in squares or diamond-shapes while warm.

title: texas brownies
directions: In bowl, combine flour and sugar.
In saucepan, combine butter, shortening, water and cocoa.
Stir and heat to boiling. Pour over flour and sugar.
Add buttermilk, eggs, baking soda and vanilla.
Mix on high speed in mixer.
Pour in 11 x 17-inch greased pan.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.
While baking, you can prepare the frosting.

title: lemon bread
directions: Grease a loaf pan.
Preheat oven to 350°.
In a large bowl combine flour ingredients.
Mix butter, milk, eggs, lemon peel and lemon extract until smooth.
Add this to flour mix.
Stir just until flour is moistened.
Pour into pan.
Bake 45 to 50 minutes or until a toothpick inserted in the center comes out clean.
Cool in pan 10 minutes.
Remove from pan and cool completely.
Makes 1 loaf.

title: cheese scones
directions: In a large bowl, combine flour, sugar, baking powder, salt and baking soda; stir in cheese.
In another bowl, combine egg, sour cream, oil and milk; stir into dry ingredients just until moistened.
Turn onto a floured surface and knead gently 10-12 times.
Gently pat out to 1/3 inch thickness. Cut with a 3 inch heart-shaped cookie cutter.
Place on a greased baking sheet. Bake at 425° for 15-20 minutes or until golden brown.

title: hamburger and vegetable soup
directions: Brown hamburger with onion.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix and simmer 5 hours in crock-pot or 2 hours on stove top.

title: chicken-broccoli stir-fry
directions: Place chicken in a medium saucepan, and cover with water. Bring to a boil; cover and reduce heat.
Simmer 15 minutes or until chicken is tender.
drain, reserving 1/2 cup both.
Bone chicken, and chop meat.
Combine cornstarch, gingerroot, and soy sauce; stir well.
Add the chicken; mix well, and let marinate in refrigerator 30 minutes.
Pour oil around top of a large skillet or wok, coating sides; allow to heat at medium-high (325°) for 2 minutes.
Add broccoli and reserved broth; cover and cook 2 minutes.
Reduce heat to medium (275°).
Stir in chicken and marinade.
Add onion, and stir-fry 1 minute.
Add mushrooms; stir-fry 1 to 2 minutes or until tender.
Serve over hot cooked rice or chow mein noodles.
Yield: 4 servings.

title: the 10-minute german sweet chocolate cream pie
directions: Heat chocolate and 2 tablespoons of milk over low heat, stirring until melted.
Beat sugar into cream cheese, add remaining milk and chocolate mixture, beat until smooth.
Fold Cool Whip into chocolate mixture and blend until smooth.
Spoon mixture into crust.
Freeze about 4 hours.

title: divinity
directions: In saucepan, mix first 4 ingredients.
Slowly bring to a boil, stirring until sugar dissolves.
Cook to 260° (hard ball stage). Meanwhile, beat egg whites until stiff.
Gradually pour hot syrup into whites, beating constantly.
Beat until candy begins to hold its shape.
Beat in vanilla and powdered sugar.
(This amount of powdered sugar makes a real improvement in texture.)
Drop from teaspoon onto waxed paper or pour into buttered pan.
Let stand several hours, until firm.
Store in airtight container.
Makes about 50 pieces.

title: homemade cocoa mix
directions: Mix and store in airtight container.
For 1 cup of cocoa, mix 3 tablespoons with 8 ounces of boiling water.
Makes 21 cups.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Mix egg, sugar and oil.
Add dry ingredients.
Stir in finely chopped apples and nuts.
Bake for 1 1/2 hours at 325° in a tube pan.
Makes 10 to 15 servings.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Fry bacon until crisp and break into small pieces.
Cut onion into small pieces
and
break up broccoli into bite size pieces. Mix dry ingredients in bowl.
Mix Miracle Whip, sugar and
vinegar together.	Stir
into
dry
mixture.
Chill
and serve.

title: jack's pork and sauerkraut hot dish
directions: Brown meat; drain and cube.
Put meat and sauerkraut in a large casserole dish.
Boil noodles, drain and add to casserole. Add mushrooms to casserole.

title: ice cream pie
directions: Melt butter.
Crush cookies; mix with butter and press into pie plate for crust.
Then, layer ice cream and whipped cream. Sprinkle nuts on top of pie.
Freeze for 2 hours to set.
Drizzle chocolate syrup all over pie before serving.

title: five cup salad
directions: Drain pineapple and oranges.
Mix all ingredients lightly. Place in covered container and refrigerate overnight or several hours.

title: sherried walnuts
directions: Mix everything except nuts in a 2 quart saucepan.
Boil to the soft ball stage (238° on a candy thermometer).
Remove from heat and add walnuts.
Stir until creamy.
Pour onto waxed paper and separate the walnuts with 2 forks.
Let dry before packing in airtight container to store.

title: salsa chicken in tomatillo sauce
directions: Preheat grill or broiler.
Combine lime juice, olive oil, salt and pepper in shallow dish; blend thoroughly.
Add chicken to marinade, turning to coat.

title: ham rolls
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Lightly grease a jelly roll pan.
Mix all ingredients thoroughly.
Shape mixture into 1-inch balls. Place about 2 inches apart on pan.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes or until brown.
Immediately remove from pan.
Serve warm.

title: cocoa pound cake
directions: Separate eggs and beat whites until stiff; set aside.
Cream Crisco and sugar; add egg yolks.
Sift dry ingredients together and add to cream mixture.
Fold in egg whites.
Bake at 350° in ring pan for 1 3/4 hours or until tested done.

title: grits casserole
directions: Boil first 3 ingredients until grits are done.
Add margarine, stir until melted.
Add Velveeta.
Add seasoned salt and Tabasco sauce.
Mix well and cook thoroughly to allow cheese to melt.
Add eggs to mixture.
Pour into a large baking dish and bake at 375° for 35 to 40 minutes or until set and slightly brown on top.

title: chicken parmigiana
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Dip chicken into egg and then into bread crumbs, coating thoroughly.
In a medium skillet, heat olive oil.
Cook chicken in oil until done and well browned on both sides.
Pour spaghetti sauce into an 11 x 7-inch baking dish. Place chicken on sauce and top with Parmesan and Mozzarella cheese.
Bake for 15 minutes or until cheese is melted and lightly browned.
Makes 4 servings.

title: farmers hardy breakfast(sausage gravy)
directions: Break up sausage and brown well.
Remove all but 3 tablespoons fat.
Add to sausage mixture the flour.
Brown flour medium brown; add milk.
Stir constantly.
Boil until thick.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Serve over biscuits.

title: sliced baked potatoes
directions: *Parsley, chives, thyme or sage or 2 to 3 teaspoons dried herbs of your choice may be used.

title: cheddar corn meal crackers
directions: In food processor, blend cheese and butter.
Add remaining ingredients.
Process until dough forms a ball.
Divide dough in half; shape each into 1 1/2-inch roll.
Wrap in plastic and refrigerate several hours or overnight.

title: taco pie
directions: Preheat oven 375°.
Spray 9 x 13 inch pan with nonstick spray. Brown hamburger and season with taco mix.
Then layer ingredients as follows:
Two tortilla, seasoned hamburger, half of red beans, optional ingredients as desired, half of grated cheese, repeat. Cook 30 to 45 minutes until heated through.

title: crazy cake
directions: Combine the first 5 ingredients.
Add the remaining ingredients.
Pour into a 9 x 12-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: winter fruit salad
directions: In saucepan, combine reserved pineapple juice and pudding; mix.
Cook over medium heat until thickened; cool.
Toss with pineapple and fruit chunks, nuts and coconut.
Chill until ready to serve.

title: fruit salad
directions: Take 1 cup pineapple juice or add mandarin orange juice to make 1 cup.
Mix pudding with juice.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until mixture thickens and becomes somewhat clear. Cool, add remaining ingredients.
Chill.

title: raspberry-coconut oatmeal bars
directions: *Do not add the ingredients called for on the label directions.

title: sweetened condensed milk
directions: Combine all ingredients in blender and process until smooth. Store in refrigerator until ready to use. Equal to one can.

title: festive chicken
directions: Wrap 2 bacon strips around each chicken breast; place in a shallow baking dish and set aside.
In small mixing bowl, combine soy sauce and sugar; add remaining ingredients.
Pour over chicken; turn to coat evenly.
Cover and refrigerate for several hours or overnight.
Drain and reserve marinade.
Bake at 325° for 60 minutes or until chicken tests done, basting occasionally with marinade.

title: caramel nut pound cake
directions: Cream butter and Crisco.
Add sugar.
Beat until creamy; add eggs.
Beat for 3 minutes.
Blend flour, salt and baking powder. Add creamed mixture with milk.
Add nuts and vanilla.
Bake in a tube pan 1 1/2 hours in a 325° oven.

title: sour cream
directions: Blend all together.
Makes one cup.
One-fourth cup equals 30 calories (.5 grams of fat).

title: chicken enchiladas
directions: Stew chicken; remove from pan and save broth.
Take meat off bones and cut into small pieces.
Add sour cream, 1/2 cup broth and drained chili peppers to cut up chicken.
Fill tortilla with chicken mixture (about 2 tablespoons).
Roll tortillas and place seam side down in a greased 9 x 13-inch casserole.
Cover with cheese.
Bake at 350° until cheese is melted, about 20 minutes. Serve with shredded lettuce and chopped tomatoes on the side, if desired.
Top enchiladas with salsa, if desired too.
Will keep in refrigerator for a couple of days.

title: oriental steamed dumplings
directions: In food processor combine chicken, egg white, cornstarch, oil and soy sauce.
When finely chopped place mixture in wonton wrappers.
Spray steamed with nonstick cooking spray.
Steam for 10 minutes.

title: ham and rice casserole
directions: In greased 2-quart casserole layer the rice, ham and onion. Pour milk over all. Season with salt and pepper.
Dot with butter. Bake in a covered casserole at 350° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours until rice is cooked.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: cheesecake
directions: Blend first two ingredients and 1/4 cup sugar. Press into bottom of a 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Beat cream cheese until fluffy.
Gradually add 4 cups of sugar and vanilla.
Beat in eggs, one at a time.
Blend in sour cream and lemon juice.
Spread in pan and bake in a 350° oven for about 60 minutes or until firm. Turn oven off and leave door slightly ajar while cake cools for 1 hour.
Take out and let finish cooling.
Chill in refrigerator overnight.
Top with pie filling and enjoy!!

title: potato appetizers country style
directions: Preheat oven to 375 degrees.
In bowl, combine soup mix with potatoes, butter and flour.
On floured board, roll dough to 1/4 inch thickness.
Cut into shapes with cookie cutters.
Place on ungreased baking sheet. Bake 12 minutes.

title: warm german style potato salad
directions: Cook potatoes in a large pot of boiling, salted water 12 minutes.
Add green beans and cook until potatoes and beans are tender, about 6 minutes; drain.
Transfer to a large bowl.

title: gram's rolls
directions: Heat Crisco, sugar and milk until Crisco and milk are melted. Remove from heat and cool to lukewarm.
Dissolve package of yeast in warm water, then add to sugar mixture.
Add 3 cups flour and mix well.
Let stand for 2 hours, loosely covered.

title: cornbread casserole
directions: Put all ingredients in a covered casserole.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.
Bake for another 10 minutes, uncovered.

title: low calorie soup
directions: Dice vegetables.
Add onion soup, beef bouillons and seasoning. Cover with water; boil hard for 10 minutes.
Simmer until vegetables are tender.

title: southern pecan pie
directions: Beat eggs thoroughly with sugar, dash of salt, corn syrup and melted butter.
Add the pecans.
Pour into unbaked pastry shell. Bake in moderate oven (350°) for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: shrimp cocktail
directions: Mix chili sauce, horseradish, lemon juice, Worcestershire sauce, salt and pepper; refrigerate until chilled.

title: grill-baked sweet potatoes
directions: Tear off four 6 x 9-inch pieces of heavy-duty foil.
Brush sweet potatoes with oil.
Pierce several times with fork.
Wrap potatoes in foil.
Grill potatoes on uncovered grill, over medium-hot Kingsford charcoal briquets, about 1 hour or until tender, turning once. Remove foil.
Open potatoes with tines of fork and push ends to fluff.
Top each with 1 tablespoon butter and 1 tablespoon brown sugar.

title: russian soup
directions: Put water and bouillon cubes in a 4-quart pan and bring to boil.
Add rest of ingredients and simmer for 30 minutes or until potatoes are tender.
Makes 6 servings.

title: carrot cake
directions: Sift flour once; measure and resift into mixing bowl with sugar, salt, baking powder, baking soda and cinnamon.
Add carrots, oil and eggs; beat at medium speed until batter is smooth and well blended.
Fold in nuts.
Bake in a greased 10-inch tube pan in a 350° oven for 1 hour or until done.

title: hobo dinner
directions: Layer ingredients in order given:
hamburger meat, milk, salt, pepper, potatoes, sliced onion, Cheddar cheese and mushroom soup. Cover and bake in casserole dish for 1 hour at 350°.
Remove lid last 15 minutes to brown slightly, if desired.

title: sloppy joes
directions: Brown hamburger and drain.
Add onion and cook until tender. Add remaining ingredients.
Stir.
Cover and simmer for 30 minutes.

title: rice pudding
directions: Bring all ingredients to a boil, then simmer 1 hour.
Stir every 10 to 15 minutes.
Makes a very large batch.

title: coconut cake
directions: Bake either a white or yellow cake in 2 layers. Cut the layers in half (optional). Mix sugar, sour cream and coconut. Chill. After chilling, put mixture (reserve 1 cup for later) between layers of cake. Mix Cool Whip with the 1 cup of reserved mixture & frost cake. Seal in an airtight container for 3 days in the refrigerator.

title: vegetable soup
directions: Mix all together for 17 minutes.
Put in microwave for 5 minutes.
Put on top of stove and cook at 7° for one hour.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Add butter, sugar and spices to hot potatoes.
Separate eggs. Beat egg yolks.
Add egg yolks, salt, milk and vanilla to the sweet potato mixture.
Fold in the beaten egg whites.
Pour into an unbaked pie shell and bake at 375° for 1 hour.
When cool, serve with whipped cream.
(Mrs. Edith Burlison)

title: kool-aid pie
directions: Mix well and pour into 9-inch graham cracker pie shell.

title: cabbage salad
directions: Place grated cabbage and carrots in a large container with a tight fitting lid.
In a small bowl, mix together the vinegar, sugar, mustard, salt and pepper.
Slowly add the oil, using a whisk to blend well.
Pour dressing over salad and mix thoroughly. Chill.

title: orange blossoms
directions: Stir sugar, corn syrup and orange juice into melted chocolate. Mix well, then add wafers and nuts.
Form into 1-inch balls. Roll in granulated sugar.
Seal in airtight container.
Let set several days.

title: chicken breasts(steamed in foil with sun-dried tomatoes)
directions: Place rack in center of oven and preheat to 500°.
Cut 6 (15-inch) squares of aluminum foil.
Slice sundried tomatoes into 1/8-inch strips.
Chop shallots with dill and tarragon.
In a medium saute pan, melt the butter over medium heat.
Add the shallot mixture and cook gently until shallots are soft, about 5 minutes.
Add the tomatoes to the pan, along with the cream, lemon juice and salt and pepper to taste.
Simmer over medium heat, stirring often until thickened, about 5 minutes.
Remove from heat and set aside.
Place the chicken breasts between two sheets of waxed paper and flatten them to a uniform thickness.
Spread about 1 tablespoon of the sauce on each square of foil.
Place chicken breasts on top and season with salt and pepper.
Spoon another tablespoon of sauce over chicken, then fold the packets so they are airtight, allowing a little air space between the chicken and the foil.
Place the packets on a large baking sheet.
Bake for 12 minutes.
Carefully fold back the foil and serve the chicken directly from the foil or transfer to heated dinner plates and serve.
Serves 6.

title: yummy yams
directions: Peel and slice potatoes as for large chunky French fries. Place in greased 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Mix sugar and cinnamon; sprinkle over potatoes.
Dot with margarine and pour whipping cream over the top.
Cover with foil and bake in a 450° oven for 45 minutes.
Baste as desired.
Remove cover last 15 minutes to brown.

title: red velvet cake
directions: Cream butter, sugar and eggs.
Mix and add to creamed mixture the cocoa and red food coloring.
Mix and add a little at a time to mixture the salt, vanilla and buttermilk.
Add alternately to mixture the cake flour.
Mix and add to mixture the soda and vinegar.
Do not beat.
Bake in 2 pans at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: carrot cake with cream cheese frosting
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Spray 13 x 9-inch baking pan with nonstick cooking spray; set aside.
In medium bowl mix first 7 ingredients; set aside.
In large bowl with whisk beat egg whites, sugar and oil.
Stir in next 6 ingredients until well combined. Stir in flour mixture until well combined.
Spoon into prepared pan.
Bake 35 minutes until pick comes out clean.
Cool in pan on wire rack.

title: pineapple preserve cake
directions: Cream Crisco and sugar; add eggs and mix well until fluffy. Sift flour and spices together.
Dissolve soda in buttermilk and add alternately with flour mixture into creamed mixture.
Add vanilla and mix well.
Fold in preserves and nuts last.
Bake in 3-9 x 5 x 2 1/2-inch loaf pans at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes or until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.

title: commissary chocolate chip cookies
directions: Beat sugar and butter until smooth.
Add eggs, milk and vanilla.
Combine flour, salt, baking soda and powder, then add to sugar mixture.
By hand stir in oats, chips and walnuts.
Chill dough, then place mixture on ungreased cookie sheets.
Make each one the size of a golf ball.
Bake at 350° for 12 minutes.
Do not overbake!!!

title: mama's biscuits
directions: Mama places her flour in a large bowl, makes a well in the center of it and adds the lard and milk to it.
Work it together and roll out.
She pinched off small pieces of dough and rolled them in palm of hand to make a biscuit.
Bake in a 425° oven until golden brown.

title: crab bisque
directions: Blend soups.
Stir in milk and cream.
Heat just to boiling. Add crabmeat.
Heat thoroughly.
Add sherry just before serving. Float butter atop.
Serves 6.

title: deli salad
directions: Combine all ingredients except pasta.
Mix thoroughly.
Gently stir in pasta.
Chill and serve.

title: scallops brochette
directions: You will need wooden skewers.

title: broccoli and cheese casserole
directions: Boil broccoli until 1/2 done.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch pan. Cube cheese and put on top of broccoli.
Slice 1 stick of oleo over broccoli.
In a skillet, saute 1/2 stick oleo and crumbled Ritz crackers.
Sprinkle over top.
Bake at 350° for about 20 to 25 minutes.

title: frick beef marinade
directions: Mix marinade and rub on both sides of 1 1/2 pounds of lean beef.
Cover and refrigerate 1 to 8 hours.
Broil or grill.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Combine butter and sugar; cream until light and fluffy.
Add eggs and bananas; mix well.
Combine dry ingredients.
Stir into banana mixture just until all ingredients are moistened.
Stir in pecans and vanilla.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Mix the first 5 ingredients.
Sift the flour, baking powder, soda and salt.
Combine all ingredients.
Add the vanilla.
Roll into balls the size of walnuts.
Place 3-inches apart on cookie sheet. Flatten with a fork dipped in flour.
Temperature:
375°. Time:
10 to 12 minutes.
Yields 3 dozen 2 1/2-inch cookies.

title: hot crab dip
directions: Mix all ingredients except crab meat and cook on stove until smooth.
Add crab meat until hot.
Serve on crackers or party breads.
Keep warm.

title: vermont apple slaw
directions: Combine mayonnaise, sugar and vinegar.
Mix well.
Add remaining ingredients; mix lightly.
Chill.
Serve in cabbage leaf-lined bowl and apple slices, if desired.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: smothered pork chops
directions: Salt and pepper chops; sprinkle generously with Accent.
Brown in shortening (both sides).
Remove chops; add flour, salt, pepper and Accent to drippings.
Brown, then add enough water to make a thin gravy.
Return chops to pan with gravy; steam, covered, over low heat for approximately 30 minutes.

title: molasses cookies
directions: Cream margarine with sugar.
Add molasses and beaten egg; beat.
Add dry ingredients, mixing well.
Add raisins; mix.
Drop on greased cookie sheet from a teaspoon.
Bake at 350° for 12 minutes.

title: hungarian country breakfast
directions: Fry bacon pieces.
Save about 1/3 cup drippings after removing bacon.
Add salt, pepper and paprika to onion.
Saute in drippings until tender.
Add potatoes and stir gently with onion.
Add 1 cup water and simmer on medium heat until potatoes are tender.
Add bacon and mix gently.
Simmer a little longer.
You may need to add another 1/4 cup of water.
This can be served alone or with eggs.

title: blueberry cheesecake
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
Combine crumbs, sugar and butter. Press firmly on bottom of a 9-inch spring-form pan.
In a large mixing bowl, beat cheese until fluffy.
Gradually beat in sweetened condensed milk until smooth.
Add eggs, lemon juice and flour.
Mix well.
Stir in 1 cup blueberries.
Pour into prepared pan.
Bake 50 to 55 minutes or until center is set.
Cool and chill.
Top with sauce.
Refrigerate leftovers.

title: seafood gumbo
directions: Make a dark roux with flour and oil. Add onions, pepper and celery and cook until tender. Add tomatoes, tomato sauce, bay leaf, salt and pepper to taste and water to make a thin soup consistency.
Simmer about 30 minutes. Add okra, crabmeat and shrimp. Continue simmering for another 30 minutes.
Serve over rice or corn bread.

title: clara's chili sauce
directions: Cut tomatoes into small cubes.
Add everything, except apples and spices.
Boil for 2 hours.
Add apples (chopped finely) 1/2 hour before taking from stove.
Add spices.

title: corn and lima beans
directions: In a small, heavy saucepan, bring the chicken broth to a boil. Add the lima beans and corn and reduce heat to moderately low. Cover and simmer for 8 minutes or until vegetables are just tender.
Add the sugar and pepper and cook for 2 to 4 minutes or until almost all the liquid has evaporated.
Stir in the sour cream and transfer the mixture to a warm vegetable dish.
Makes 4 servings.

title: zucchini bread(makes 2 loaves)
directions: Mix these ingredients well, then add 1 cup chopped nuts. Grease and flour pans.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 15 minutes or until toothpick comes out clean.
Cool in pans for 15 minutes, then cool on racks.

title: eggless-milkless-butterless cake with two eggs
directions: Place in 9-inch square pan that has been well-greased with vegetable shortening.
Bake at 325° for 55 minutes.
Or use a 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan and bake for 75 minutes.

title: stuffed yellow squash
directions: Scoop out inside of squash and save.
Mix raw meat and raw rice.
Season with salt, pepper and 1/2 chopped onion.
Stuff mixture inside squash.
Arrange stuffed squash in electric skillet or Dutch oven.
Pour tomatoes and tomato sauce over stuffed squash.
Add squash that was scooped out; arrange on top of stuffed squash.
Season with salt, pepper and rest of onion. Cover and simmer for 1 hour or until rice is done.

title: oriental chicken
directions: Stir together salad dressing, soy sauce and seasonings.
Place chicken on grill or broiler rack.
Brush with half of sauce. Grill or broil 8 to 10 minutes.
Turn and brush with remaining sauce.
Grill or broil 8 to 10 minutes more until tender.

title: sparkling berry punch
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Garnish with sliced lemon.
Makes 3 quarts or 24 servings.

title: fruited rice pudding
directions: In a large saucepan, mix milk and honey.
Stir and cook over medium heat until honey dissolves.
Add rice, vanilla and raisins. Turn heat to high; stir until mixture comes to a boil.
Reduce heat to medium-low; partially cover pan.
Heat for 20 minutes or until rice is cooked, stirring every 5 minutes.
Serve hot or cold, sprinkled with nutmeg and garnished with strawberries and walnuts.
Makes 4 servings.

title: cinnamon rolls
directions: Mix cake mix, flour and yeast.
Stir in water.
The dough will be sticky.
Cover and let rise until double.
Roll out and spread with margarine, sugar and cinnamon.
You can add raisins and nuts, also.
Roll lengthwise and cut in one inch slices.
Place in pan and let rise again.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: pecan coconut pie
directions: Combine eggs, sugar, margarine, lemon juice and vanilla; mix well.
Add coconut and pecans.
Pour into pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: banana bread
directions: Mix in order given.
Bake in greased pan for 1 hour in 325° oven.

title: fudge pecan pie
directions: Prepare and roll out pastry. Line a 9-inch pie plate. Trim pastry to 1/2-inch beyond edge of pie plate. Flute edge high. Line pastry with a double thickness of aluminum foil. Bake in a 450° oven 8 minutes. Remove foil. Bake 4 to 5 minutes more or until pastry is set and dry. Reduce the oven temperature to 350°.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients and pour into a greased 9 x 13-inch casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: lamb or veal shanks
directions: Pour over shanks and cook at 275° for 4 hours in covered baking pan.

title: chocolate gravy
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients, mix well.
Add milk and set aside.
Bring 1 1/2 c. water and 1 1/2 c. milk to gentle boil - add the above mixture into boiling liquid.
Stir until thickened. Add vanilla.
Serve over hot biscuits.

title: gazpacho spanish cold soup
directions: Chop cucumber, pepper and onion in blender.
Add vinegar, oil, salt and pepper.
Add tomatoes.
Blend all ingredients.
Place in individual bowls.
Add one ice cube.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Serve with crackers or Italian bread.

title: vanilla wafer cake
directions: Cream oleo and sugar.
Add eggs, beating continuously.
Add alternately the milk, crushed vanilla wafers, coconut and pecans. Bake in an angel pan 1 1/2 hours at 300°.

title: cranberry mold
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water.
While liquid is hot, stir in cranberry sauce, pineapple, celery and nuts.
Refrigerate.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Mix together and then put in 2 shortbread crumb crusts.
Put in freezer.
Very good.

title: wild onions and eggs
directions: Wash the onions.
Chop whole onion (the green tops also) into small pieces.
Boil in water to cover adding 1 tbsp. bacon grease. Boil about 20 minutes or until tender and liquid is absorbed. Break eggs into this mixture.
Stir and cook about 5 more minutes.

title: lemon bars
directions: Mix together the first 3 ingredients; press into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes (until golden brown). Meanwhile, mix the eggs, 2 cups sugar and lemon juice.
Stir in 1/4 cup flour and baking powder; pour onto baked crust.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar.
Cut when cool.

title: pecan fingers
directions: Mix all the ingredients well.
Pat into shape with hands (a small oblong shape about 2 inches long and 1-inch wide).
Cook almost 50 minutes in a very slow (300°) oven or less.
When cool, roll in powdered sugar.

title: texas grilled potato pack
directions: Take a large piece of foil; slice potatoes on the foil.
Slice onions over the potatoes.
Sprinkle cheese over this, also peppers and bacon.
Cover good with foil.
Cook on grill outside; also may be cooked in oven at 325° for about 1 hour until done.
Very good with hamburgers or barbecue.

title: irish potato casserole
directions: Peel and slice potatoes in 1/4 or 1/2-inch pieces.
Boil in salted water until tender when stuck with a fork but still in whole pieces.
Drain and place in buttered casserole dish.
Dot with butter and sprinkle with finely diced onion.
Dilute the can of soup with 1/2 can of water and spread over the potatoes.
Sprinkle with pepper and bake at 350° until slightly browned.
Serves 6.

title: orange salad
directions: Mix jello and boiling water in cake pan (9 x 13-inch).
Add undiluted orange juice, pineapple and oranges.
Refrigerate until set.
Mix milk and pudding well; add Cool Whip and spread on set jello.

title: mushroom barley soup
directions: Prepare and put all in soup pot.
Cover and cook on medium heat for 1 hour or longer.
Test for doneness.

title: creeping crystals
directions: You will need 2 two-inch jar lids, saucepan, potholder and a spoon.

title: garlic grits
directions: Cook grits according to directions on package. Remove from heat. Add all other ingredients and mix well. Pour into baking dish; bake at 375° for 30 minutes. This is a good substitute for rice or mashed potatoes. Also goes well with breakfast sausages.

title: endive
directions: Mix above ingredients, then add 1 lb. fried bacon, crumbled, endive lettuce, chopped, 1 small onion, chopped.

title: sliced tomatoes with basil vinaigrette
directions: Medium Slicer:
Slice romaine using light pressure.
Arrange on large platter.

title: speedy spinach lasagne
directions: Beat eggs in a large bowl and add Ricotta, spinach, salt and 1/4 cup Parmesan cheese.
Lightly grease bottom of 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Cover with a little sauce.
Layer noodles, half of the cheese-spinach mixture, half of the Mozzarella cheese and half of the tomato sauce.
Repeat layers, ending with tomato sauce. Sprinkle with 1/4 cup Parmesan cheese.
Cover dish with a lightly greased sheet of aluminum foil and bake in a preheated 350° oven for 60 minutes or until noodles are tender.
Let stand 10 minutes before cutting into squares.

title: cranberry sauce
directions: Put all ingredients in pan and cook until tender, about 20 minutes.

title: marinated bean salad
directions: Drain canned vegetables.
Chop onions, celery and pepper. Dissolve sugar in vinegar, oil and water.
Pour over mixed vegetables.
Let set overnight in refrigerator.
Before serving, drain liquid from salad.

title: cheese soup
directions: In saucepan, put water and bouillon and bring to a boil.
Then add celery and onion and cook for 20 minutes.
Then add potatoes, carrots and any other vegetables you have on hand.
Cook slowly until vegetables are done.
Then add cheese and soup.
Heat and serve.

title: milky way cake
directions: Melt candy and 1 stick of butter.
Set aside.
Cream sugar and 1 stick of butter.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Add flour with soda. Add alternately with buttermilk.
Add melted candy mixture.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 10 minutes.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Stir ingredients together until smooth.
Can be stored in refrigerator for months.

title: mama's cake
directions: Beat until creamy the egg yolks, sugar and salt.
Sift flour and baking powder together; add to eggs with coffee.
Beat egg whites until stiff.
Fold into batter.
Bake in 4 (8-inch) pans at 325° for about 45 minutes.

title: chili dog pie
directions: Combine baking mix, mustard and water in small mixing bowl. Stir until dough forms.
Press dough into a greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Be sure to press dough up sides of baking dish.
Set aside.
Quarter hot dogs by cutting in half lengthwise and again crosswise.
Place hot dogs on dough.
Spoon chili over hot dogs.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake at 425° for 20 minutes.

title: grandmom gori's "chumbelli's"(italian aniseed cookies)
directions: Beat eggs. Add sugar, butter, whiskey and baking powder; stir. Add flour and stir.
Keep adding flour until dough has thick consistency (not too sticky). Add the aniseed.
Knead dough until blended.
Place in oiled bowl and rub top of dough with oil. Cover and chill 2 hours.

title: vegetable beef stew
directions: Cook beef in hot oil in large Dutch oven until brown.
Add remaining ingredients.
Bring to boil.
Cover, reduce heat and simmer 2 to 2 1/2 hours.
Add additional water during cooking, if necessary.
Serve with crackers or cornbread.

title: 7-up cake
directions: Mix cake mix, pudding, oil, eggs and 7-Up together. Pour into greased and floured cake pans or 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: chocolate brownie cake
directions: Mix Crisco, margarine, cocoa and water and bring to a boil. Sift flour and sugar together. Pour boiling mixture over flour and sugar. Mix well. Add eggs, buttermilk, soda and vanilla. Put in 13 x 9-inch pan and bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: frozen fruit salad
directions: Bring water, sugar and orange juice to a boil.
Add all other ingredients.
Pour in pan and freeze.
Take out 1 hour before you want to serve.

title: fudge
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients in large boiler.
Bring to a rolling boil for 5 minutes, then add remaining ingredients.
Mix well and spoon out onto wax paper.
Makes approximately 5 pounds.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Mix together zucchini, eggs, sugar, flour, oil and vanilla. Add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Bake for 1 hour at 325° in 2 greased loaf pans.

title: breadmaker sopaipillas
directions: Place ingredients in breadmaker according to manufacturer's directions. Set on dough cycle. Remove after dough cycle. Roll into large rectangle. Fold in half. Cut into triangles. Drop into deep fryer for 1 to 2 minutes. Dust with confectioners sugar. Serve with honey.

title: chicken enchiladas
directions: Alternate mixture of the first 7 ingredients and tortillas in layers in baking dish.
Sprinkle cheese on top.
Dab with sour cream.
Bake 20 minutes at 350°.
Do not get too dry.

title: chicken-fried steak
directions: Cut steak into four equal portions.
Pound the portions until each is about 1/4 inch thick.
Place flour in a shallow bowl. In a second dish, stir together the baking powder and baking soda, pepper and salt, and mix in the buttermilk, egg, Tabasco and garlic.

Dredge each steak first in flour and then in the batter. Dunk the steaks back into the flour and dredge them well, patting in the flour until the surface of the meat is dry. Add enough shortening to a deep cast iron skillet or Dutch oven to deep fry the steaks in at least 4 inches of fat.
Bring the temperature of the shortening to 325 degrees.
Fry the steaks, pushing them down under the fat or turning them over as they bob to the surface, for 7 to 8 minutes, or until they are golden brown.
Drain the steaks, and transfer them to a platter.
Keep them warm while you prepare Gravy.
Place the steaks on separate plates and spoon mashed potatoes next to them.
Cover both generously with the gravy. Serve immediately.

title: chicken salad on melon
directions: To peel melon, cut lengthwise in half.
Remove seeds, then cut each melon-half lengthwise in half again.
Remove peel from each piece.
Cut each melon quarter into 3 slices.
Set aside.
Cut the strawberries or grapes in half.
Drain the chicken.

title: peanut butter chocolate squares
directions: Melt margarine and peanut butter together over low heat.
Add confectioners sugar and stir until smooth.
Spread mixture into a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Melt chocolate bar and spread on top of mixture. Cool completely and cut into squares.
Makes 15 to 18 servings.

title: sausage balls
directions: Melt cheese in double boiler.
