Mix with sausage and Bisquick and form in balls.
Bake at 350° until done, 15 minutes.
Makes 90 balls.

title: cider mill punch
directions: Bring to a boil.
Cover and simmer 1 hour; serve.

title: chocolate icing
directions: Melt 1 stick butter or margarine with 4 tablespoons cocoa and 6 tablespoons buttermilk.
Let come to boil.
Add 1 box powdered sugar.
Beat until ready to spread.

title: pork st. tammy
directions: Cook rice according to package; set aside.
Pour boiling water over apricots and let stand 20 minutes; drain.
Saute green pepper, mushrooms and onions in butter until tender.
Add rice, apricots, pecans and seasonings.
Cut a lengthwise slit on top of each tenderloin, being careful not to cut through bottom.
Spoon 1/2 of stuffing into the opening of 1 tender; place cut side of 2nd tender over stuffing.
Tie tenders with string and place on roasting rack.
Top with 2 bacon slices.
Repeat with remaining tenders.

title: baked pinto beans
directions: In 1 1/2-quart casserole, mix all the ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours, covered.

title: crackle top ginger cookies
directions: Mix the first 5 ingredients well.
Sift the remaining ingredients; add to first mixture.
Mix thoroughly; chill dough. Roll dough into balls; roll in sugar.
Add cinnamon to sugar, if you please.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes.
Do not press sugared balls down, as they will puff up, then become flat with a crinkly top.

title: key lime pie
directions: In double boiler beat together eggs and sugar.
Work cornstarch into softened butter and add to egg mixture.
Add lime juice, zest of rind, and salt.
Cook until thick.
Pour into graham cracker crust.
Let pie cool completely.

title: texas beef skillet
directions: Brown ground beef and onion.
Drain.
Mix beans, tomatoes, garlic powder, rice and chili.
Brown.
Simmer 20 minutes.
Melt shredded cheese on top.
Serve over tortilla chips.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Blend all ingredients together.
Pour enough milk until juicy. Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: zucchini appetizers
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix all ingredients; spread in a greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Bake until golden brown, about 25 minutes. Cut into pieces, about 1 x 2-inches.

title: vanilla wafer cake
directions: Cream butter.
Add sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Add vanilla wafers which have been crushed along with a little milk.
Add coconut and nuts, mixing well.
Line a tube cake pan bottom with wax paper.
Pour mixture into pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours, or until done.
Cool 10 minutes on rack before turning out cake.
Cake is delicious, but heavy.
No baking powder is used.

title: pickled beet salad
directions: Dissolve jello in hot water.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mold and refrigerate.

title: bunny-in-the-hole
directions: Cut a 2-inch circle in center of bread.
Set aside the bread round.
In medium skillet, over medium heat, melt 1/2 teaspoon oleo.
Saute bread until golden brown on one side.
Turn with spatula.
Break egg into hole; sprinkle with salt and pepper. Reduce heat and cover.
Cook until desired doneness.
Remove egg and toast to plate.

title: seven layer casserole
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Parboil sliced potatoes for 5 minutes and drain.
Place in bottom of greased 2-quart casserole.
In skillet, brown hamburger, salt, pepper, garlic powder, dill weed and celery.
Drain; place on top of potatoes.
Place sliced onion on top of hamburger.
Spread can of corn on top of onions.
Pour tomato soup mixed with 3/4 can water over all the layers.
Add grated cheese on top of all.
Put bread crumbs over cheese.
Bake 1 hour.

title: frosted cauliflower
directions: Remove core from cauliflower, leaving head whole.
Wash and wrap head in plastic wrap.
Microcook for 7 minutes per pound. Turn once at half cooking time.
Microwave mix of mayo, salt, mustard and Cheez Whiz 1 minute.
Spread on cauliflower.
Sprinkle with paprika and serve.

title: sausage and apple overnight casserole
directions: Fry the sausage in a skillet, breaking it up as you cook it, and drain on paper towels.
Reserve the fat.
Place the sausage in a lightly greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish, or divide between two 1 1/2-quart casserole dishes.
Saute apple slices in the sausage fat.
Combine apples, bread cubes, mustard, egg, cheese and milk and mix well.
Pour this
mixture over the sausage; cover and refrigerate overnight.
Heat oven to 350°.
Bake the casserole, covered, for 30 minutes.
Uncover and bake another 30 minutes.

title: white jello salad
directions: Mix 2 envelopes Knox gelatine and 1/2 cup water and set aside. Bring to boil the pineapple and sugar.
Add gelatine mixture and bring to a boil again.
Cream the cream cheese and Marshmallow Creme.
Add pineapple/gelatine mixture to cream cheese/Creme mixture.
Blend well.
Chill until almost set (15 minutes).
Mix the Dream Whip as directed and blend into the gelatine mixture well.
Top with nuts and chill.

title: french green bean salad
directions: Mix sugar, salad oil, white vinegar, water, black pepper and paprika.
Mix well until sugar dissolves and pour over vegetables. Cover and refrigerate for several hours.

title: peanut butter cookies(1948 kansas free fair blue ribbon)
directions: Beat the eggs until light.
Add the Crisco, brown sugar, white sugar and peanut butter.
Cream.
Add the salt, vanilla and soda. Slowly add the flour.
Pinch off dough in walnut size pieces. Press with fork both ways.
Bake at 350° for approximately 10 to 15 minutes.

title: chocolate nut pudding
directions: Sift together flour, sugar, salt, baking powder and cocoa. Add milk, melted oleo and vanilla; mix only until smooth.
Turn into greased pudding pans to a depth of 1/2-inch.

title: corn spoon bread
directions: Mix together first 6 ingredients.
Pour into a greased baking pan.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.
Sprinkle grated Swiss cheese on top and bake 10 minutes more.

title: zucchini brown bread
directions: Stir well to blend.
Pour into greased and floured pans (2 medium loaf pans).
Bake 45 minutes at 350° or until done.

title: meat balls in sour cream
directions: Mix first 10 ingredients together; form into meat balls.
Brown in fat.
Remove meat balls from fat, let fat cool, add sour cream and blend.
Heat to simmering.
Add meat balls; simmer 30 minutes.

title: german skillet(diabetic and low calorie)
directions: Brown and drain hamburger.
Add sauerkraut, celery, onion, green peppers and tomato juice.
Sprinkle 2 packets sugar substitute.
Stir.
Cover; simmer for 35 minutes.
Serves 2.

title: deviled eggs delight
directions: Boil eggs and cool.
Cut in half and place yolks in bowl.
Mix with rest of ingredients and place in egg halves.
Sprinkle with paprika.

title: oreo cookie dessert
directions: Melt butter and pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Break Oreos and place on butter.
Mix together cream cheese, powdered sugar and 8 ounces La Creme; spread over cookies.
Make chocolate pudding and spread over cream cheese mixture.
Then ice with 8 ounces La Creme and sprinkle with crushed Oreos.

title: oven hash brown
directions: Mix melted butter, cheese, soup, sour cream and salt together. Toss with onions and hash browns.
Spread in 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan that has been greased or sprayed with Pam.

title: orange salad
directions: Put in bowl and chill until firm.

title: spinach balls
directions: Cook spinach and press all the water out.
Then add remaining ingredients.
Put teaspoonful on greased cookie sheet.
Bake for 10 minutes at 350°.
Can freeze after cooled, then reheat again at 350° for 10 minutes from freezer.

title: heavenly hash sweet potato salad
directions: Peel chilled sweet potatoes and cut into small cubes; add pineapple, pecans, marshmallows and celery.
Mix orange juice with mayonnaise.
Add to salad and toss gently.
Serve on bed of lettuce and top with maraschino cherries.

title: turkey chow mein
directions: Cook celery and cabbage in oil until tender.
Add salt, pepper, sugar, soy sauce, bean sprouts, water chestnuts, turkey broth, turkey and mushrooms.
Heat to boiling.
Combine cornstarch and water and to other ingredients.
Serve over chow mein noodles. Serves 6 to 8.

title: sour cream substitute
directions: Place 1/4 cup of the milk and all the remaining ingredients in a blender.
Whirl at high speed until completely smooth.
Add up to 1/4 cup more milk (or more to your liking).

title: chocolate cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar well.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each.
Add flour, syrup and vanilla.
Bake at 350° for 2 layers for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: double crust lemon pie
directions: Combine sugar, flour and salt.
Mix well, blend in butter thoroughly with spoon.
Add eggs.
Blend until smooth.
Grate lemon rind from medium lemon.
Peel lemon, slice into paper thin slices (about 1/3 cup).
Add 1/3 cup water, grated lemon rind and slices to sugar mixture.
Blend well.
Turn lemon filling into pastry-lined pie pan.
Roll out remaining pastry.
Cut slits to allow escape of steam.
Place over filling.
Fold edge of top crust under lower crust, seal and flute edge.
Brush with egg whites and sprinkle with mixture of sugar and cinnamon.
Bake in moderate oven about 1 hour.
Cool thoroughly before serving.

title: strawberry bread
directions: Mix all dry ingredients together. Add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Bake at 350° approximately 1 hour.
Let cool in pans before removing.
Makes 2 large or 6 small loaves.
Makes great gifts.

title: raspberry tea smoothy
directions: In teapot, pour water over tea bag; brew 4 minutes.
Remove tea bag and add sugar and lemon juice; chill.
In blender, combine tea and sherbet; blend until smooth.
Serve immediately.
Makes 3 servings.

title: easy jambulaza
directions: Cut sausage into 1-inch slices. Cook in skillet until done. Add rest of ingredients except shrimp. Heat to boiling, stir occasionally, add shrimp, reduce heat. Simmer 25 minutes.

title: mexican roll ups
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Spread on tortillas.
Roll tortillas tight.
Refrigerate at least 2 hours.
Cut rolls into one inch pieces.
Discard end pieces.

title: fried corn
directions: Place corn in pan; add 1 to 1 1/2 cups water.
Stir in sugar, salt and bacon fat; cook until corn is tender.
Beat egg well with beater; beat in flour.
Thin mixture with 2 tablespoons water. Add to corn slowly, stirring.
Cook 5 minutes.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix together and form small balls. Bake at 400° until brown.

title: puppy formula
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Cook for 20 minutes.
Feed to puppies 4 to 8 weeks, during weaning.

title: country chicken bake
directions: Place rice in 13 x 9-inch greased baking dish; cover with combined vegetables and seasonings.
Combine soup and salad dressing; mix well.
Gradually add water to soup mixture; mix well until blended.
Pour half soup mix over veggies; top with chicken and cover with remaining soup mix.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until chicken and rice are tender.
Enjoy!

title: holiday ham balls
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Shape into 1-inch balls.
Place on a lightly greased pan about 2 inches apart.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes at 350° until golden brown.
Remove immediately from pan.
Yields about 7 dozen.

title: sour cream noodle bake
directions: Melt margarine in skillet.
Add ground chuck and cook until it loses its pink color.
Add tomato sauce, salt, garlic salt and pepper.
Cover and simmer 5 minutes.
Fold together noodles, onions and sour cream.
Spoon 1/2 mixture into 2 1/2-quart casserole.
Cover with half meat mixture.
Repeat layers. Sprinkle with shredded cheese.
Refrigerate or freeze.
When ready to serve, return to room temperature and bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: triple dream shake
directions: In a blender container, combine orange juice, banana, ice cubes and dry milk.
Cover and blend until mixed.
Serve right away.
Makes 1 serving.

title: shrimp mousse
directions: Add water to gelatin and mix in blender. Heat soup in saucepan and bring to a boil.
Add to gelatin in blender with cream cheese and mayonnaise.
Blend until smooth.
Pour back into saucepan and stir in remaining ingredients by hand.
Pour into a lightly greased mold and let set until firm.
Unmold and serve on lettuce.

title: chicken and broccoli dish
directions: Cook and drain broccoli; arrange in bottom of flat casserole. Add chopped toasted almonds.
Cover with cooked chicken, cut into chunks.
Pour sauce over all (recipe to follow).
Sprinkle with bread crumbs.
Bake for 45 minutes in a slow oven (325°).

title: byrdie's grape-nuts salad
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients together. Moisten with mayonnaise. Add banana and mix well. Chill several hours or overnight before serving.

title: j and j chicken salad
directions: Stir and stuff in tomato.
Serve on toast for sandwich or on crackers.

title: best bean salad
directions: Drain 3 cans of beans.
Pour contents into salad bowl.
Chop up onion and add.
Pour in vinegar and oil.
Add spices to taste. Stir and allow to marinate for 12 plus hours.
Serve chilled.

title: pineapple squares
directions: Blend flour, milk and Crisco like pie crust.
Roll out and put on cookie sheet.
Mix pineapple, tapioca and sugar and put on cookie sheet.
Bake 20 minutes at 400°.

title: oat pancakes(heart smart & low calorie)
directions: Place dry ingredients into food processor and blend until oats, flour and nuts are incorporated into a dry mix. Store in airtight container.

title: white fudge
directions: Combine sugar, sour cream, corn syrup, margarine and salt in pan.
Bring slowly to a boil, stirring until sugar dissolves. Boil, without stirring, covered 3 minutes.
Uncover and
boil on medium heat to 236° on candy thermometer.
Remove from heat and let stand 15 minutes, without stirring.
Add vanilla and beat until mixture starts to lose its glossy appearance in 8 minutes. Stir in nuts and pour into greased pan.
Cool and cut into pieces.

title: pineapple salad
directions: Combine the first 7 ingredients in a medium bowl.
Mix, stirring, the mayonnaise, sour cream and sugar. Add this dressing to salad and toss to blend.
Serve immediately on lettuce leaves. Serves 4.

title: texas potatoes
directions: Combine all ingredients in a greased 9 x 13 inch pan. Top with 2 c. crushed cornflakes mixed with butter. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: monkey bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease Bundt pan.
Cut biscuits into fourths.
Roll in white sugar and cinnamon.
Place in greased Bundt pan.
Melt margarine.
Mix with brown sugar.
Pour over dough.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
There will be brown sugar and cinnamon left.
Cool 10 minutes in pan and turn out, right side up.

title: cranberry ribbon loaf
directions: Mash cranberry sauce with fork; mix with apple.
Pack in flat layer in bottom of 8-inch square pan.
Whip the cream; add sugar and vanilla and whip until it stands in soft peaks.
Add most of nuts.
Arrange whipped cream in layer on top of cranberry mixture. Sprinkle with remaining nuts.
Freeze.
Serves 16.

title: easy potato soup
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients in a large heavy pan and bring to boil. Cover and simmer for 30 minutes. Stir in soups and milk; heat. Garnish if desired. Makes 2 1/2 quarts.

title: lazy daisy cake
directions: Combine eggs, sugar and vanilla in bowl.
Beat until light and fluffy.
Heat milk and butter in saucepan until butter is melted. Add to egg mixture; mix well.
Add sifted dry ingredients; mix well.
Pour into 8 x 10-inch greased and floured cake pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: First cream shortening, eggs and sugar to a smooth batter. Then add vanilla.
Put baking soda in milk.
Alternately add milk and flour.
Let dough set overnight for several hours.
If you want to roll out, just add a scoop or so more of flour.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Add chocolate chips.

title: letha laverty's family recipe for apple cake
directions: Blend oil, sugar, eggs and vanilla.
Add flour, soda and baking powder.
Add apples and pecans.
Bake 40 minutes at 350°.

title: potato casserole
directions: Heat soup, butter and milk until butter melts.
Add other ingredients.
Cover with corn flakes crumbs.
Sprinkle with melted butter.
Cook until done.

title: split pea soup
directions: Rejuvenate the dried onions in 1/2 cup of water.
Cook the ham hocks until they are done.
Clean the meat out and discard the skin, gristle and bone.
Use this water to cook the split peas. Always wash the hocks well.
Strain the liquid before you put it in with the peas.
When the peas are done, put the spices and onions in and simmer.
Taste; add salt or whatever until it is right.

title: easy pepperoni pan pizza
directions: Press dough into a greased 8 inch deep dish pie pan.
Spread pizza sauce over dough.
Mix meats, seasonings, and onion. Sprinkle this mixture over pizza sauce.
Top with cheese and bake for 25 minutes at 375 degrees.
Serve immediately.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli and drain.
Mix broccoli with other ingredients. Sprinkle with crushed Ritz crackers.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: simple bread
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Measure water into large mixer bowl. Sprinkle yeast over water.
Add dry milk, sugar, salt, oil and about 3 1/4 cups of flour to make a thick batter.
Blend well. Beat 3 minutes at medium speed of mixer.
By hand, gradually add remaining flour to form a very stiff dough.
Toss dough on floured surface until no longer sticky.
Knead until smooth 1 to 2 minutes.
May need to add more flour.

title: tater tot casserole
directions: Brown ground beef.
Pour into greased casserole dish.
Place chopped onion on top of beef.
Pour mushroom soup over mixture. Cover top of casserole with Tater Tots, then with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: seafoam or buttermilk salad
directions: Heat together jello and pineapple until jello dissolves.
Let cool.
Add buttermilk and Cool Whip.
Makes a large bowl.

title: smothered chicken
directions: Combine flour, salt and pepper.
Coat chicken with flour mixture.
Heat oil in large skillet.
Brown chicken on all sides; remove from skillet.
Brown remaining flour mixture in oil until golden brown, stirring constantly.
Slowly stir in water.
Return chicken to skillet; add onion.
Cover and cook over low heat until done, about 25 to 30 minutes.
Yield:
4 servings.

title: crock-pot beans
directions: Brown hamburger; pour off fat.
Put in crock-pot.
Brown bacon and onions.
Add onions and crumbled bacon to crock-pot.
Add all remaining ingredients.
Cook on low setting for 4 to 9 hours.

title: uncooked cranberry sauce
directions: Wash cranberries.
Run through a medium or fine knife or food chopper.
Peel and remove all fiber from pulp of oranges.
(I leave just a little peel on for color.)
Grind oranges through chopper. Put all ingredients together in a plastic container and let stand, covered, at room temperature for 2 hours.
This recipe makes a lot, but can be frozen.

title: kathy's pork chops
directions: Put pork chops in crock-pot.
Mix all other ingredients and pour over chops.
Cook 6 to 8 hours on low.

title: wontons or small egg rolls(korean)
directions: Mix cabbage, onion, green onions, and garlic together.
Cook in a little oil in pan.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Add meat. Stuff Wonton skins and glue them together using 2 tsp. of sugar and 1 cup of water as the glue mixture.
Fry the Wontons in hot grease.

title: cheese ball
directions: Grate Velveeta and sharp Cheddar cheese and let set at room temperature until soft.
Blend cream cheese and roll into a ball. Roll ball in pecans.
Refrigerate.
This is good to freeze.

title: no cook mint patties
directions: Blend sugar, corn syrup, butter and peppermint.
Shape into balls and flatten on waxed paper with a fork.
Let dry.
May be left in ball and dipped in chocolate.

title: pineapple cream cheese ham sandwich spread
directions: Mix all together. Good sandwiches for coffees or lunches.

title: luscious lemon bars
directions: Soften butter; blend well with powdered sugar, 3 cups flour and salt.
Press into bottom of buttered 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Blend together the remaining ingredients. Pour over first layer and continue baking for 25 minutes.
Sift additional powdered sugar over the top immediately after removing from oven.
Cool; cut into squares.
Makes 3 dozen.

title: corn pudding
directions: Pour into buttered casserole.
Bake at 350 for 30 minutes.

title: ranch casserole
directions: Cut chicken
or
turkey
in
bite
size pieces and cook until done.
Cool.
Mix soups, onion, milk and salsa together. Place 1/2 of
tortillas
on bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cover with 1/2
of meat and 1/2 of sauce and cheese.
Repeat layers; cover with remaining
cheese.
Bake
at 300° for 1 1/2 hours. Best if made the night before.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Beat this with a mixer for 5 minutes.
Add 3 eggs, one at a time and beat 5 minutes after adding each egg.
Pour into baked pie shell.
Chill 2 hours.
Can be served with whipped cream.

title: rich rice pudding
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Rinse rice.
In large saucepan, combine rice, cream, apricots, sugar, salt and cinnamon.
Simmer, stirring often, over low heat, for about 20 minutes or until rice is tender.

title: sticky buns
directions: Generously butter a tube pan.
Place frozen rolls in pan. Sprinkle pudding mix evenly over rolls.
Sprinkle nuts on top.

title: shrimp bisque
directions: In saucepan on low heat, heat all ingredients, stirring often, until hot and shrimp turn pink.
Yields approximately 5 servings of 1 cup each.

title: plantation pecan pie
directions: Beat 2 eggs and 1 egg yolk.
Stir in flour.
Beat remaining egg white in separate bowl until it holds peaks.
Beat in 3 tablespoons sugar.
Fold into first mixture.
Gradually add raisins, nuts and vanilla.
Put in an unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 425° for 10 minutes.
Lower temperature to 350°; continue baking for 30 minutes.
Cool; decorate with Cool Whip.

title: sausage casserole
directions: Mix all together and pour into large casserole dish.
Top with grated cheddar cheese.
Bake at 350° until bubbly.

title: white bean and sausage soup with pepper
directions: Melt butter in a pot. Add onions, carrot and garlic; cook, covered, over low heat until vegetables are tender and lightly colored, about 25 minutes. Add parsley, thyme and bay leaf; pour in the stock. Drain the beans and stir them into the pot. Bring to a boil; reduce heat and simmer, partially covered, until beans are very tender, 45 minutes to 1 hour. Pour the soup through

a strainer, reserving the stock. Discard the bay leaf and transfer the solids to the bowl of a food processor fitted with a steel blade or use a food mill with a medium disc. Add 1 cup of the cooking stock if using the food processor and process until smooth. Return pureed soup to the pot and stir in additional liquid, 2 to 3 cups, until soup is of the desired consistency. Cut away stems and ribs of the peppers and dice them. Heat olive oil in a small skillet; add peppers and saute over low heat, stirring occasionally, until tender but still crunchy, about 15 minutes. Transfer peppers to the soup with a slotted spoon. Skin the kielbasa if necessary; dice it and add it to the soup. Set over medium heat and cook, partially covered, until heated through, about 15 minutes. Season to taste. Serve immediately. Serves 4 to 6.

title: oven stew
directions: Mix ingredients in large casserole.
Cover.
Bake in 250° oven for 5 hours.

title: easy fruit cobbler
directions: Melt butter in pan.
Mix the ingredients.
Pour in a buttered pan.
Spoon fruit all over.
Bake at 350° until edges are firm, but middle shakes, about 30 to 35 minutes.

title: hot dog chili
directions: Pour water on cooked meat.
Stir up and add chili powder, catsup, salt and pepper.
Mix well and simmer for an hour.

title: hidden pear salad
directions: In a saucepan, bring pear liquid to a boil.
Stir in gelatin until dissolved.
Remove from the heat and cool at room temperature until syrupy.

title: peach pick-me-up
directions: Combine all ingredients in container of blender.
Add enough ice cubes to bring to 3-cup level.
Blend until smooth.
Serve immediately.
Yield: 3 cups, 184 calories per cup.

title: flour gravy
directions: Put oil in skillet and heat.
Sprinkle flour over skillet, covering bottom well.
Stir until well browned.
Gradually add water and stir until mixture thickens.
Add salt and pepper. Super when sopped with homemade biscuits!

title: "quick" lemon bars
directions: Put into a greased and floured jelly roll pan. Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes. Frost with powdered sugar frosting with lemon juice added.

title: hershey bar pie
directions: Melt the first 4 ingredients together.
Cool.
Fold in whipped cream.
Pour into crust and refrigerate.

title: ham salad spread
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Mix well together.
Cover and chill at least 2 hours.

title: beef cubes in crock-pot
directions: Mix beef cubes, dry onoin soup, cream of mushroom soup and water or milk in crock-pot.
Cook on low 6 to 8 hours.
Make noodles or rice.
Serve with beef sauce over noodles or rice.

title: zucchini streusel cake
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients together, then add vanilla and zucchini.
Add remaining ingredients.
Spoon 1/2 batter into greased and floured Bundt pan, or 11 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle streusel mix over batter.
Spoon remaining batter on top of streusel.
Bake at 350° for 55 to 60 minutes.

title: diabetic applesauce bar cookies
directions: Cream margarine with sugar until fluffy. Add egg and continue beating. Combine and sift dry ingredients, add alternately with applesauce. Stir just enough to blend. Add raisins. Pour into greased 8 inch pan. Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.

title: cranberry orange oat bread
directions: Mix flour with baking powder and salt.
Beat eggs, milk, sugar, orange rind, juice and oil.
Add to flour mixture and just enough to moisten flour.
Stir in cereal, cranberries and nuts. Pour into a well-greased 9 x 5-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 60 minutes or until tester inserted in center comes out clean.

title: smoked herring(modern)
directions: Clean and cut herring; leave head on.
Rub with a mixture of dry ingredients.
Let herring cure in mixture for 7 days at 35°. Reapply mixture when needed so that the fish is always coated. After 7 days, rinse with fresh water and hang until dry.
Smoke at 70° to 80° in a home smoker for 7 days.

title: microwave lasagna
directions: Combine sauce, water, meat and onion.
Mix cottage cheese and egg together.
Layer in 7 x 11-inch pan:
noodles, cottage cheese, Mozzarella cheese and sauce.
End with noodles and sauce on top. Cover with plastic wrap.
Cook in microwave on High for 8 minutes. Reduce temperature to Medium-low and continue cooking for 32 minutes.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese after removing from oven.

title: rigatoni with italian sausage
directions: Brown sausage.
Remove and brown garlic, onions and green peppers.
Stir occasionally.
Add to rest of ingredients and simmer 2 hours, stirring occasionally.
Cook rigatoni as instructed on package.
Serve sauce over rigatoni and garnish with Parmesan cheese.
Serves 6.

title: old fashion chocolate pie
directions: Mix sugar, flour, salt and cocoa.
Add milk and beaten egg yokes. Cook until thick (about 20 minutes) stirring constantly. Remove from heat and add butter and vanilla.
Stir until butter is melted.
Pour into 9 inch baked pie shell.

title: grandma's pound cake
directions: Beat the yolks and whites of the eggs separately.
Cream the butter; cream the sugar into it.
Add the egg yolks; mix well. Add the stiff egg whites alternately with the flour.
Put into the oven when you can still bear to put your hand on the bottom of the oven.
Gradually increase the oven heat to moderate (350°) and bake for 2 hours.

title: yogurt pie
directions: Mix crushed wafers and melted margarine and pat into pie pan. Crust does not have to be baked.
Mix yogurt and Cool Whip.
Pour into prepared crust.
Put pie into freezer until ready to use.

title: soft chocolate chip cookies
directions: Cream margarine and sugars thoroughly.
Add eggs and vanilla. Beat until fluffy.
Sift together flour, soda and pudding, then add to mixture.
Fold in chips.
Drop by spoon onto cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: death by chocolate
directions: Bake brownies and cool.
Poke holes in brownies with fork. Pour Kahlua over.
Make mousse according to directions.
Break Heath bars into small pieces.
Layer in a large clear bowl as follows:
1/2 brownies, 1/2 mousse, 1/2 Heath bars, 1/2 Cool Whip. Repeat layers.
Save small amount of candy to garnish top.

title: pecan pie
directions: Melt butter.
Add sugar and blend.
Add beaten eggs, salt, syrup, vanilla and pecans.
Pour into pie shell.
Bake at 325° about 50 minutes or until set.

title: diabetic orange nut cookies
directions: Cream Crisco; add eggs.
Then add sweetener and orange juice; beat well.
Sift flour, baking powder and salt.
Add dry ingredients to first ingredients and mix gently.
Add vanilla and nuts.
Drop by spoonfuls onto greased baking sheet.
Bake at 350° for 12 minutes.

title: icing
directions: Mix milk and flour.
Cook over medium heat until thick, stirring constantly.
When cool, beat with creamed 10x sugar, Crisco, butter and vanilla.
Mix everything together, the longer the creamier.

title: frosty orange treat
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water.
Stir in orange sherbet until well blended.
Fold in drained fruit.
Chill until firm.

title: apple jack
directions: Put
apples in large baking dish.
Combine dry ingredients. Pour lemon juice over apples.
Sprinkle dry ingredients over apple mixture.
Add pecans.

title: french coffee
directions: Mix coffee, boiling water and sugar in large bowl until dissolved; add milk and ice cream.
After mixing well, pour into cups and put 2 tablespoons Cool Whip on top of each cup.

title: zucchini appetizers
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees.

title: potato soup
directions: Boil potatoes, onions and celery in water until tender. Remove vegetables, reserving broth.
Blend vegetables in blender or force through sieve.
Return to broth.
Add pepper, salt, flour and butter to cream and stir into soup.
Stir in parsley and dill.
Reheat to serving temperature, but do not boil.
Makes 6 to 8 servings and may be frozen.

title: no fat chocolate cake(sunset magazine, 5-1991)
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients.
Beat next 4 ingredients until well blended.
Stir in flour mixture and beat until evenly moistened. Pour batter into a nonstick 8-inch square pan (or coat an unfinished pan with spray and dust with flour).
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Let cake cool 15 minutes.
Invert onto serving plate.
Dust cake with powdered sugar.
Makes 8 servings, 220 calories each serving, 0.8 gram fat, 230 mg sodium and 0.6 mg cholesterol.

title: angel cookies
directions: Beat sugars with Crisco; add egg.
Add soda, cream of tartar, salt and vanilla, then add flour.
Beating with the mixer is what makes these cookies light and tender.
Mix chips and walnuts in by hand.
Roll in balls (size of walnuts).
Bake at 350° about 10 minutes.

title: pepper steak stir-fry
directions: Cook rice according to package directions.
While rice is cooking, melt butter in 10-inch skillet over medium-high heat. Add beef and garlic.
Cook and stir 2 minutes; push to one side. Add mushrooms.
Cook and stir 1 minute.
Add pepper strips, broth, pepper and salt.
Cook and stir until peppers are crisp-tender, about 2 minutes.
Stir in green onions.
Serve over hot, cooked rice.
Serves 2 to 4.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Put Fleischmann's in 9 x 13-inch pan and melt.
Then put peaches in.
Mix all other ingredients well and pour in pan.
Bake at 350° until done.

title: soft pretzels
directions: Dissolve yeast and sugar in water.
Let set 5 to 10 minutes. Add 2 cups of flour, salt and oil.
Beat until smooth.
Gradually put in more flour to make dough soft.
Knead dough until smooth and elastic.
Add more dough, if sticky.
Place dough into greased bowl; cover and let set until risen (45 minutes to 1 hour).

title: scotcharoos
directions: Bring white sugar and Karo syrup to a boil in large quart pan. Remove from heat, stirring all the time.
Add peanut butter and Rice Krispies.
Mix together well.
Press into a buttered pan. Melt together chocolate chips and butterscotch chips in a double boiler and spread over top.
Let cool.

title: pecan pie
directions: In saucepan, combine corn syrup, sugar and butter or margarine.
Bring to boiling.
Boil gently, uncovered, 5 minutes. Stir occasionally.
Cool slightly.
Prepare and roll cut pastry. Line a 9-inch pie plate with pastry.
Flute edge; do not prick pastry.
Place pecans in pastry shell.
Combine eggs, vanilla and salt.
Pour cooled syrup mixture into eggs and beat well.
Pour over nuts (pecans will rise to top).
Bake in 375° oven for 30 to 35 minutes or until knife inserted near center comes out clean. Cool before serving.
Cover; chill to store.

title: cream of broccoli soup
directions: In saucepan, combine chicken broth, chopped onion, broccoli and spices.
Bring to boil.
Reduce heat.
Cover and simmer 15 to 20 minutes or until vegetables are tender.
Remove bay leaf and set aside.

title: mexican beef hero's
directions: Cook bacon until crisp; drain.
Brown beef and onion in bacon drippings.
Stir in green chilies, olives, catsup, salt and chili powder.
Cook 5 minutes, stirring occasionally.

title: chocolate zucchini cake
directions: Cream oleo, oil and sugar.
Add eggs, vanilla and sour milk. Beat.
Mix together dry ingredients; add to liquid mixture.
Stir in zucchini.
Spoon batter into greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle chips on top.
Bake for 55 minutes at 325°.

title: russian tea
directions: Bring water to a boil in a large saucepan.
Add tea bags; remove from heat.
Cover for 15 minutes.
Remove tea bags.
Add all other ingredients.
Bring to a boil again; boil for 5 minutes. Serve or refrigerate and heat at serving time.
Serves 12 to 15.

title: louisiana yam pie
directions: In large mixing bowl, mix yams, brown sugar, cream, milk, eggs, salt, cinnamon, nutmeg and ginger.
Pour into pastry shell. Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until knife put in center comes out clean.

title: banana split torte
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients and press into a 9 x 13-inch pan. Chill.
Combine the margarine, eggs, sugar and vanilla and beat until smooth.
Spread on crust.
Next, place sliced bananas on crust mixture.
Spread pineapple over bananas.
Spread on Cool Whip.
Sprinkle with chopped nuts.
Garnish with cherries.

title: melinda's pumpkin dump cake
directions: Melt butter and set aside.
Mix first 7 ingredients in a 13 x 9-inch pan or casserole dish.
Pour cake mix over the top of the mixture (do not mix with other ingredients).
Pour melted butter over cake mix.
Bake at 350° until brown, around 30 minutes.

title: artichoke dip
directions: Combine all ingredients together and bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes until puff or golden.
Bake in a shallow dish for 25 minutes.
Serve with plain crackers.
Serves 10.

title: blueberry cobbler
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Place fruit in greased 9 x 9-inch baking dish.
Cut crusts from bread and cut each slice into 5 fingers. Place bread fingers over berries.
In a bowl, mix sugar, flour, egg and butter.
Pour over bread and fruit.
Bake for 35 to 45 minutes until golden.
Serves 5 or 6.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix melted butter with crushed Ritz crackers.
Spray casserole dish with Pam.
Sprinkle layer of cracker crumb mixture on bottom of baking dish.
Add chicken mixture and top with remainder of crumbs.
Bake at 350° until casserole bubbles.

title: golden anniversary punch
directions: Combine all ingredients, except Ginger Ale.

Freeze in zip-lock bags (I put three in one gallon bag); then later add 1-2 liters of Ginger Ale for each zip-lock bag that is put in the punch bowl. Remove frozen bag from the freezer for 45 minutes before serving. Just before serving, add the Ginger Ale.
Yields 45- 50 cups.

title: savannah red rice
directions: In a large skillet, fry bacon crisp. Remove to paper towel. Brown bell pepper and onions in drippings.
Add rice, tomatoes, sauce and crumbled bacon.
Add cooked sausage.
Pour into
greased 9 x 13-inch casserole dish.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese and bake at 325° for 30 minutes or until rice is dry enough to separate.

title: muffins
directions: Mix ingredients and pour into greased muffin pan.
Bake in 350° oven for about 20 minutes.
Makes 12 small or 8 large muffins.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Melt margarine in dish.
Set aside. Mix together flour, sugar and milk.
Pour in dish with butter; add peaches.
Bake at 450° for approximately 40 to 45 minutes.

title: mrs. smith's homemade chili beans
directions: Brown ground chuck and onion; add tomato juice.
Mix flour and chili powder together; sprinkle over meat mixture.
Add chili to amount and kind of beans you desire.
Add meat mixture and cook slowly for about 2 hours.

title: tex mex dip
directions: Brown ground beef, then drain.
Cut cheese into small squares. Combine all ingredients into a crock-pot on high.
Stir occasionally until mixture is bubbly.
Use as a dip or pour over tortilla chips.
It is wonderful.

title: soda bread
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Mix together dry ingredients.
Make a well in the center and add wet ingredients, including raisins.
Mix well by hand.
Turn onto lightly floured surface and knead until smooth.
Spray a 9-inch round cake pan with nonstick cooking spray.
Pat in the dough.
With a sharp knife, cut an "X" into top of dough.
Bake for 35 to 40 minutes, until golden brown.

title: lasagna pizza
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Grease cookie sheet.
Brown and drain hamburger.
Stir in tomato sauce, water and spaghetti sauce mix. Simmer.

title: lemon chicken
directions: Place chicken pieces in baking dish.
Pour lemon juice over chicken.
Sprinkle with garlic salt and pepper.
Lay lemon slice on each piece of chicken.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 45 minutes on one side.
Turn and bake for 30 minutes longer.

title: rhubarb and strawberry soup
directions: Combine strawberries, rhubarb and water and boil for 5 minutes.
Set aside for 2 hours.
Place the soup in blender and add lemon juice, sugar and sour cream.
Blend until smooth.
Serve hot or cold.
Serves 6.

title: party shrimp
directions: Put all the ingredients in a pot and bring to a boil, then reduce the heat immediately.
Simmer 3 minutes or until the shrimp turn pink.
Cool the shrimp in the liquid, then shell and devein. Chill and serve with Cocktail Sauce (recipe following).
Serves 4.
